review_text: Suasana dan makanannya menyenangkan, top
review_translated_text: The atmosphere and food are fun, top

review_text: Enak
review_translated_text: Nice

review_text: Sudah beberapa kali saya ketempat ini kalau ke jogja, kopinya enak, layanan cepat dan suasana sangat bagus, walau awal pertama kesana kurang mengasikkan.
review_translated_text: Ive been to this place several times when Ive been to Jogja, the coffee is delicious, the service is fast and the atmosphere is very good, even though the first time I went there wasnt that exciting.

review_text: Pertama kali ke Legend, karena ada undangan dari bank Mandiri. Makanan enak, minuman oke. Sup Iga Nachos Garlic bread B aja Lychee tea Degan yang menjadi pertanyaan, kenapa harus kasih jaminan Kartu ATM atau deposit uang 100K sebelum duduk bagi customer yang bukan kategori Corporate? Misalnya takut customer lari, sebaiknya pakai sistem bayar dulu baru duduk. Ada keuntungan untuk legend sendiri, dan customer saya rasa akan lebih nyaman. Spot waitress juga baiknya diperbanyak, sehingga Customer tidak harus jalan ke depan untuk order. Terimakasih.
review_translated_text: First time going to Legend, because there was an invitation from Bank Mandiri. Good food, okay drinks. Rib Soup Nachos Just garlic bread B Lychee tea Degan The question is, why do you have to provide an ATM card guarantee or a deposit of 100K before sitting down for customers who are not in the Corporate category? For example, if you are afraid of customers running away, you should use a pay first then sit down system. There are benefits for the legend itself, and I think customers will be more comfortable. There should also be more waitress spots, so that customers dont have to walk to the front to order. Thank You.

review_text: Sore2 datang ke sini. Pesan cafe latte arang dan cafe latte green tea. Unik juga rasanya.... Untuk harga ya mirip dg cafe yg lain. Sore kondisi masih blm terlalu rame, bnyk pilihan kursi dan meja. Tinggal pilih aja. Kebanyakan di luar jd cocok bagi para smoker dan vaper. Tersedia macam2 snack dan jg makan besar.
review_translated_text: Come here in the afternoon. Order the charcoal cafe latte and green tea cafe latte. It feels unique too.... For the price, its similar to other cafes. In the afternoon it was still not too busy, lots of choices of chairs and tables. Just choose. Most of it is outside so it is suitable for smokers and vapers. There are various kinds of snacks and large meals available.

review_text: Tempatnya unik otentik dan luas.. ada live music nya.. untuk makanan harganya terjangkau dan porsinya besar cocok untuk kumpul bersama teman2 atau keluarga
review_translated_text: The place is unique, authentic and spacious.. there is live music.. the food is affordable and the portions are large, suitable for gatherings with friends or family

review_text: The place is spacious and comfortable. The food is delicious at standard prices. Suitable for hanging out with your bestie. There is a meeting room too. Dont forget to stop by
Lumayan
review_translated_text: Reasonable

review_text: Worth it, suasananya nyaman dan makanannya enak, pegawainya juga ramah, ada live musicnya juga.. Banyak tempat duduknya In frame Chicken Katsu, Spaghetti Carbonara, French Fries, Lychee Squash, Hot Hazelnut Latte Vegetarian options: Ada salad sayur bagi vegetarian Parking: Dekat dengan pintu masuk
review_translated_text: Worth it, the atmosphere is comfortable and the food is delicious, the staff are friendly, there is live music too... Lots of places to sit In frame Chicken Katsu, Spaghetti Carbonara, French Fries, Lychee Squash, Hot Hazelnut Latte Vegetarian options: There is a vegetable salad for vegetarians Parking: Close to the entrance

review_text: Makanan minuman enak, tempatnya luas enak buat nugas atau kumpul2 sm temen bahkan sm keluarga

review_text: Makanan indonya enak enak banget sih parah, kopinya aja ya kureng

review_text: over all enak makanannya, tapi mengecewakan sekali, saya cuma minta air putih biasa. kenapa kena charge  es ??? kalo minta air putih biasa aja bayar, mending saya beli air mineral sekalian,
review_translated_text: over all the food is delicious, but very disappointing, I just asked for plain water. why does it get charged ice??? If you ask for plain water, just pay, its better if I buy mineral water too.

review_text: Pertama kesini dengan teman-teman Relawan Jurnal Indonesia

review_text: Large and cozy cafe and restaurant near malioboro. Nice to enjoy with friends, business partner or couple. The food and beverages also tasteful. Service for customer keep improving time by time especially interaction with customer and responses. Standard price. Cash and non cash payment. Paid parking service and slightly narrow for cars. Recommended.
Pelayanan ramah the best, suasana bikin nyaman betah nongki, makanan jg gk kalah enak2 jg.
review_translated_text: The best friendly service, the atmosphere makes you feel comfortable hanging out, the food is no less delicious too.

review_text: Good for coworking space Kid-friendliness: Ok Wheelchair accessibility: Ok
makanannya cepat datangnya walaupun lagi agak rame

review_text: Piliham menu banyak.. Rasa standar... Tempat luas, banyak pilihan tempat duduk..cocok untuk nongkrong atau kerja/nugas... Lokasi mudah di cari & strategis
review_translated_text: Lots of menu choices... Standard taste... Spacious place, lots of seating options... suitable for hanging out or working/on assignment... The location is easy to find & strategic

review_text: The most durable cafe among the many new cafes that are scattered around The homey concept is always acceptable & makes you feel at home hanging out there for a long time 10 years ago the concept was still open 24 hours but yesterday when I went there I realized that there were already opening and closing hours.
Pelayanan cukup ramah, minuman standar, suasana ckup nyaman. Hanya saja rasa masakan makanannya kurang istimewa dengan harga rata-rata 35+. Semoga ada perbaikan. Terimakasih
review_translated_text: The service is quite friendly, the drinks are standard, the atmosphere is quite comfortable. Its just that the taste of the food is less special with an average price of 35+. Hopefully there will be improvements. Thank You

review_text: Hati-hati buat yang pake maps krna kalau pakai jalan maps biasanya diarahkan dr blkg yg mana ga bs dilalui kendaraan. Tukang angkringan disitu juga bilang byk yg suka kesasar kesitu kalo pake maps. Ancer2nya dr pasar ngasem aja nnti ketemu pertigaan yg ada pohon beringinnya terus belok kiri kalo dr pasar ngasem, stlh itu lurus dah nyampek. Sekarang sy ulas menu2nya, waktu itu sy dipesankan bbrpa menu makanan. Favoritku dan aku rekomendasikan juga adalah java beer tapi lupa ga kefoto, selebihnya menu makanannya biasa aja rasanya. Dessertnya enaak tapi lupa namanya. Utk suasana tenang dan ayem dgn nuansa bangunan jawa.  Tempat bersih toilet bersih. Tapiii sgt disayangkan kolam air mancurnya bau menyengat, warnanya juga hijau. Waktu ksna ada pertunjukan tari juga. Dan disana juga ada galeri seninya jd bs sekalian keliling galeri seni. Dari segi pelayanan sudah bagus tapi ada karyawan yg menurut sy kurang ramah.
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih kak lulu-u Azizah telah berkunjung ke Bale Raos. Terimakasih atas reviewnya yg diberikan. Kami mohon maaf atas ketidaknyamanannya. Akan kami jadikan evaluasi untuk team kedepan. Kami tunggu kedatangannya kembali di Bale Raos Restoran kak. Terimakasih
review_translated_text: Be careful for those using maps because if you use maps roads are usually directed from the block which cannot be passed by vehicles. The angkringan worker there also said that many people like to get lost there if they use maps. Just go from the Ngasem market and youll find a T-junction with a banyan tree, then turn left if you come from the Ngasem market, then go straight and youll reach it. Now Im reviewing the menus, at that time I ordered several food menus. My favorite and the one I also recommend is Java beer but I forgot not to take a photo, the rest of the food menu is just ordinary. The dessert is delicious but forgot the name. For a calm and serene atmosphere with the feel of a Javanese building. Clean place, clean toilet. But its a shame that the fountain pool has a strong smell, and the color is also green. At that time there was a dance performance too. And there is also an art gallery there so you can also go around the art gallery. In terms of service, it is good, but there are employees who in my opinion are not friendly.

review_text: Berkesempatan menikmati menu Sultans Dishes yang terletak di area Keraton Yogyakarta. Konsep dining dengan menu rata rata tradisional khas Yogyakarta. Secara umum taste yang ditawarkan tidak sekedar manis dan legit seperti stereotip masakan Jawa namun juga gurih. Sebenarnya tidak ada menu khas atau yang paling direkomendasikan, karena tiap menu punya keunikan dan kelebihannya sendiri. Pelayanan ramah dengan hospitality seperti di hotel berbintang. Ruangan resto cukup luas dan ada beberapa spot duduk, kesan dan ornamen Yogyakarta yang kental.
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih kak YN Alvana telah meluangkan waktu untuk berkunjung mencicipi hidangan Bale Raos Restoran Yogyakarta. Terimakasih juga atas review yg diberikan. Kami berharap kak YN Alvana berkenan dengan sajian dan pelayanan dari team kami. Kami tunggu kedatangannya kembali di Bale Raos Restoran Yogyakarta    terimakasih
review_translated_text: Have the opportunity to enjoy the Sultans Dishes menu which is located in the Yogyakarta Palace area. Dining concept with a traditional menu typical of Yogyakarta. In general, the taste offered is not just sweet and delicious like the stereotype of Javanese cuisine but also savory. Actually, there is no typical or most recommended menu, because each menu has its own uniqueness and advantages. Friendly service with hospitality like in a star hotel. The restaurant room is quite spacious and there are several seating spots, with a strong Yogyakarta impression and ornaments.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you, Sis YN Alvana, for taking the time to visit to taste the dishes at Bale Raos Restaurant Yogyakarta. Thank you also for the review given. review_text: Makanan cenderung manis ya, mungkin karena lidah orang jawa yang cenderung manis. Aneh saja Garang Asemnya kok jadi manis hehehehe. Awal pengen nyobain menu bukbernya, dengan seharga 100rb ke atas per orang harusnya tempatnya lebih proper ya, dalam arti bebas lalat dan adem, tapi sebaliknya, saya dan teman saya berasa di-steam sampai keringatan. Lalat yang berterbangan di sekitar tempat makan juga bikin kurang nyaman. Mungkin tempat wudhu juga bisa dibikin lebih proper lagi. Dari segi pelayanan sudah OK banget, hanya saja perlu dibenahi kualitas makanan dan tempatnya.
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih kak Bee telah berkunjung ke Bale Raos Restoran. Terimakasih juga atas masukannya kepada kami. Atas nama manajemen kami memohon maaf. Akan kami jadikan evaluasi kedepannya . Kami tunggu kedatangannya kembali kak.Terimakasih
review_translated_text: Food tends to be sweet, maybe because the Javanese tongue tends to be sweet. Its strange how the Garang Asem is so sweet hehehehe. Initially I wanted to try the bukber menu, at a price of 100 thousand and above per person, the place should have been more appropriate, in the sense of being fly-free and cool, but instead, my friend and I felt like we had been steamed to the point of sweating. Flies flying around the dining area also make it uncomfortable. Maybe the ablution place can also be made more appropriate. In terms of service, its really OK, it just needs to be improved on the quality of the food and the place.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you, Sis Bee, for visiting Bale Raos Restaurant. Thank you also for your input to us. On behalf of management, we apologize. We will make an evaluation in the future. We are waiting for your return, sis. Thank you

review_translated_text: When I come here I forget what date it is, usually I just buy mcflurry ice cream   in my opinion... its better to buy it here if you eat in Malioboro   if mcd is delicious the food is delicious. Not like the expensive ones but there are no side dishes  ice cream, the food is delicious. Just yesterday I ordered lemon tea if Im not mistaken, he gave me Coca Cola instead  but its okay

review_text: Menikmati makan siang di Malioboro tapi di luar benar-benar panas, jadi ya paling sejuk makan di McD Malioboro Mall. Secara, si kecil juga suka banget dengan fried chicken dan si besar paling suka dengan es krim jadi ya sudah pas lah kalau kita makan disini. Sebetulnya saya dan istri kepingin banget kulineran ke beberapa tempat yang sudah kami hunting tapi karena anak-anak sudah tidak sabar jadi disini tempat terbaik bagi anak-anakku.
review_translated_text: Enjoying lunch at Malioboro but its really hot outside, so its coolest to eat at McD Malioboro Mall. In fact, the little one also really likes fried chicken and the big one really likes ice cream so its only fitting that we eat here. Actually, my wife and I really wanted to go to some of the places we had hunted for culinary delights, but because the kids couldnt wait, this was the best place for my kids.

review_text: Sama kayak mcd pada umumnya, karna di mall jadi tempat duduknya terbatas & kalo rame bisa ga dpt tempat duduk,, antrinya juga pjg apalagi pas weekend & Libur sekolah, mudah di cari ketika masuk mall.
review_translated_text: Just like McDs in general, because in malls there are limited seats & if its busy you might not get a seat, the queue is also long, especially on weekends & school holidays, its easy to find when entering the mall.

review_text: Kayaknya cukup terakhir ini saya beli makan dicabang plaza malioboro. Yg tempo hari dpt ayam yg kyak minyaknya sdh brkli2 bt goreng, ayamnya bnr2 tampilannya gak bgt berminyak kecoklatan kyak jlantah pd nempel ,sama olive enakan olive khusus cabang yg malioboro. Dan yg kmrn kentangnya asiiinnn banget Kl kesini kyky cukup beli eskrim aja, kl pgn mkn berat lebih baik yg cabang sudirman atau ambarukmo
review_translated_text: I think this is the last time I bought food at the Malioboro Plaza branch. The other day I got chicken that looked like the oil had just been fried, the chicken really didnt look like it was oily, brownish like it was stuck to it, the olive was delicious, especially the Malioboro branch. And yesterday the potatoes were really delicious If you come here, just buy ice cream, if you want to eat a heavy meal, its better to go to the Sudirman or Ambarukmo branches.

review_text: Kasir gak ramah blas.
review_translated_text: The cashier is not very friendly.

review_text: Jutek banget kasirnya. Nuggetnya juga agak2 gosong.
review_translated_text: The cashier was very rude. The nuggets were also a bit burnt.

review_text: Nothing special, a little old and not very clean. It has few seats

review_text: Good place, strategic location. But oh my God, the bathroom is so dirty, even if you want to wash your hands, the sink is all broken, some are full of water and you cant get in. The toilet is really disgusting... Places on the outskirts of the city like that should maintain a level of cleanliness.

review_text: Beli panas 2 ayamnya besar kecil ko gk bisa request ya? Kan saya pembeli..beda bgt sama di tmpt saya

review_text: Makanannya enak standar Mc Donald, layanan juga baik, cuma tempatnya menurut saya agak sempit jadi kurang leluasa, mungkin karena letaknya di Mall. Dan karena di tempat wisata jadi pengunjung juga banyak.
review_translated_text: The food is delicious at Mc Donalds standards, the service is also good, but in my opinion the place is a bit narrow so theres not enough space, maybe because its located in the mall. And because its a tourist spot, there are also lots of visitors.

review_text: McD Jogja di Malioboro, tapi ikonnya Borobudur di Magelang. Wkwkwk
review_translated_text: McD Jogja is in Malioboro, but the icon is Borobudur in Magelang. Hahaha

review_text: Three times we visited McDonalds Jogja. We got Cold burgers and french fries 3 times . We had asked for extra toppings on our burgers and were charged more $$ and got nothing extra.  This store is not a very good standard for McDonalds in Indonesia or the world. Very disappointed. The toilets smells of urine . The manager needs to fix this as soon as possible. Come on McDonalds look after your customers please . Please take care, sorry for the bad review. Looking at the other reviews we are not the only people dissatisfied.

Saya diberi nasi yang ada bagian terbuka sehingga nasi kering, dan di buru2 padahal tidak ada antrian. Karena saya dan pasangan saya menggunakan sendal jepit. Sayangnya tidak saya foto nasi kerinngnya
review_translated_text: I was given rice that had an open part so the rice was dry, and I was rushed even though there was no queue. Because my partner and I wear flip-flops. Unfortunately I didnt take a photo of the dry rice

review_text: Bukan masalah nominal tp kejujuran sekitar jam 15.00 ngasih 50rban 2 lembar kasirnya gak kasih kembalian ciri2 kasir perempuan pakai ikat rambut kamboja trus dy taruh uang 60rb diatas meja pada saat sy lengah ambil 500rupiah yg dia minta..
review_translated_text: Its not a matter of nominal but honesty, around 15.00 I gave 50 thousand rupiah for 2 pieces. The cashier didnt give me change. Characteristics of the female cashier was wearing a frangipani hair tie and then she put 60 thousand rupiah on the table when I was careless and took the 500 rupiah she asked for...

review_translated_text: Viavia Jogja Bakery is located in Prawirotaman, the pastries, cakes and bread are very delicious, this place was also a shooting location for AADC II. Highly recommended for you pastry lovers. Dont forget to stop by if you go to Jogja, you wont regret it

review_text: We came three days for breakfast, lunch and dinner. The food is very delicious and economical. The staff is very polite and friendly. The best place to eat in this area of Yogja. Recommended
review_translated_text: Vinimos tres dias a desayunar, almorzar y cenar. La comida es muy rica y economica. El personal es muy educado y amable. El mejor sitio para comer en esta zona de Yogja. Recomendado

review_text: Konsep store-nya grab and go gitu, asik banget kalo buru-buru nggak banyak milih lagi. Sebagai pencinta roti keras, ini bakal jadi salah satu destinasi di Jogja. Karena setauku masih dikit yang jual sourdough ready stok, biasanya harus PO dulu. Harganya juga terbilang cukup terjangkau ya.
review_translated_text: The concept of the store is grab and go, its really cool if youre in a hurry, theres not much to choose from. As a lover of hard bread, this will be one of your destinations in Jogja. Because as far as I know there are still very few who sell ready stock sourdough, usually you have to PO first. The price is also quite affordable.

review_text: Dari dulu suka banget beli ditempat ini Rasanya enak dan harganya terbilang murah Tempat dan suasananya nyaman bgt. Serasa lagi kayak bukan di Jogja. Disini banyak pilihan menu dessert yang bisa dipilih. Pokoknya gak pernah nyesel beli dari Viavia Thank u
review_translated_text: Ive always loved buying from this place It tastes delicious and the price is relatively cheap The place and atmosphere are really comfortable. It feels like Im not in Jogja. Here there are many dessert menu options to choose from. Anyway, never regret buying from Viavia Thank u

review_text: Maaf untuk memberikan Bintang 1 untuk resto yang adalah resto favoritku di Prawirotaman. Bukan karena Makanan, bukan karena Harga, bukan karena ambience nya. Tapi ada bapak2 namanya Bembeng ( kalo ga salah) aneh banget suka sksd sama org2 bikin ga nyaman. Seluruh staff tau dan emang orang ini suka bikin onar. Pesen cuma bir tp gayanya selangit . Untuk management, pleaseeeee tolong dibaca dan dipahami, sayang banget orang2 pada pergi gara2 si bapak2 gatau diri ini.
review_translated_text: Sorry to give 1 star to this restaurant which is my favorite restaurant in Prawirotaman. Not because of the food, not because of the price, not because of the ambience. But there is a guy called Bembeng (if Im not mistaken) who really likes to mess with people who make him uncomfortable. The entire staff knows that this person really likes to cause trouble. Ordered just beer but the style was exorbitant. For management, pleaseeeee please read and understand, its really a shame that people are leaving because these gentlemen dont know themselves.

review_text: Good things first: -nice and comfy atmosphere with good music -staff really nice and friendly -banana almond peanut butter drink and cappuccino really nice. Unfortunately the food was not tasty at all. Falafel not crunchy at all with no specific taste, burger pattie the same. Potato wedges were good. Black coffee average. Feels a bit overrated. Parking: Moto only, parking opposite restaurant

There are a lot of foreigners, and some foreigners cook for themselves. So far, I think this is the most delicious meal in Indonesia. It costs 150 per person. Bintang Beer 50 can fill two glasses The French fries are delicious. They were served right after they were fried. They are just not very flavorful. You can sprinkle them with salt yourself. Creamy pasta is not bad, you can choose chicken or beef, the creamy flavor is very strong Beef bone soup is served with rice. The bones are delicious and the soup has a strange spice flavor. Vegetarian meat burrito with mashed potatoes and garlic sauce, so-so
review_translated_text: 150 bintang   50

review_text: Pretty tasty Indonesian food!! The service is good, friendly staff. I really recommend this place if you wanna try Indonesian food plus, pretty good prices.
Nice place but a bit hot during day
We would have eaten every meal here if we could have. Excellent food for all tastes and service in a vibrant atmosphere. Vegetarian options: Many vegetarian and vegan options.
Feels like in Kuta, lots of foreigners, lots of fans who drink beer For standard Indonesian and western tasting food but the presentation looks good looking
I love the Night Jazz
Great athmosphere, good food, you can also choose your sour dough bread and eat here.

A must-visit bakery if you go to Jogja! Most recommend that if you come here you must buy the cinnamon rolls...theres no competition!! You have to try kombucha as a drink...fresh, cold, really delicious
Affordable pastry
Food is fine, very western but nice space to sit & very nice staff!
The best

This restaurant does not even deserve 1 star, the food arrived after 1.5 hours when we received it, it was not delivered at the same time, it was half an hour between each dish, so we could not eat together, the food was not even tasty something I could recommend is dont eat here dont do it please dont do it if you dont want to wait for hours and dont want to eat with your family then dont come here

review_text: One of highly recommend restaurant, they not only have vegan and non-vegan menu but also make it all around the world cuisine, no wonder there are many foreigners eating here. They are very responsible about environment by not using plastic, air conditioner and they actively recycling their products. The foods looks nice, taste good and the price also affordable. If you happen to stay nearby, be sure to give it a try, its highly recommended! Vegetarian options: Have plenty of vegan menu Dietary restrictions: Dietary restrictions by request Kid-friendliness: Has dessert Wheelchair accessibility: Not wheelchair friendly
Good Place, same with bali
We met Mister Beng-Beng here, what a legend. If he speaks to you and meets you, youre in luck! This man is amazing and takes you to the most beautiful places in Yogjakarta
review_translated_text: Wij hebben hier Mister Beng-Beng ontmoet wat een legende. Mocht hij je aanspreken je tegenkomen dan heb je geluk! Deze man is geweldig en brengt je naar de mooiste plekjes van Yogjakarta

review_text: Ordered bun cha, poke, and falafel wrap. All were very bland. If you had the real Vietnamese bun cha, avoid this one. It was really dry and somehow they added basil? They cooked the fish in the poke, and it was very fishy and almost inedible. Probably it s best to stick to the Indonesian food or breakfast items. Avoid the international cuisine. Three stars for the fast and friendly service and the delicious drinks. Do try their kombuchas! I will not come back for their food but definitely for the drinks and vibes!

The concept is great, eco friendly etc etc but the flavour of the food is not amazing. A lots of the food was unnecessarily spicy. Also last order is 9pm on Saturday night. Website says they serve food til 11pm! They would not even serve desserts to children after 9pm sharp (and they were adamant about it) but we are on a holiday so that is very disappointing. As we were leaving at 9:30-10:00pm, staff were having their dinner at the front table of the restaurant which made me think they absolutely value staff or themselves more than customers. I saw a cookie jar on the counter as we were leaving. Could they not offer that to children? Service is friendly and price is very reasonable.
very good

Excellent food and good prices. Very friendly service. Nice atmosphere. They have an extensive menu for the whole day. The lamb shawarma was a bit boring. The salad dressing was also soaked into the bun. Tip: put the salad in a separate container. The chicken laksa was excellent! Amplely filled and tasty.
review_translated_text: Prima eten en goede prijzen. Heel vriendelijke service. Fijne sfeer. Ze hebben een uitgebreide kaart voor heel de dag. De lamshoarma was een beetje saai. De dressing van de salade werd ook in het broodje gezogen. Tip: de salade in een apart bakje doen. De chicken laksa was uitstekend! Ruim gevuld en goed op smaak.

review_text: Tempatnya lumayan nyaman, karena berasa kayak lagi diluar negeri hehe, pelayanan oke, nyoba latte hot sama kombucha kawista & pinneapple nya rekomend banget

Another rekomendasi tempat makan dari film AADC 2. Untuk Nasi Campur Paru nya termasuk murah bagi dompet Jakarta, rasa nya juga enak dengan porsi yang cukup banyak. Klo untuk Es Koyor nya sih B aja. Suasana buat dine in cukup menyenangkan, ditemani playlist lagu keroncong.

review_text: The place is nice; when I came at 19.30, it turned out some of the favorite foods were already sold out, maybe because it was a long weekend. Ive tried Lele Njungkring; at first, its a little bit scary because the Lele is dark, but the taste is good. The portion is small, even for me, who is not a big eater. Bubur Durian Mlekoh is quite nice for the taste; its a unique food. The durian is liquid like soup, and the porridge is made from plain bread. For teh rempah, its tasty and refreshing.
Two of us ate for  5. Perfect if you want to try local dishes and spend little. Friendly staff. Too bad about the cockroaches that were wandering around

review_text: Tempat dining dgn menu tradisional Jawa, diantara banyak resto dan cafe dgn menu masakan barat atau internasional. Di sini non AC tapi tempatnya teduh dan adem. Makanan cukup enak. Usul aja bakwan disajikan dlm keadaan hangat jd lbh nikmat.
review_translated_text: A dining place with a traditional Javanese menu, among many restaurants and cafes with western or international cuisine menus. There is no AC here but the place is shady and cool. Food is quite good. Just suggest serving the bakwan warm so its more delicious.

review_text: Small portions of ok traditional food at low prices.

review_translated_text: Some time ago I had lunch at this stall on the recommendation of a friend from Jogja, parking was a bit difficult, but by chance the owner and Mr Pakir looked for a place across from it. The place isnt very big, but its homey and clean, there are lots of staff and very friendly The food menu is varied and most of them are home-cooked Javanese dishes hehehe, the employee asked me so I ordered Nasi Campur Lung, its really delicious, its just perfect for my taste buds hihihi Service is also fast even though its quite busy during lunch time, and met one of the senior artists, Slamet Raharjo, after the night before, we met at one of the places to eat too hehehehe

review_translated_text: Ordered rice mixed with shredded grilled chicken but the chicken didnt look like it was grilled. The chicken tastes like home-cooked food, not really tasty like in restaurants. Delicious potato chips . I think if you add a little warm sauce on top of the rice, it will be tastier. The place is suitable for families because it is spacious + has a village house-like theme.

review_text: Food is very good, but portions are tiny. Veggy plates were 15,000 and the meat 28,000 Food

review_text: Comfortable place Parking ok Delicious food,

Warung ini berhasil menciptakan suasana tradisional yang kental melalui desain interior yang menggambarkan kehangatan rumah tradisional Jawa. Ini memberikan pengalaman makan yang autentik dan bersahaja. Nasi campur, sebagai menu spesial, memberikan pelanggan kesempatan untuk menikmati berbagai hidangan khas Jawa dalam satu piring. Keberagaman rasa dan tekstur menciptakan pengalaman kuliner yang memuaskan. Teh rempah merupakan keunikan Warung Bu Ageng. Kombinasi rempah-rempah dalam teh memberikan sentuhan hangat dan aroma yang khas, memberikan variasi yang menarik dari minuman biasa. Warung Bu Ageng adalah destinasi yang cocok bagi pecinta kuliner tradisional Jawa. Dengan menu nasi campur sebagai andalannya dan suasana yang mengundang, tempat ini memberikan pengalaman makan yang memuaskan dan bernuansa tradisional. Tetapkan untuk mencoba nasi campur dan teh rempahnya saat mengunjungi Warung Bu Ageng untuk merasakan kelezatan khas Jawa.
review_translated_text: This stall has succeeded in creating a strong traditional atmosphere through an interior design that depicts the warmth of a traditional Javanese house. This provides an authentic and unpretentious dining experience. Nasi campur, as a special menu, gives customers the opportunity to enjoy a variety of typical Javanese dishes on one plate. The diversity of flavors and textures creates a satisfying culinary experience. Spiced tea is unique to Warung Bu Ageng. The combination of spices in tea provides a warm touch and a distinctive aroma, providing an interesting variation from the usual drink. Warung Bu Ageng is a suitable destination for lovers of traditional Javanese culinary delights. With a menu of mixed rice as its mainstay and an inviting atmosphere, this place provides a satisfying dining experience with a traditional nuance. Make sure to try their mixed rice and spiced tea when you visit Warung Bu Ageng to experience Javanese delights.

review_text: Panties Pizza di Tamansiswa, Yogyakarta, memang terkenal dengan suasana yang nyaman dan harga yang terjangkau, membuatnya menjadi pilihan yang tepat untuk bersantai bersama keluarga. Keunikan mereka memberikan pizza gratis pada saat ulang tahun pelanggan menambah pengalaman yang menyenangkan dan personal. Ini bukan hanya tentang makanan yang lezat, tapi juga tentang pengalaman yang hangat dan ramah yang ditawarkan. Panties Pizza Jogja Tamansiswa adalah tempat yang sempurna untuk membuat kenangan bersama orang-orang terkasih, sambil menikmati pizza yang enak. Rekomendasi yang bagus untuk siapa saja yang mencari tempat santai dengan layanan yang memuaskan.
review_translated_text: Panties Pizza in Tamansiswa, Yogyakarta, is famous for its comfortable atmosphere and affordable prices, making it the right choice for relaxing with the family. Their unique feature of providing free pizza on customers birthdays adds to the fun and personalized experience. Its not just about the delicious food, but also about the warm and welcoming experience on offer. Panties Pizza Jogja Tamansiswa is the perfect place to make memories with loved ones, while enjoying delicious pizza. A great recommendation for anyone looking for a relaxing place with great service.

review_text: Pertama kali ke sini dan taw nya dari tiktok, pizzanya enak lembut dan harganya juga terjangkau.. Next kalo ke Jogja maw ke sini lagi insyallah

review_text: makanan enak, ada pastanya juga karena collab. tapi sayangnya meskipun ac ada 4, indoornya masih panas. pelayanan baik dan ramah. sayang smoking roomnya dipenuhi karyawan, jadi mau keluar agak segan karena jalannya tertutupi
response_from_owner_text: Halo kak Angela Terimakasih atas reviewnya, dan mohon maaf atas ketidaknyamanannya Untuk selanjutnya kami akan mengevaluasi terkait kenyamanan outlet di panties pizza cabang tamansiswa, terimakasih atas kritik dan sarannya kak , kritik dan saran kakak sangat membantu bagi kami
review_translated_text: delicious food, theres pasta too because of a collab. but unfortunately even though there are 4 ACs, the indoor is still hot. good and friendly service. Unfortunately the smoking room was filled with employees, so I was a bit reluctant to leave because the road was blocked
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Sis Angela Thank you for the review, and sorry for the inconvenience Next, we will evaluate the comfort of the outlets at the Tamansiswa branch of Pizza Panties, thank you for your criticism and suggestions, sis, your criticism and suggestions are very helpful for us.

review_text: Baru banget pesen panties tamsis, tapi ini pengalaman pesen di ojol ya. Awalnya pesen pizza darurat, dan dari dulu favorit cuma broadway, udah semua rasa dicoba dan tetep baliknya ke broadway wkwkwk. Terus setelah pesen baru sadar kalo mencet yang mission, auto badmood kesel. Mau di cancel biar bisa order ulang tapi gabisa dibatalkan, masih menunggu driver dan gabisa hub driver juga, finally coba hub ke cs. Telpon ga diangkat, mungkin karna no bisnis dan aku lgsg tlpn tanpa aba2 kali ya. Aku chat dan nyoba tlpn lagi diangkat akhirnya ngomong minta di batalin karna mau order ulang, posisi pesennya jam 20.29 dan panties close order 20.45. Buru2 karna pas itu udah mepet bgt. Mas csnya oke banget sampe mau mengupayakan pesenanku dan akhirnya bisa dirubah ke broadway. Dahlah, makanannya udah oke ditambah pelayanannya oke. Kalo bisa kasih bintang 100 ku kasih semua. Salam buat mas2 csnya!!!
review_translated_text: Im really new to ordering tamsis panties, but this is my experience with ordering from Ojol. Initially I ordered emergency pizza, and from the past my favorite was Broadway, Ive tried all the flavors and I keep coming back to Broadway hahaha. Then after ordering, I realized that if I pressed mission, I was automatically in a bad mood and annoyed. I wanted to cancel so I could reorder but couldnt cancel, still waiting for the driver and couldnt contact the driver either, finally tried connecting to CS. The phone wasnt picked up, maybe because it was a business number and I called straight away without warning. I chatted and tried calling again and finally answered asking to cancel because I wanted to reorder, the order position was at 20.29 and panties closed for orders at 20.45. Hurry up because its really tight at that time. The CS was so good that he wanted to try my order and finally it was changed to Broadway. Dahlah, the food is okay plus the service is okay. If I could give 100 stars, I would give them all. Greetings to you guys!!!

Cocok dikunjungi bersama teman maupun keluarga.

The quality remains good by maintaining premium ingredients, starting from the filling of beef slices, salami, even kebab slices. Helpful service with a comfortable outlet atmosphere. Suitable to visit with friends or family.

review_text: Saya bermalam disini 1 hari semalem enak , nyaman , saya cari hotel itu yg kamar mandi nya bersih. Makanannya enak lumayan, pelayanannya ramah cepat tanggap, kolam renangnya ada yg dangkal ada yg dalem. Dengan harga 350 ribu permalam menurut saya worth it. Minus nya : -kamar kurang kedap suara banyak terdengar suara berisik dari kamar sebelah saya. -bangunan perlu diperbaiki terutama tembok2 nya itu banyak sekali yg udh rapuh rapuh. -selimut bersih tapi wangi nya apek ga wangi2 laundry. Selebihnya ramah, senengg banget deh sama bapak2 penjaga kolam renang disana , baik bangettt. Salam ya untuk bapak2 penjaga kolam renang nyaa.
review_translated_text: I spent the night here for 1 day last night, it was nice, comfortable, I looked for a hotel with a clean bathroom. And this includes the bathrooms which are very clean, there is also a water heater in the bathroom, shower caps, coffee, tea and minerals are provided. The food is quite tasty, the service is friendly and responsive, there are swimming pools that are shallow and some are deep. With a price of 350 thousand per night, I think its worth it. The minuses: -The room was not soundproof, there was a lot of noise from the room next to me. -The building needs to be repaired, especially the walls, many of which are already fragile. - The blanket is clean but it smells musty and doesnt smell like laundry. The rest were friendly, I was really happy with the swimming pool guards there, they were really nice. Greetings to the swimming pool guards.

review_translated_text: Comes Ekstens Coffee 7 adults, 2 toddlers. Choose a place to look in an air-conditioned room considering that its night time. We ordered about as needed per person, one meal and drink. After ordering it turned out that one menu was left behind, in the end I had to order again from the cashier who waited for a long time When paying for a menu that is left behind, a price of less than 50K cannot be paid using a debit card, which in fact is the debit card and swipe card of the same bank. The taste of the food is also ordinary, not comfortable. No more going to Ekstens Coffee

review_text: Pertama x datang kesini Jumat mlm tgl 26 April kemarin brg suami emang sengaja pengen menikmati mlm sambil medang dan makan. Suasana nya enak dan estetik, bikin betah, minuman nya lumayan enak, tapi untuk makanan NO. Saya pesan nasi saikoro ekstens dan suami saya nasi goreng ayam Saya bertanya ke kasir cewek didepan makanan apa yg rekomended dan best seller, kasir tsb jawabnasi saikoro ekstens jadi saya order. Ternyata sama sekali tidak enak, daging saikoronya alot sekali tidak bisa digigit, dikunyah tetep aja tidak hancur. Kayak makan urat yang sangat alot bgt bgt. Cuma diicip dicak2 doang ga dimakan karena terlanjur bete. Nasi goreng ayam nya terlalu basah dan berminyak dan tidak ada rasanya. Kecewa bgt sih. Dan kapok datang kesini lagi. Tempat nya emang oke tapi soal makanan BIG NO. Tapi terimakasih. Ini menjadi pengalaman buat kami, dan jadi paham. Pantesan kebanyakan yg datang kesitu cuma pesan minuman klo yg saya liat. Karena byk pengunjung terutama anak muda hanya pesan minuman dimeja.Tempat enak belum tentu makanan nya worth it. Maaf dan Terimakasih
review_translated_text: The first time I came here was Friday evening, April 26, yesterday, my husband really wanted to enjoy the evening while eating and eating. The atmosphere is nice and aesthetic, makes you feel at home, the drinks are pretty good, but for food NO. I ordered extended saikoro rice and my husband ordered chicken fried rice. I asked the female cashier in front of what food was recommended and the best seller, the cashier answered extended saikoro rice so I ordered. It turned out that it wasnt delicious at all, the saikoro meat was so tough that you couldnt bite it, and when you chewed it, it still didnt fall apart. Its like eating really tough tendons. I just tasted it and didnt eat it because I was already bored. The chicken fried rice was too wet and oily and had no taste. Im really disappointed. And Im tired of coming here again. The place is indeed okay but when it comes to food its a BIG NO. But thanks. This is an experience for us, and we understand it. No wonder most people who come there only order drinks from what I see. Because many visitors, especially young people, only order drinks at the table. A nice place doesnt necessarily mean the food is worth it. Sorry and thank you

review_text: Amazing...

This place wins on its ambience. Beautifully decorated in Javanese opulence with spacious layout. The food is pretty good except the sate I ordered was bone dry and seems to have been reheated several times. Definitely did not seem freshly grilled. The Ikan Bakar (grilled fish) was freshly grilled though and came out hot.

Suka banget sama nuansa restoran ini. Banyak spot foto cantik karena bangunannya estetik seperti di keraton. Parkirannya luas, ada toilet dan mushola. Pelayanan sangat ramah dan cepat. Menu makanan variatif, mulai dari western and traditional food hingga Indonesian delight dilengkapi dengan berbagai macam appetizer dan dessert. Special menus  From Mataram Palace  memiliki porsi yang cenderung besar, bisa untuk 2-3 orang. Kemarin udah nyobain ayam panggang lembaran, sate lilit denpasar, sate ayam kotagede, dan ayam bakar kotagede. Trus dapet free keripik singkong sambil nunggu pesanannya dateng. Overall makanannya cukup enak sih, tapi justru pis kopyor yang paling enak. Saran untuk mbak-mbak yang melayani pesanan agar lebih memahami menu yang ada di restoran, supaya bisa menjelaskan ketika ditanya (sebenernya wajar sih karena menunya banyak buanget hehe). Next time mau coba ke sini lagi pas sore atau malem, kayaknya lebih syahdu~
review_translated_text: Really like the feel of this restaurant. There are lots of beautiful photo spots because the building is aesthetic, like a palace. The parking area is spacious, there are toilets and prayer rooms. Service is very friendly and fast. The food menu is varied, ranging from western and traditional food to Indonesian delight, equipped with various kinds of appetizers and desserts. The special menu From Mataram Palace has portions that tend to be large, enough for 2-3 people. Yesterday I tried grilled chicken strips, satay lilit Denpasar, chicken satay Kotagede, and grilled chicken Kotagede. Then get free cassava chips while waiting for your order to arrive. Overall the food is quite good, but the pis kopyor is the tastiest. Advice for ladies who serve orders to better understand the menu in the restaurant, so that they can explain when asked (actually its normal because the menu is a lot of waste hehe). Next time I want to try coming here again in the afternoon or evening, it seems more serene~

review_text: Pertama kali kesini pas bukber sama temen temen. Dapet pas bagian bukber nya di halaman luar ngga di dalam. Untungnya hari itu cerah ngga hujan. Bangunan nya vibes kraton banget jadi cocok buat foto  di sini. Menu makanan minuman yg di sediakan pas bukber bervariasi lebih ke nusantara food. Tapi ada bagian makanan yg dikerubungin semut udh aku kasih tau petugasnya trs di kasih lilin sekitar makanan yg ada semut tp masih aja ada semut yg dateng di bagian puding jd kudu hati hati pas ambil makanan takut ada semut nempel. Terus rasa makanannya menurutku standar ga yang enak bangett gituu sih lumayan lah sebanding harga bukber nya 85k. Terus aku kurang suka sama pelayanan petugasnya atau karyawannya. Waktu itu sebelum open buffet aku minta tolong ke salah satu karyawan buat fotoin aku dan temen  aku ga asal minta tolong itu aku liat karyawan nya terlihat ga sibuk banget makanya berani minta tolong fotoin. Pas aku minta tolong responnya ga ngarah ke aku malah bilang ke temennya klo ga salah  kui minta di fotokan  trs aku ga tau kelanjutannya apa. Aku tungguin tu bbrapa menit kok ga ada respon mau fotoin kita apa nggak, yaudah kita putuskan ke lantai atas foto  sendiri kita mikir mungkin lg sibuk otw open buffet makanya kita ga di respon. Tapi seharusnya kasih respon dong klo memang lg ga bisa ngelayanin kita bilang aja maaf lagi banyak yg di urusin ini atau lagi ga bisa bantu fotoin jangan malah kita nya di cuekin gitu aja tanpa ada respon sedikitpun. Itu aja deh review dari aku semoga ada evaluasi dri pihak sekar kedhaton. Terima kasih dan sukses selalu
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih kak Fitriana atas kunjungannya. Kami mohon maaf apabila ada ketidaknyamanan yang dirasakan pada saat berkunjung. Kami akan meningkatkan lagi kualitas pelayanan kami ke depannya. Terima kasih kami tunggu kedatangan kakak kembali
review_translated_text: The first time I came here was for bukber with friends. Got it when the bukber part was in the yard outside, not inside. Luckily it was a sunny day without rain. The building has a really palace vibe so its suitable for taking photos here. The food and drink menu provided during bukber varies more towards Indonesian food. But there was a part of the food that was covered in ants, I told the staff and put candles around the food that had ants but there were still ants coming to the pudding section so you had to be careful when picking up the food in case there were ants sticking to it. Then, in my opinion, the taste of the food is not of a very good standard, but its not bad compared to the price of the bukber, 85k. Then I dont like the service of the officers or employees. At that time, before the open buffet, I asked one of the employees to take a photo of me and my friends. I didnt just ask for help. I saw that the employee didnt look very busy, so I dared to ask for help in taking a photo. When I asked for help, the response was not direct, instead I said to my friend, if Im not mistaken, Im asking for a photo, but I didnt know what to do next. I waited a few minutes, but there was no response, whether to take our photo or not, so we decided to go upstairs to take photos. We thought maybe we were busy at the open buffet, thats why we didnt respond. But you should give a response, if you really cant serve us, just say sorry, theres a lot of work to do or you cant help with photos, dont let us just ignore you without the slightest response. Thats all my review. I hope there will be an evaluation from Sekar Kedhaton. Thank you and always success
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you Sis Fitriana for your visit. We apologize if you experience any inconvenience during your visit. We will further improve the quality of our service in the future. Thank you, we look forward to welcoming you back

review_text: Rekomendasi resto yang homey. Tempatnya minimalis tapi artistik. Sudut-sudut ruangan banyak banget spot yg Instagramable. Ada indoor sama semi outdoor areanya. Agak pricey tapi oke, nggk mengecewakan. Makanannya enak, specially the chicken burger. Aku prefer chicken burger daripada beef burgernya. Racikan sausnya enak, nampol banget. Minumannya juga oke. Service nya juga ramah, komunikatif, dan humoris. Toilet bersih. Cashless available. Ada kang parkir yg bantu rapikan kendaraan.
review_translated_text: Homey restaurant recommendation. The place is minimalist but artistic. There are lots of Instagrammable spots in the corners of the room. There are indoor and semi outdoor areas. A bit pricey but okay, didnt disappoint. The food is delicious, especially the chicken burger. I prefer the chicken burger over the beef burger. The sauce mixture is delicious, really delicious. The drinks are okay too. The service is also friendly, communicative and humorous. Clean toilets. Cashless available. There is a parking attendant who helps tidy up the vehicle.

But still, the burger is awesome.

review_text: Dari awal berdiri 2017 zamannya cuma jual cake sampai skr sudah full jual F&B,gk pernah absen tiap kali ke jogja selain makanan nya enak,suasanan homiiee dan gk kalah pelayanan nya sangat ramah dan jogja banget,Namanya Mas didit yg siap melayani dengam tulus sepenuh hati,tiap ke tempat ini mas didit selalu memberikan ruang kepuasaan pelayanan tersendiri di samping enaknya makanan dan minuman. Terimakasih mas didit.
review_translated_text: Since its inception in 2017, it was just selling cakes until now it is full of selling F&B, I have never been absent every time I have been to Jogja, apart from the food being delicious, the atmosphere is homie and not to mention the service is very friendly and really Jogja, his name is Mas Didit who is ready to serve with all his heart and sincerity Every time you go to this place, Mas Didit always provides a room of satisfaction with his own service in addition to delicious food and drinks. Thank you bro Didit.

review_text: Review ditulis di hari yang sama saat kunjungan. Ini pengalaman pertama kali datang ke sini. Kesan pertama : tempatnya adem banget. Terbilang nyaman, dingin ACnya, dan ada area outdoor juga. 5/5 untuk kenyamanan tempatnya. Semua menu makanan kosong (spaghetti/nasi/kentang) hanya tersedia bleger beef (blegger chicken kosong) dan minuman. Paling berkesan sama kopi koplo bia. Penilaian untuk kopi 5/5 enak banget, creamynya berasa padahal esnya udah mencair, dan single shot espressonya pas buat yang pengen ngopi ngopi ringan. Kalo pengen double shot, bisa pilih kopi koplo abi ya. Penilaian untuk blegernya 4/5 Suka sama saos mayonya, seperti racikan khusus karena cenderung manis. Tingkat serat dagingnya dan roti bun nya oke. Penilaian untuk pelayanan 3.5/5 Maaf untuk penilaian kasir kurang memuaskan sebab kasir beralasan uang pengunjung besar semua (diminta bayar pakai uang pas aja atau qris). Semoga ke depannya bisa lebih diatur lagi uang kecil yang tersedia di kasir. Untuk waiternya sangat ramah senyum. Nilai plus. Sehat sehat berkah selalu mas waiter. Aamiin. Fasilitas lainnya 4/5 Tersedia musholla dengan area yang cukupan, area indoor dan outdoor, dan toilet. Area parkir terbilang cukup terbatas. Toilet perempuan kurang pas untuk dikunci. Semoga segera diperbaiki demi keamanan dan kenyamanan customer. Untuk yang penasaran sama restonya kak Zaskia A Mecca, monggo mampir pinarak.
review_translated_text: Review written on the same day of visit. This is my first experience coming here. First impression: the place is really cool. It is said to be comfortable, the AC is cold, and there is an outdoor area too. 5/5 for the comfort of the place. All food menus are empty (spaghetti/rice/potatoes) only bleger beef (empty blegger chicken) and drinks are available. Most impressive is Koplo Bia coffee. Rating for coffee 5/5 Its really delicious, it feels creamy even though the ice has melted, and the single shot of espresso is perfect for those who want a light drink of coffee. If you want a double shot, you can choose Koplo Abi coffee. The rating for the blender is 4/5 I like the mayo sauce, its like a special concoction because it tends to be sweet. The fiber level of the meat and bread is okay. Rating for service 3.5/5 Sorry for the cashiers assessment which was less than satisfactory because the cashier argued that all the visitors money was large (they were asked to pay using just the right money or qris). Hopefully in the future we can better regulate the small money available at the cashier. The waiter is very friendly with a smile. Plus value. Always healthy, blessed, sir, waiter. Amen. Other facilities 4/5 There is a prayer room with sufficient area, indoor and outdoor areas, and toilets. The parking area is quite limited. The womens toilet is not suitable for locking. Hopefully it will be repaired soon for customer safety and comfort. For those who are curious about Sis Zaskia A Meccas restaurant, please stop by Pinarak.

review_text: Ke Mamahke untuk beli cake reguler double chocolate nya karena direcommend teman. Untuk tempatnya nyaman banget dan staff nya ramah banget, sabar ngejelasinnya. Sayangnya pas saya datang yang ukuran reguler hanya tersedia yang double chocolate, redvelvet dan tiramisu. Tiramisu pun tinggal 1 dan keburu dibeli teman saya. Nextnya mau coba untuk yang keju karena secara pribadi saya lebih suka keju dripada cokelat.
review_translated_text: Went to Mamahke to buy the regular double chocolate cake because it was recommended by a friend. Unfortunately, when I arrived, the regular size was only available in double chocolate, redvelvet and tiramisu. There was only 1 Tiramisu left and my friend bought it in a hurry. Next, I want to try the cheese one because personally I prefer cheese over chocolate.

review_text: Came here on the 2nd day of Eid, reserved since the day before, ordered the menu before arrival, but the food came out 40-60mins later after we arrived. Some of the staffs kept saying that they re  just  in charge of ordering and giving excuse that they aren t the kitchen s staff to emphasize it s not their responsibility about the delay. So disappointed for the service.

udah reservasi jam 17.00 buat buka puasa, eh malah makanannya lama banget datengnya sampe harus nanya ke staff. padahal buka puasa jam 17.53 tapi makanannya baru dateng jam 18.30, nunggu setengah jam lebih keburu laper  jelek banget pelayanannya untuk resto yang itungannya lumayan fancy, kalah sama resto lain   free takjilnya juga dikit banget ga nyampe berapa menit dah abis duluan  ga lagi lagi deh kesini tambahan: harusnya dari awal udah persiapan kalo bulan puasa pasti crowded di waktu yang bersamaan, jadi bisa nambah staff kitchen. nyatanya saya di resto lain selalu on time kok makanannya walaupun di bulan puasa. manajemen amco aja yg kurang. trs katanya free takjil direfill terus berdasarkan reservasi? tapi aku ga dapet makanannya loh kak sedangkan aku harus nunggu setengah jam lebih, aku tunggu-tunggu juga ga direfill ulang tuh.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih kak Ines Nisa atas ulasannya. Kami mohon maaf atas ketidaknyamanannya. Di karenakan di jam buka puasa tamu datang bersamaan dan kondisi memang crowded dan makanan harus keluar bersamaan. Kami mohon maaf atas kejadian tersebut. Untuk membatalkan puasa kami sediakan free tajil untuk membatalkan . Dan free tajil kami selalu di refil berdasarkan jumlah reservasi di hari tersebut.
review_translated_text: I made a reservation at 17.00 to break the fast, but the food took so long to arrive that I had to ask the staff. even though breaking the fast was at 17.53 but the food only arrived at 18.30, I waited for half an hour and I was really hungry  the service was really bad for a restaurant that was quite fancy, inferior to other restaurants   the free takjil was also very small and didnt arrive in a few minutes before it finished  no more come here again addition: You should have prepared from the start if the fasting month would be crowded at the same time, so you could add more kitchen staff. In fact, at other restaurants, the food is always on time, even during the fasting month. Amcos management is just lacking. then it says free takjil is continuously refilled based on reservations? but I didnt get the food, bro, even though I had to wait more than half an hour, I waited and it wasnt refilled.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you, Ines Nisa, for your review. We apologize for the inconvenience. This is because at breaking the fast the guests come at the same time and conditions are indeed crowded and the food has to come out at the same time. We apologize for this incident. To break the fast, we provide free tajil to cancel it. And our free tajil is always refilled based on the number of reservations on that day.

review_text: sudah dikasih invoice dari tanggal 2 Januari dan kami sudah membayar DP di tanggal 5 Januari. kami pesan untuk tanggal 11 Januari tiba di hari H dan kami sudah di lokasi pegawainya pada kaget karena merasa tidak ada pesanan dari rombongan kami. ketika dikonfirmasi bilang kalau yg pegang hp admin tidak ada di lokasi, akhirnya ada miskomunikasi. ternyata itu hanya alibi padahal senyatanya ada kecerobohan di pihak owner. yg akhirnya kami pesan untuk prasmanan harus di box krn tidak memungkinkan kami menunggu masakan selama satu jam sedangkan siswa kami harus kejar jam di lokasi wisata lain. tidak ada kompensasi untuk kami, bahkan pihak owner mengatakan kalau untuk beli box harusnya nambah 2k tp tidak minta bea tambahan ke kami. oke kami mengalah, daripada debat mending diiyakan saja. untung saja mau mengantar makanan ke lokasi kami berkegiatan saat itu (keraton jogja). tetapi minuman nya tidak sesuai yg kami pesan harusnya teh dikasih air mineral
review_translated_text: We have been given an invoice from January 2 and we have paid the deposit on January 5. we ordered for January 11th arrived on the day and we were at the location where the staff were shocked because they felt there were no orders from our group. when confirmed, they said that the person holding the admins cellphone was not at the location, in the end there was a miscommunication. It turns out it was just an alibi even though in reality there was carelessness on the part of the owner. What we finally ordered for the buffet had to be boxed because it didnt allow us to wait for the food for an hour while our students had to catch the clock at another tourist location. There was no compensation for us, the owner even said that to buy a box we should add 2k but didnt ask us for additional fees. OK, we give in, instead of arguing, its better to just say yes. Luckily they wanted to deliver food to the location where we were doing activities at that time (Jogja Palace). but the drink didnt match what we ordered, tea should have been given mineral water

review_text: Overall enak makanannya dan tempatnya standard. Cuma minus dipelayanan, mas-mas nya ramah, tapi yang anter makanan perempuan ngga ada etikanya. Masa anter makanan diem aja tanpa kek bilang silahkan, its okay lah kalau emg ngga bilang gtu, tapi pas makannya ditaruh terus aku sama temenku bilang makasih ga ada jawaban samsek? Hello?? Aku juga kerja dipelayanan publik, perasaan dituntut ramah deh walau secapek apapun. Gilak si ngga expect kalo lebih ramah lelakinya dripd cewenya. Terus jg waktu temenku mau bayar dia kek jutek bgt yang welcome yang laki. Bisa-bisanya org kek gtu kerja di pelayanan publik. Minimal senyum kek atau bilang sama-sama sesusah itu kah? Tolong ya mbak lebih belajar lagi caranya melayani pelanggan.
review_translated_text: Overall the food is delicious and the place is standard. The only minus is the service, the guys are friendly, but the women who deliver the food have no etiquette. When they deliver the food, just stay silent without saying please, its okay if you dont say that, but when I put the food down, my friend and I say thank you or not. Do you have an answer, sir? Hello?? I also work in public services, I feel like Im required to be friendly, no matter how tired I am. Its crazy that I dont expect men to be friendlier than women. Also, when my friend wants to pay, hes a really mean guy who welcomes men. Its possible for people like that to work in public services. At least smile or say youre welcome, its that difficult, right? Please, sis, learn more about how to serve customers.

review_text: Best place for hangout

Kopi istimewa di utara alun-alun utara Jogja. Menghidangkan kopi unik yang gelasnya dibalik, dengan ditemani mendoan hangat, sangat cocok untuk menikmati suasana malam alun-alun utara sambil memandangi 2 beringin dan merenungi diri. Kurangnya adalah parkiran untuk mobil yang memang harus memakan jalan yang juga sudah sempit, dan kalau di bagian dalam mungkin agak sulit untuk merenungi diri karena dicampuri oleh nyamuk yang juga ingin menikmati. Toiletnya bisa gabung di bagian dalam dapur, tapi memang ya seadanya seperti itu. *Sarannya dibangunkan area 2 toilet khusus untuk wanita dan pria, 2 WC aja Harga masih terhitung terjangkau untuk pendopo kopi di tempat yang sangat strategis. (r) Tips cara minumnya bukan langsung di balik lagi gelasnya atau jangan sekali-kali mencoba cara-cara di luar nalar. Lebih baik bertanya ke stafnya daripada malu. Cara yang biasa digunakan adalah dibuka sedikit demi sedikit dengan memanfaatkan hukum fisika, agar air di dalam gelas bertukar dengan udara sedikit demi sedikit (c) Khairunnas anfauhum linnas:)
review_translated_text: Special coffee north of Jogjas north square. Serving unique coffee with the glass turned upside down, accompanied by warm mendoan, very suitable for enjoying the night atmosphere of the North Square while looking at 2 banyans and contemplating yourself. Whats lacking is parking for cars which have to take up the already narrow road, and if youre on the inside it might be a bit difficult to reflect on yourself because its surrounded by mosquitoes who also want to enjoy it. The toilet can be integrated into the kitchen, but thats how it is. *The suggestion is to build a special 2 toilet area for women and men, just 2 toilets Prices are still relatively affordable for a coffee shop in a very strategic location. (r) Tips on how to drink, dont go straight behind the glass or never try methods beyond reason. Its better to ask the staff than to be embarrassed. The method usually used is to open it little by little using the laws of physics, so that the water in the glass exchanges with air little by little (c) Khairunnas anfauhum linnas :)

review_translated_text: Its very cool to try a new experience, namely coffee at Walik with a unique way of drinking it, of course, but here for the taste of the coffee, its just standard or not, but for the atmosphere, its really chill, bro, and its strategically located in front of the North Square, of course it adds to the taste. which is cool

review_text: Tempat terbuka, parkir mudah, harga murah, cukup nyaman untuk ngobrol santai.
review_translated_text: Open place, easy parking, cheap prices, comfortable enough to chat casually.

review_text: syahdu tempatnya, menu makanan minuman cemilannya hemat di kantong, recommended deh buat yg mau ngabisin waktu di deket alun2 utara jogja
review_translated_text: beautiful place, the food and drink snack menu is pocket friendly, recommended for those who want to spend time near the north square of Jogja

review_text: Nyaman ....pasti balik lagi kesini
review_translated_text: Comfortable...definitely come back here again

review_text: *Berlokasi di alun2 utara yang hanya beberapa ratus meter dari Malioboro maka kedai ini sangat strategis (5/5) *Kualitas makanan baik (4/5) *Porsi penyajian, menurut saya pas (5/5) *Kebersihan sangat baik (5/5) *Kecepatan pelayanan harap maklum, bakmi Jogja khususnya mmg butuh sabar (3/5) *Friendly staff (5/5) *Harga compare dengan porsi, kualitas, dan penyajian menurut saya worth it (5/5) *Parking area ya pinggir jalan alun2, pas peak ya susah (4/5) *Toilet baik (4/5) *Tersedia outdoor yang astetik serta namun adem (5/5) Minum kopi disini unik karena gelasnya dibalik, jadi minumnya agak susah karena disruput di lepeknya. Pada dasarnya kopinya biasa saja namun sensasinya luar biasa. Untuk makanan juga macam2, ada Magelabgan, bakmi, dll dengan kualitas rasa yang biasa saja namun secara posisi di alun2 maka sensasinya sangat meneduhkan. Saya senang kesini, penuh kenangan
review_translated_text: *Located in the north square which is only a few hundred meters from Malioboro, this shop is very strategic (5/5) *Food quality is good (4/5) *Serving portion, in my opinion is just right (5/5) *Cleanliness is very good (5/5) *Please understand the speed of service, Bakmi Jogja in particular requires patience (3/5) *Friendly staff (5/5) *Compare price with portion, quality and presentation, in my opinion its worth it (5/5) *Parking area is on the side of the main road, at peak times its difficult (4/5) *Good toilet (4/5) *Aesthetic and cool outdoor space available (5/5) Drinking coffee here is unique because the glass is turned upside down, so drinking it is a bit difficult because it is slurped in the saucer. Basically the coffee is just ordinary but the sensation is extraordinary. There are also various kinds of food, there are Magelabgan, noodles, etc. with an ordinary taste quality but due to its position in the square, the sensation is very calming. I love coming here, full of memories

review_text: Tempat nongki disekitar alun2 deket 0km harga murah, nongki sampai malem ataupun sampai pagi cocoklah sambil ngopi, nyemil, makan.
review_translated_text: Hanging out places around the main square near 0km are cheap, hanging out until late at night or until morning is suitable while drinking coffee, snacking, eating.

review_text: tempat yg asyik buat hang out bersama teman atau kerabat makanan and minumannya enak semua
review_translated_text: a fun place to hang out with friends or relatives, the food and drinks are all delicious

review_text: Maybe am too late to came here Didnt get the chance to try their foods, only the unique drinking style Coffee only in Jogjakarta. Strong and nice coffee But their crew already tired when try to serve me n my friends
Pelayanan tidak RAMAH.
review_translated_text: Service is not FRIENDLY.

review_text: Kopinya ok dan banyak pilihan. Boleh coba cold brew dan americanonya. Punya manual brew juga. Bangunan kayaknya tema industrial, 2 lantai walaupun ga terlalu luas. Parkir motor langsung di tempat, parkir mobil masuk agak ke dalam mungkin muat sekitar 8 mobil. Walaupun kayaknya gabung dengan parkir mobil orang sekitar. review_translated_text: The coffee is ok and lots of choices. You can try the cold brew and americano. Has manual brew too. The building seems to have an industrial theme, 2 floors although not very spacious. Motorbike parking directly on the spot, car parking goes a little inside, maybe fits around 8 cars. Even though it seems to be joining the car park of people around. More suitable for yourself, couples or friends. Yes, although according to preference, it can be for families too. Recommended...

review_text: Tempat ngopi langganan kalau mau kerja. Ambiencenya ok dan mendukung untuk fokus. Beverages dan snacknya enak, cuma makanan beratnya kurang cocok. Lemongrass chickennya kebanyakan tepung. Semoga bisa diperbaiki ya. Tapi overall menyelamatkan banget buat yang tinggal di Jogja selatan untuk cari tempat kerja selain di rumah. Tips: silakan bisa perhatikan di chalkboardnya kalau ada promo. Suka ngga dikasih tau kalau nggak tanya.
review_translated_text: Regular coffee place if you want to work. The ambience is ok and supports focus. The beverages and snacks are delicious, but the heavy food is not suitable. Lemongrass chicken is mostly flour. Hopefully it can be fixed. But overall it really saves those who live in southern Jogja looking for a place to work other than at home. Tips: please pay attention on the chalkboard if there are promotions. I dont like being told if I dont ask.

review_text: One of my worst experiences datang ke cafe.  Suara keributan di balik tirai dari para karyawan yg bercanda dg suara keras dan tertawa berisik mengurangi kenyamanan.  Yang di depan hanya ada 1 embak cashier yg pake kawat gigi rambut pendek pakai topi.  Dia jutek cemberut terus seakan2 sebal kita datang.  Dia melayani sambil sesekali menoleh ke teman2nya dan mengingatkan, sstttt.... Ssttt... Tapi Teman2nya yg diingatkan cuek saja. Tetap ribut ketawa2....  Si embak melayani kembali dengan cemberut.  Membungkus dengan cemberut.  Menerima pembayaran dengan cemberut dan menyerahkan pesanan dan kembalian tanpa senyum, tanpa memandang, dan tanpa terima kasih.... Woooow.... Pengalaman luar biasa di jaman persaingan dan padatnya cafe di Jogja sekarang ini ... Will not come back for sure...  Kalau dilihat dari review2 yg lain... Embak cashier 1 ini bahkan difoto dengan ekspresi jutek yg sama persis yg saya lihat tadi .... wkwkwk... Seharusnya pihak manajemen memperhatikan, minimal menegur dan mentraining senyum sapa salam.... Kalau mau survive siiih
review_translated_text: One of my worst experiences was coming to the cafe. The noise behind the curtain from employees joking loudly and laughing noisily reduces comfort. At the front there was only 1 cashier wearing braces, short hair and a hat. He kept pouting as if he was annoyed that we came. He served while occasionally turning to his friends and reminding him, Shh... Shh... But his friends who were reminded were just indifferent. Still laughing loudly.... The grandmother served again with a frown. Wrapping up with a frown. Receiving payment with a frown and handing over the order and change without a smile, without looking, and without thanks.... Woooow.... An extraordinary experience in this era of competition and crowded cafes in Jogja ... Will not come back for sure... If you look at the other reviews... Miss cashier 1 was even photographed with the exact same sullen expression I saw earlier... hahaha... The management should pay attention, at least reprimand and train to smile and say hello.... If you want to survive, thats fine

review_text: Kasir yg cewe dua dua nya jutek dan galak, gaada sisi good service nya, pdhal mereka dibagian depan harusnya punya sisi good service, klo emg cape gausah kerja mba! Klo gabisa ramah mending jangan dibagian depan, di dapur aja! Dan ternyata gak cuma satu dua yg komen klo mba mba nya galak, tp banyak! Tolong dong management nya ini mba mba nya di training lagi!
review_translated_text: Both of the female cashiers are mean and grumpy, they dont have a good service side, even though those at the front should have a good service side, if youre really tired, dont work, sis! If you cant be friendly, its better not to be at the front, just in the kitchen! And it turns out that not only one or two commented that she was fierce, but many! Please, sis, this management will be trained again!

Kafe yang mungkin underrated di kawasan sekitar JEC. Padahal di sini menawarkan suasana coworking yang nyaman. Apalagi di ruang AC-nya. Minusnya mungkin cuma mejanya aja yang terlalu sempit di situ. Tapi ya mungkin didesain gitu buat WFC ya.. Jadi kerja sendiri-sendiri gitu. Untuk makanan paling unik di sini ada Nasi Pecel. Enak, tapi sayang porsinya kurang buat cowok. Nasi gorengnya juga lumayan lah. Paling recommended untuk minumnya: Banguntapan Bold. Double shots espresso + gula aren, cocok untuk booster produktivitas. Sayang kamar mandi cuma satu. Ada musholla tapi ngga terlalu luas. Bentuknya gazebo gitu. Ya not bad lah. Tapi semoga bisa diperluas & ditingkatkan lagi kebersihannya. Terima kasih.
review_translated_text: A cafe that may be underrated in the area around JEC. Even though here it offers a comfortable coworking atmosphere. Especially in the AC room. The only minus is that the table is too narrow there. But yes, maybe it was designed that way for WFC, right? So it works independently. For the most unique food here, there is Nasi Pecel. Its delicious, but unfortunately the portion is not enough for men. The fried rice is also pretty good. Most recommended drink: Banguntapan Bold. Double shots of espresso + palm sugar, perfect for a productivity booster. Unfortunately there is only one bathroom. There is a prayer room but its not too big. It looks like a gazebo. Yes, its not bad. But hopefully the cleanliness can be expanded & improved. Thank You.

review_text: TLDR ; Good for chat and work, artsy interior and great coffee. Review Rekaya Artisan Coffee Tempat 5/5 Rekaya Artisan Coffee bertempat di seberang JEC, dekat dengan Jl. Raya Janti, jadi mudah untuk dicapai. Tempat parkir cukup luas, bisa muat beberapa mobil. Tempat dibagi menjadi dua bagian, satu indoor non-AC, dan satu indoor AC di depan. Dua-duanya enak digunakan untuk mengobrol dan bekerja, tapi ruangan AC di depan agak sempit, jadi lebih enak digunakan untuk bekerja saja. Menu 5/5 Yang unik disini dan masih jarang saya temui di kafe-kafe Jogja adalah daftar menu yang full online, kita scan QR code untuk bisa melihat daftar menu. Rata-rata menu berkisar di harga 25k, harga yang cukup tinggi untuk kafe di daerah sini, tapi bagi saya rasa menunya enak dan tempatnya nyaman, jadi oke lah not bad. Saya mencoba menu Rekara, yaitu Kopi Susu Karamel, dan Rum N Roll, Kopi Susu Rum. Dua-duanya rasanya enak, campuran kopi susu dan rasa pas. Tapi kalau porsi menurut saya kurang banyak dikit. Pelayanan 5/5 Barista ramah dalam melayani, bisa menuntun saya dalam memesan dengan QR code. Kamar mandi 4/5 Kamar mandi standar, bersih dan tidak bau.
review_translated_text: TLDR ; Good for chat and work, artsy interior and great coffee. Rekaya Artisan Coffee Review Place 5/5 Rekaya Artisan Coffee is located opposite JEC, close to Jl. Raya Janti, so its easy to reach. The parking lot is quite large, can fit several cars. The place is divided into two parts, one indoor non-AC, and one indoor AC at the front. Both are good for chatting and working, but the AC space at the front is a bit narrow, so its better to just use it for working. Menu 5/5 What is unique here and which I rarely find in Jogja cafes is that the menu list is fully online, we scan the QR code to be able to see the menu list. The average menu price is around 25k, a fairly high price for cafes in this area, but for me I think the menu is delicious and the place is comfortable, so its okay, not bad. I tried the Rekara menu, namely Caramel Milk Coffee, and Rum N Roll, Rum Milk Coffee. Both taste delicious, a mixture of coffee and milk and the taste is just right. But in my opinion, the portion is a bit small. Service 5/5 Barista is friendly in serving, can guide me in ordering with QR code. Bathroom 4/5 Standard bathroom, clean and not smelly.

review_text: Jujur saya suka bgt nasi ayam bakarnya, dengan harga murah dpt daging ayam yg texturenya juicy, lezat pokoknya, kudos to the chef. Tempat juga enak, dengan view lgsg sawah, tidak menyesakkan. Keesokan harinya saya sampai mau makan disini lg, pdhl kemarin udh makan 2x. Karna kebetulan saya lg stay di hotel sini. Besoknya pagi  jam 9.30 saya datang lg, tp msh sepi bgt, bahkan saya orang yg pertama datang dibanding staffnya, padahal tulisannya buka jam 9. Walaupun lapar sudah drtd, tp gpp saya tunggu aja sebentar, demi ayam enak. Bbrp lama setelah itu staff mulai datang, tp saya ga langsung pesan karna tau msh prepare. 10.15 akhirnya saya bilang mau pesan makan, tp ternyata mbak kasir bilang kitchen baru ready jam 10.30. Saya tunggu lg deh, udh kadung nunggu lama, another 15mnt ga masalah. Setelah 15mnt saya pesan ayam bakar, kasir baru mau menanyakan ketersediaan ayam dengan orang kitchen, kemudian bilang kalau hari ini belum bisa pesan karna lg ada acara, karna lapar bgt, saya tanya ketersediaan menu selain ayam, ternyata blm bisa dipesan jg. Nah saya sedikit menyayangkan, diinformasikan bisa pesan jam 10.30, taunya masih gabisa pesen jg. Saya bisa maklum kalau memang ada acara dan ketersediaan terbatas, tp saya harap next time kalau memang tidak bisa, bilang saja dari awal. Saya pergi masih dalam keadaan lapar dan kehilangan waktu 1jam menunggu :(
review_translated_text: Honestly, I really like the grilled chicken rice, for a cheap price you can get chicken meat with a juicy texture, really delicious, kudos to the chef. The place is also nice, with a direct view of rice fields, not oppressive. The next day I wanted to eat here again, even though I had eaten twice yesterday. Because I happen to be staying at the hotel here. The next morning, at 9.30 I came again, but it was still very quiet, in fact I was the first to arrive compared to the staff, even though it said it opened at 9. Even though I was already hungry, it didnt matter if I just waited a little, for the sake of the delicious chicken. Some time after that the staff started to come, but I didnt order straight away because I knew I was still preparing. 10.15 finally I said I wanted to order food, but it turned out the cashier said the kitchen would only be ready at 10.30. Ill wait again, Ive been waiting too long, another 15 minutes is no problem. After 15 minutes I ordered grilled chicken, the cashier just wanted to ask the kitchen person about the availability of chicken, then said that I couldnt order it today because there was an event, because I was really hungry, I asked about the availability of menus other than chicken, it turned out I couldnt order it yet. Well, I regret it a little, I was told that I could order at 10.30, but I still cant order. I can understand if there is an event and availability is limited, but I hope that next time if you cant, just say so from the start. I left still hungry and lost 1 hour waiting :(

Pisang bakar (17k) Kentang goreng (14k) : saya makan beberapa saja karna look nya seperti digoreng dengan minyak bekas yg kotor Intel spesial (18k) Minum jus mangga (17k) porsi wajar Layanan : jam 11.30 saya pesan, tapi banyak yang belum ready karna kitchen nya baru belanja. Menunggu kurang lebih jam 12 an baru makanan saya datang

Grilled Banana (17k) French fries (14k): I only ate a few because they looked like they were fried in dirty used oil Intel special (18k) Drink a reasonable portion of mango juice (17k). Service: I ordered at 11.30, but many were not ready because the kitchen was just shopping. Waited around 12 oclock for my food to arrive
