review_text: ketika pertama kali datang ke sini, saya cukup kaget kenapa tempat sebagus ini bisa sepi sekali. padahal tempatnya sangatlah bagus. dan saya pun datang di jam 19 malam alias jam makan malam. dan saat saya berjalan ke meja pelayanan dan melihat harga di menu, saya melihat bahwa harga yang dijual di sini relatif terjangkau. tidaklah yang mahal sekali. dan per orang misal katakanlah membawa Rp.20.000 saja pun sudah bisa makan kenyang. dan saya datang ke sini berdua. habisnya tidak sampai Rp.40.000 di mana saya memesan nasi goreng dan orang yang bersama saya memesan mie godhog. pelayanan dari mbaknya juga ramah banget. dan biasanya kan kebanyakan pembayaran itu ada di awal. ternyata tempat ini bisa melakukan pembayaran di akhir juga. entah mungkin karena sedang sepi, atau memang biasanya boleh membayar di akhir. baiklah akan saya komentari nasi goreng dan mie godhognya. saya mulai dengan nasi goreng terlebih dahulu. nasi goreng yang ada di sini tidak ada kurangnya sama sekali. rasa gurihnya pas, tidak keasinan, dan tidak kemanisan pula. karena saya pesan pedas, takaran pedasnya juga masih sangat mudah ditoleransi. tidak yang pedas sekali. untuk kerupuknya juga renyah. lalu porsinya juga mengenyangkan. lalu untuk mie godhognya akan saya kritik ya. kuahnya itu sangatlah encer meskipun gurih. ekspektasi saya kalau mie godhog itu kuahnya agak kental gitu. tapi di sini berbeda. lalu untuk tekstur mienya juga cenderung tipis dan tidak tebal. padahal biasanya mie godhog itu punya tekstur mie yang tebal. saya sih bisa maklum karena harganya memang murah. tapi saya tidak masalah apabila harganya dinaikkan supaya mendapatkan kualitas makanan yang terbaik. overall sih cukup direkomendasikan, terutama untuk nasi gorengnya enak sekali sih. saya bahkan tidak menemukan celahnya sama sekali. good job dan pertahankan untuk rasanya ya.
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih Kak untuk ulasan mendalamnya, harapannya kami bisa tetap berkomitmen memberikan yg terbaik, kami tunggu kedatangannya kembali untik mencoba hidangan kami yg lain, dan bila ada yg kurang pas bisa langsung mengabari kami, terimakasih banyak Kak. Izin kak silahkan dm Instagram kami @mocorosoid untuk dapatkan evouchernya
review_translated_text: When I first came here, I was quite surprised why a place as good as this could be so quiet. even though the place is very good. and I came at 19 pm, aka dinner time. and when I walked to the service desk and looked at the prices on the menu, I saw that the prices sold here were relatively affordable. not very expensive. and for example, if you bring Rp. 20,000 per person, you can eat your fill. and I came here both. It didnt end up reaching IDR 40,000 where I ordered fried rice and the person with me ordered godhog noodles. The service from Ms. is also very friendly. and usually most of the payments are at the beginning. Turns out this place can make payments at the end too. Maybe its because its quiet, or maybe youre usually allowed to pay at the end. OK, Ill comment on the fried rice and godhog noodles. I started with fried rice first. There is no shortage of fried rice here at all. The savory taste is just right, not salty and not sweet either. because I ordered spicy, the spicy dose was still very easy to tolerate. not very spicy. the crackers are also crunchy. then the portion is also filling. then I will criticize the godhog noodles. The sauce was very runny even though it was tasty. My expectation was that the soup for godhog noodles would be a bit thick. but here its different. Then the texture of the noodles also tends to be thin and not thick. even though godhog noodles usually have a thick noodle texture. I can understand it because the price is cheap. but I dont have a problem if the price is increased to get the best quality food. Overall, its quite recommended, especially for the fried rice, its really delicious. I didnt even find the gap at all. good job and keep it up for the taste.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you Sis for your in-depth review, we hope we can remain committed to providing the best, we look forward to welcoming you back to try our other dishes, and if there is something that isnt quite right, you can let us know straight away, thank you very much Sis. With permission, please DM our Instagram @mocorosoid to get the evoucher

review_text: Tempat ngopi lokal favorit karena yg paling deket kos. Paling seneng disini karena ga terlalu ramai, samping jalan tamsis tp di dalam ga ramai suara kayak di luar. Lebih asyik di lantai atas, sambil ngerjain sesuatu di laptop, sambil baca buku, atau buat bengong juga enak. Tiap meja ada colokannya. Internet lumayan kenceng. Pesanan favorit paket kopi kenangan mantan less sugar + roti coklat jd 25ribu. Pernah nyoba matcha espresso juga enak tp dominan kopinya jd balik lg ke kopken mantan aja. Banyak promo bank juga di kopken. Baristanya ramah. Kadang sendiri kadang ada dua. Kamar mandinya bersih, disediain tissue juga. Ada tukang parkir (berbayar).
review_translated_text: Favorite local coffee place because its the closest to the boarding house. I like it here the most because its not too busy, its next to Tamsis Road but inside theres not as much noise as outside. Its more fun upstairs, doing something on the laptop, reading a book, or just relaxing. Every table has a plug. The internet is quite fast. Favorite order of ex-memory coffee package less sugar + chocolate bread for 25 thousand. Ive tried matcha espresso, its also delicious but the coffee is dominant so I just go back to the former Kopken. There are also lots of bank promotions in Kopken. The baristas are friendly. Sometimes alone, sometimes there are two. The bathroom is clean, tissue is provided too. There is a parking attendant (paid).

review_text: Barista/Kasirnya telponan sama temennya dengan suara kenceng banget ngelebihin customer. Customer yang di indoor malah sunyi, semua pada ngadep laptop, kalo ngobrol pun dengan volume pelan. Saya juga nyium bau rokok di indoor room, padahal saya perhatiin customer indoor gaada yg ngerokok. Makanan, minuman dan vibe cafenya oke, cuma untuk service bisa ditingkatin lagi training ke karyawannya. Misal kalo mau ngobrol atau telponan bisa keluar dulu atau ada ruangan khusus.
review_translated_text: The barista/cashier called his friend with a very loud voice over the customer. The customers indoors are actually quiet, everyone is facing their laptops, even if they chat at a low volume. I also smelled cigarettes in the indoor room, even though I noticed that there were no indoor customers smoking. The food, drinks and cafe vibe are okay, only the service could be improved with more training for the employees. For example, if you want to chat or make a phone call, you can go out first or there is a special room.

review_text: Coday Coffee & Eatery adalah kafe sekaligus co-working. Lantai satu untuk kafe, sedangkan lantai dua khusus untuk co-working. Di lantai satu, ada tiga area utama. Satu area bebas rokok, lalu dua area merokok yang berada belakang dan samping. Sebuah meja dengan tempat duduk single di depan barista adalah tempat yang saya pilih. Suara musik yang menggema di ruangan cukup meredam beberapa suara dari obrolan para pengunjung. Varian kopi dan camilan pun banyak ditawarkan Coday Coffee and Eatery. Menu spesial di sini adalah bebeknya. Melewati hari libur di Coday Coffee and Eatery sungguh menyenangkan bagi saya. Ini adalah kafe di Bantul yang menyenangkan untuk menyendiri. Saya merasa nyaman ketika duduk di area ini. Jika saya bawa buku, mungkin membaca dan menghabiskan satu buku pun bisa dilakukan di sini.
review_translated_text: Coday Coffee & Eatery is a cafe and co-working. The first floor is for cafes, while the second floor is specifically for co-working. On the first floor, there are three main areas. One non-smoking area, then two smoking areas at the back and side. A table with single seating in front of the barista is the place I chose. The sound of music echoing in the room was enough to drown out some of the sounds of chatter from the visitors. Coday Coffee and Eatery also offers many coffee and snack variants. The special menu here is the duck. Spending the holidays at Coday Coffee and Eatery was really fun for me. This is a cafe in Bantul that is nice to be alone with. I feel comfortable when sitting in this area. If I bring a book, maybe reading and finishing a book can be done here.

review_text: MASUKAN UNTUK CODAY COFFEE & EATERY Dear owner coday, sungguh kecewa saya hari ini. pengalaman terburuk yg pernah saya alami di coday caffee&eatery! saya udah langganan disini krn tmptnya cozy kl untuk belajar, wc dan mushola bersih, harga terjangkau. Bahkan saya sering ajak dan rekomendasiin temen kesini, ngejob jg kesini, ngonten juga. Sampai tmn, saya suruh review karena tmptnya cozy (akun wondojunior) tp sayang hari ini saya dipermalukan didepan byk konsumen. saya duduk disharing table krn table yg dekat colokan terpakai semua, dr siang hingga sore. kemudian waiters cowok tinggi pakai baju stabilo (ada di foto 1) pasang tulisan  reservasi  tanpa bilang apa2 membisu. sy tetap duduk krn sy sedang belajar dan sy pikir jika sudah dekat waktu reservasi pasti di infokan krn setau saya attitude yg sopan seharusnya begitu sehingga saya bisa pindah sebelum tamu datang. tp tau2 rombongan hbs wisuda datang bersama keluarganya. trs smpe ada yg nyeletuk  ini kan mejanya, iya kok ini dah ada tulisan reservasi, kok ada orgnya blabla  didepan saya dan dikeras2in. lalu waiters wanita (difoto 2) menegur saya tiba2  permisi kak mejanya sudah direservasi, kakaknya bisa pindah sebelah sana . Tau gk anda mempermalukan konsumen didepan konsumen yg lain, ngusir itu namanya krn tanpa peringatan apapun!. udah gitu gk pke kata maaf yg jelas2 anda salah melakukan itu didepan byk konsumen yg lain. terus habis pindah table, didatengin lg sm lain waiters buat ambil 2 kursi didepan saya. sopan sih mintanya, tp jujur makin berasa diusirnya, pdhl ada kursi kosong yg lain yg bisa diambil selain yg ada didepan saya. baru ini saya sekecewa dan sekagol ini ke cafe. yg tadinya saya langganan disini, skrg gkmau lagi dateng ke cafe ini. so sad, poor attitude, sebagai org yg juga belajar dan berkecimpung didunia kuliner ini sikap yg butuh diperbaiki jika ingin cafe ini bertahan. hari ini menjadi hari terakhir saya kesana. semoga ini bisa jadi masukan dan pembelajaran yg diterima agar tidak ada konsumen yg dipermalukan lagi seperti saya dan anda kehilangan pelanggan lagi. tadi saya sudah meninggalkan pesan dikertas, jika tidak ada maka tanyakan pada waiters hari ini, terimakasih.
review_translated_text: INPUT FOR CODAY COFFEE & EATERY Dear coday owner, I am really disappointed today. The worst experience Ive ever had at Coday Caffee&Eatery! I have subscribed here because the place is comfortable for studying, the toilets and prayer room are clean, the prices are affordable. In fact, I often invite and recommend friends to come here, to do jobs here, to watch content too. Until friends, I asked for a review because the place is cozy (wondojunior account) but unfortunately today I was embarrassed in front of many consumers. I sat at a shared table because the tables near the sockets were all used, from noon to evening. then the tall male waiter wearing a highlighter shirt (in photo 1) put up the words reservation without saying anything and remained silent. I remained seated because I was studying and I thought that if it was near the reservation time, I would have been informed because as far as I was concerned, a polite attitude should be so that I could move before the guests arrived. But suddenly the graduation group came with their families. Then someone shouted This is the table, yes, how come it already says reservation, why is there someone blabla in front of me and shouted loudly. then the female waiter (pictured 2) suddenly reprimanded me excuse me sis, the table has been reserved, your brother can move over there. Did you know that you embarrass consumers in front of other consumers, thats what they call driving them away without any warning! Thats it, dont use an apology that clearly means you did it wrong in front of lots of other consumers. Then after moving tables, another waiter approached me to take 2 chairs in front of me. It was polite to ask, but honestly it felt even more like he was being pushed away, even though there were other empty seats that could be taken apart from the one in front of me. Recently I was as disappointed and confused as I was at the cafe. I used to be a regular here, but now I dont want to come to this cafe anymore. so sad, poor attitude, as someone who is also studying and involved in the culinary world, this is an attitude that needs to be improved if this cafe wants to survive. Today is my last day there. Hopefully this can be input and learning received so that no more consumers are embarrassed like me and you lose any more customers. Ive left a message on the paper earlier, if its not there then ask the waiters today, thank you.

Service: pelayanan ramah dan cepat. Pelayan2nya kayak barista2 senja, penampilannya barista banget lah jadi meyakinkan. Atmosphere: terbuka, jd ga cocok kalo yang senengnya dingin2an AC. Tp ini ga pake AC pun adem dibawah pohon beringin, suasana alun2. Tempatnya jadoel2 gitu, cocok banget buat anak senja deh. Nongkrong lama2 disini seru.
review_translated_text: Food: the coffee is delicious. Havent tried the V60 yet, but the Banana Coffee and Bonbon Coffee flavors are really delicious. He said it was also full Arabica so you dont need to worry about unusual stomach aches. Service: friendly and fast service. The waiters are like twilight baristas, their barista appearance is really convincing. Atmosphere: open, so not suitable for those who like cold air conditioning. But this doesnt use air conditioning and its cool under the banyan tree, in a square atmosphere. Its such a cool place, really suitable for twilight children. Hanging out here for a long time is fun.

review_translated_text: Recommended locations when traveling to North Square Kraton Yogyakarta, Sonobudoyo Museum, Gedhe Kauman Mosque, and Nol KM Malioboro. Stop by for coffee in a fansy atmosphere while enjoying the traffic passing by in the square. Coffee, cake and food are available. Ponti Egg Rice & Talua Tea are the choices to taste. Ponti egg rice with various toppings starting from 12 thousand and tahlua tea is a recommended drink menu that must be tried.

review_text: A nice place to chill around malioboro

I ordered a latte with almond milk because Im lactose intolerant. When I tried the coffee, it tasted like regular milk. I informed the woman at the counter, and she claimed she had made it with almond milk herself. The texture was different, but the taste was definitely that of regular milk. She didnt apologize or investigate further, but rather defended herself by insisting it was almond milk. Even if I was mistaken, I expected a better response to my complaint. I ended up ordering an americano because I couldnt continue drinking the latte. The male waiter apologized, which led me to give an extra star, but I was still very disappointed with how the woman handled the situation. It should be part of their training to understand that milk substitutions are not just about taste, but also about accommodating people who are genuinely allergic to regular milk.
Delicious coffee and drinks, friendly and professional staff. It has balcony with nice Malioboro view.

When I arrived, the boss was really friendly, wanted to chat first and wasnt in a rush (but that doesnt mean its slow.) I stayed while drinking coffee which was really cheap and really delicious in my opinion, I was really willing to go for a long time. But what I applaud is, my car is really clean, right up to the side of my seat which is usually still dirty when I wash it in another place, at a cheap price its really clean, right down to the carpet and the sides of the seats (my hair falls out too, right). But this is really clean and genuine Unfortunately, I work at SBY, not Jogja. If I were at SBY, I hope I can continue to subscribe. Thank you learn coffee car wash and cafe! Good job guys!!!

Iseng iseng liat di google maps ternyata HARGANYA TERBILANG MURAH UNTUK UKURAN CAFE DI KOTA air mineral biasanya mahal di sini cuman 4k omgg serasa ingin berlama-lama tanpa harus menghemat minum. Jujur makanan dan minuman nya masih affordable, tempat nya emang kecil tapi super nyaman di dalem ada 2 meja ku rasa cukup kalo di pagi-siang hari ngak berebut karena emang sepi masih cocok untuk wfc. Dan indoor nya dingin ber-AC + ada kipas, colokan juga ada bersih, pelayanannya paling okeeee ngak lama, dan super ramah barista nya. WA nya juga super fasrespon nanyain jam buka langsung dijawab. Overall semuanya baikk malah super baik, cuman kalo mau kesana rada kejauhan karena dari bantull
review_translated_text: Came here because I often pass through new cities and I noticed several times that there was a cafe which, from the front, was simple, I had been wanting to come here for a long time but because it was so far I only got there yesterday. Just looking for fun on Google Maps, it turns out the PRICE IS CHEAP FOR A CAFE IN THE CITY. Mineral water is usually expensive here, only 4k, I feel like I want to stay for a long time without having to save on drinking. Honestly, the food and drinks are still affordable, the place is small but super comfortable. Inside, there are 2 tables, I think its enough if you dont have to fight in the morning because its quiet, its still suitable for WFC. And the indoor area is cool, air-conditioned + there is a fan, the plugs are also clean, the service is the best, it doesnt take long, and the baristas are super friendly. The WA is also super responsive, asking for opening hours was answered immediately. Overall everything is good, in fact super good, but if you want to go there its a bit far because its from Bantul

Kedua kali makan disini dine in, pesan cookies matcha sama banana crispy rasanya masih sama enak banget. Ga nyesel beli disini, next pengen nyoba pain au choco atau banana strudlenya.
review_translated_text: The first time I ordered cookies, fudgy brownies and crispy bananas at this place, I didnt have high expectations because I had bought soft cookies that tasted too sweet. It turned out that the desserts here were all delicious, the chocolate and matcha flavors were just right, not unpleasant, not too sweet either. tasteless. The second time I ate here, I ordered matcha cookies and banana crispy, the taste was still the same, it was really delicious. You wont regret buying here, next time you want to try the pain au choco or banana strudle.

review_text: Kemarin Oktober pas masih di Jogja pesen kopi disini. Sebenere nek dari aplikasi aku pesen yang lokasinya di Umbulharjo. Tapi ini mau ku review maps nya temporarily closed, yaudah kesini aja. Semoga sama aja ya Dimanapun pesen kopi, buatku paling aman adalah americano no sugar. Karna aku bener2 lagi concern buat ngurangi banyak gula. Bukan penikmat kopi sebenarnya, cuma suka aja minum kopi. Kopinya enak. Pait kopinya masih ada. Menurutku dari beberapa kopi yg pernah ku minum kek cenderung lebih pait, tapi gapapa kalo aku mah, hidupku jauh lebih pait soalnya Aku juga pesen pastrynya pas itu. Ini enak bgt bgt menurutku. Pas baru nyampe wanginya bener2 bikin laper sih. Ku pesen 2 karna biar kena promo aja, taunya makan 1 aja udah kenyang. Gatau coldhands yang sini ada pastrynya engga, tapi seriusan ini enak. Dari beberapa kopi yg pernah kucoba, ku ngga pernah kepikiran untuk repeat order. Tapi di coldhands ini rasanya ku ingin beli lagi karna pastrynya enak. Sayang di Boyolali gaada coldhands. Tapi kupastikan kalo aku ke Jogja, Ill back here
review_translated_text: Last October, when I was still in Jogja, I ordered coffee here. Actually, Grandma, from the application I ordered the location in Umbulharjo. But I want to review the temporarily closed maps, so lets just come here. I hope its the same Wherever I order coffee, for me the safest is Americano without sugar. Because Im really concerned about reducing sugar. Not really a coffee drinker, I just like drinking coffee. The coffee is delicious. The coffee pie is still there. I think from some of the coffee Ive drunk, it tends to be more bitter, but thats okay for me, my life is much more miserable because of that I also ordered the pastry at that time. I think this is really delicious. When it just arrived, the smell really made me hungry. I ordered 2 because I was going to get a promotion, I knew Id be full by eating just 1. I dont know if the coldhands here have pastry, but seriously, this is delicious. Of the several coffees Ive tried, Ive never thought about repeat ordering. But at Coldhands, I think I want to buy it again because the pastry is delicious. Unfortunately in Boyolali there are no cold hands. But I assure you that if I go to Jogja, Ill come back here

review_text: Saya menunggu terlalu lama
response_from_owner_text: Halo kk bisa disebutkan orderannya? Kakak customer offline atau driver online ya? Kami selalu punya SOP waktu estimasi pembuatan menu. Kalo kaka driver online,kami selalu memberi tahu estimasi masak/menghangatkan makanan dan persiapan menu minuman. Kalo kaka seorang driver dengan merating resto bintang 1 hanya karena menunggu persiapan menu rasanya tidak fair karena kami juga butuh waktu apalagi ketika antrian sedang full. Kami memang bukan kedai besar, tapi kami selalu berhati-hati dalam pembuatan menu offline dan online. Apabila ada keluhan silahkan datang ke kedai atau bisa hubungi no contact cs kedai.
review_translated_text: I waited too long
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello, can you mention the order? Are you an offline customer or an online driver? We always have an SOP for estimating time for menu creation. If you are an online driver, we always give you estimates for cooking/heating food and preparing drink menus. If you are a driver who rates a restaurant 1 star just because you are waiting for the menu to be prepared, it doesnt seem fair because we also need time, especially when the queue is full. We are not a big shop, but we are always careful in creating offline and online menus. If you have any complaints, please come to the shop or contact the shops CS contact number.

review_text: Percayalah ini salah satu coffeeshop enak buat menikmati waktu pagi dan sore hari di tengah kota, apalagi tempatnya ada di Prawirotaman yang sekilas ambiencenya mirip dengan Kuta yang ada di Bali. Tempat duduknya kebanyakan outdoor tapi ada beberapa pohon yang membuatnya lumayan rindang ketika siang hari, kopinya enak apalagi yang flavoured latte dua, tiga, dan empatnya wajib dicoba bagi yang suka kopi dengan citarasa manis. Selain kopi susu tersedia juga mocktails dan cocktails yang bervariasi. Koneksi wifi tidak ada namun dengan ambience yang didapat nampaknya mau tanpa wifipun kita bisa enjoy menikmati waktu yang kita habiskan disana.
review_translated_text: Believe me, this is one of the nice coffeeshops for enjoying the morning and evening in the middle of the city, especially since the place is in Prawirotaman, where at first glance the ambience is similar to Kuta in Bali. The seating is mostly outdoor but there are several trees which make it quite shady during the day, the coffee is delicious especially the two, three and four flavoured lattes are a must try for those who like coffee with a sweet taste. Apart from milk coffee, there are also various mocktails and cocktails available. There is no wifi connection, but with the ambience we get, it seems like even without wifi, we can enjoy the time we spend there.

Utk pelayanan okay banget karena request minta dibuatkan agak nantian karena mau jalan sebentar di prawirotaman dan baru dibuatkan pas kami datang jadi mocktail masih fresh dan cappucino nya pun masih panas. Untuk tempat dikasih 4 karena agak kurang tertata, mungkin kalo lebih dimaintenance bisa lebih baik yaaaa Vegetarian options: Aman Dietary restrictions: Pilih aja americano no sugar Parking: Parkir terbatas Kid-friendliness: Gak terlalu kids friendliness, dekat jalan dan ada menu cocktail Wheelchair accessibility: Tidak ada akses sepertinya
review_translated_text: Small coffee bar around Prawirotaman, the same place as Zabunch Burger. The place is not that big, its outdoor like that. There is a coffee menu, mocktails, and even cocktails. Coincidentally, yesterday when I arrived, I ordered the hooks cappuccino and mocktail. Overall the coffee is okay, the mocktail doesnt taste markety (the hock has hints of rose and banana) its fresh. As for the service, it was really good because the request asked for it to be made a bit later because I was going for a short walk in Prawirotaman and it was only made when we arrived so the mocktail was still fresh and the cappuccino was still hot. The place was given 4 because its a bit less organized, maybe if it was maintained better it could be better Vegetarian options: Safe Dietary restrictions: Just choose Americano no sugar Parking: Limited parking Kid-friendliness: Not too kid friendly, close to the road and there is a cocktail menu Wheelchair accessibility: There doesnt seem to be any access

review_text: I just an ordinary coffee fan. and I must say that Dropshot Coffee Bar knows how to brew a mean cup of coffee. The taste of their coffee is truly exceptional. Its rich, aromatic, and perfectly balanced, making every sip a heavenly experience. I found myself savoring every moment and craving another cup. The ambiance at Dropshot Coffee Bar is a warm embrace for the soul. The combination of rustic decor, comfortable seating, and soft lighting creates a welcoming atmosphere thats perfect for catching up with friends, studying, or simply enjoying a peaceful moment with your coffee. Its a place where time seems to slow down, allowing you to fully relax. The cookies at Dropshot Coffee Bar are a delightful addition to your coffee experience. I, too, fell in love with their cookies. They complement the coffee perfectly and are a sweet treat that adds an extra layer of enjoyment to your visit. In summary, Dropshot Coffee Bar in Yogyakarta is a coffee lovers paradise. The exceptional coffee taste, heartwarming ambiance, and delectable cookies make it a must-visit destination. Whether youre a local or a traveler passing through Yogyakarta, this coffee haven deserves a spot on your list. I cant wait to return for another memorable coffee session.

review_text: Dropshot is a trendy coffee and mocktail cafe that offers a minimalist and fun menu that is sure to delight all of your senses. The atmosphere is relaxed and welcoming, with a modern decor that features clean lines, bright colors, and playful accents. One of the standout features of Dropshot is its unique and innovative menu. The cafe offers a wide selection of specialty coffee drinks that are made with high-quality, locally-sourced beans. Whether you prefer a classic latte or something more adventurous, there is something for everyone on the menu. In addition to its coffee offerings, Dropshot also serves a variety of mocktails that are perfect for those who want to enjoy a refreshing and alcohol-free beverage. From fruity and tropical flavors to more complex and savory concoctions, the mocktail menu at Dropshot is both creative and satisfying. But what really sets Dropshot apart is its playful approach to presentation. Each drink is carefully crafted and served with fun and unexpected elements, like edible flowers, brightly-colored straws, and whimsical garnishes. The cafes commitment to aesthetic detail is evident in every aspect of the menu, from the carefully curated flavor combinations to the unique and eye-catching drinkware. Overall, Dropshot is a must-visit destination for anyone looking for a fun and creative coffee and mocktail experience. With its minimalist and playful menu, relaxed atmosphere, and commitment to quality and innovation, this cafe is sure to become a favorite among coffee and mocktail enthusiasts alike.

review_translated_text: DROPSHOTESPRESSOBAR . Jogja . Hello D.I.Y young people! Oh, how can I say that, basically this is a place where you really have to try one of their coffee & non-coffee mocktails as a refreshing drink so that the coffee doesnt look like its just like that, you know... . In terms of baverages, the Mocktail is Debest! [Just communicate with the Barista who is on shift, so the Barista knows what kind of taste you want] The design of the outdoor place is cool, oh yeah here, there is also a semi-outdoor on the inside. Dont forget to ask so its optional if you feel comfortable. . So hurry up and get there, order the Mocktail you like & enjoy!

review_text: Sy menginap di sktr cafe ini, lalu anak sy berniat makan di cafe ini, sy berikan dia credit card & kartu debet, krn anak sy makan dgn adiknya tanpa saya, anak sy sudah memesan spageti dan nasi goreng ayam sesuai daftar menu, dan pelayannya menanyakan duduk dmn, anak sy sdh memberitahunya, tp dgn tiba2 pelayannya blg nasi gorengnya habis, lalu anak sy tanya apakah spagetinya ada, dgn gugup pelayannya blg sudah close order, padahal di cafe tsb msh banyak bule2 yg makan dan nongkrong, apakah krn anak sy berpakaian baju tdr dan keliatan tdk berkelas, jadi anak sy tdk layak utk makan di cafe ini? Anak sy mau mkn di t4 ini liburan lebaran tgl. 11 apr 24, di gugel sy liat jam operasional jam.01.00, anak sy makan jam 23.00. Klo memang close order dr awal anak sy msk pelayannya sudah bilang donk  sudah close order , apakah cafe ini hny diperuntukan bule2 saja??? Org Indo asli ga boleh makan di t4 ini meskipun bayar????!!!
response_from_owner_text: Ibu Susy Djaha yang terhormat, Karena Anda menulis ulasan atas nama anak Anda, sayangnya ada beberapa hal yang tidak benar. Berikut ini adalah apa yang terjadi : Seperti yang Anda lihat di profil Google kami, dapur tutup pada jam 22:30. Anak-anak Anda datang setelah waktu tersebut. Waktu itu di dapur sedang menyelesaikan pesanan terakhir. Pelayan kami mengambil pesanan anak-anak Anda, tetapi kemudian menyadari bahwa sekarang sudah pukul 23:00 dan dapur sudah tutup. Seharusnya dia memeriksa dapur terlebih dahulu, untuk itu kami mohon maaf. Tapi dia tidak bilang bawha Nasi Goreng habis dan kemudian mengubah perkataannya! Kami sangat sedih mendengar bahwa Anda merasa kami tidak ingin melayani anak-anak Anda karena pakaian dan/atau ras mereka. Di Easy Groovy kami menyambut semua orang dan memperlakukan mereka dengan sama tanpa memandang usia, ras, pakaian, jenis kelamin, agama, atau apa pun! Keberagaman sangat penting bagi kami dan ini tercermin dalam tim campuran kami. Kami dengan tulus meminta Anda untuk mempertimbangkan untuk mengubah ulasan Anda atau menghapusnya, karena Anda belum pernah ke sana dan hanya mendengar cerita dari anak-anak Anda. Sekali lagi, kami mohon maaf karena lupa memeriksa status dapur sebelum mengambil pesanan anak-anak Anda
review_translated_text: I was staying near this cafe, then my child intended to eat at this cafe, I gave him a credit card & debit card, because my child was eating with his sister without me, my child had ordered spaghetti and chicken fried rice according to the menu, and the waiter asked sitting there, my child has already told him, but suddenly the waiter says the fried rice is finished, then my child asks if there is spaghetti, nervously the waiter says he has closed the order, even though in the cafe there are still lots of foreigners eating and hanging out, is it because my child is dressed? The clothes are worn out and they dont look classy, so my child isnt fit to eat at this cafe? My child wants to eat at T4 this Eid holiday. 11 April 24, on Google I saw that the operating hours were 01.00, my child ate at 23.00. If my child had closed orders from the start, the waiter had already said its closed orders, is this cafe only intended for foreigners??? Real Indo people cant eat at this T4 even if they pay????!!!
response_from_owner_translated_text: Dear Mrs. Susy Djaha, Since you are writing a review on behalf of your child, unfortunately there are some things that are not true. Here is what happened: As you can see on our Google profile, the kitchen closes at 10:30 p.m. Your children come after that time. At that time in the kitchen finishing the last order. Our waiter takes your kids orders, but then realizes its 11pm and the kitchen is closed. He should have checked the kitchen first, for that we apologize. But he didnt say that the Fried Rice was finished and then change his words! We are deeply saddened to hear that you feel we do not want to serve your children because of their clothing and/or race. At Easy Groovy we welcome everyone and treat them the same regardless of age, race, clothing, gender, religion or anything else! Diversity is very important to us and this is reflected in our mixed team. We sincerely ask you to consider changing your review or removing it, as you have never been there and have only heard stories from your children. Once again, we apologize for forgetting to check the kitchen status before taking your childrens orders

review_text: A Groovy Return to Pawirotaman From Easy Going to Easy Garden, and now Easy Groovy - it seems Yogyakarta cant get enough of your easy vibes! As a happy customer on your Pawirotaman adventure, Im excited to share my experience at the new spot. First things first, location is king, and Easy Groovy nails it. Right across from Gelato on Pawirotaman, its a prime spot for grabbing a bite and a bevvy after a day of exploring. The menu offered a delightful mix of familiar favorites and some intriguing newcomers. We enjoyed good, solid food   juicy burgers, fresh salads, and of course a good beer selection. Those amazing pizzas have left the menu, but enough news to choose from. The juices were a refreshing burst of flavor, and the cold beer hit the spot on a warm Yogyakarta afternoon. Now, opening any new restaurant comes with its challenges, and the hustle and bustle of the first day added to the charm. It was clear the Easy team was working hard to keep everyone happy, and the atmosphere was buzzing with excitement. Overall, Easy Groovy delivers on its promise: easy vibes, good food, and a great location. Its a welcome addition to the Pawirotaman scene, and I cant wait to see what new grooves theyll lay down in the future. Today the staff handled the opening-day rush well! The decor, the music, the overall feeling of the place was comfy. It was casual and a bit laid-back. We want to wish the Easy team success.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Gijs for this absolutely lovely review! We are delighted to hear that you liked our new place and hope you will come back again soon. Yes, we decided to discontinue our famous pizzas but we added many new Mexican dishes and more Indonesian food to our menu.
Thank you sister

Lebih seru dari event sunmor atau CFD dimana pun. Karena di BSF selain bisa belanja makanan, minuman, tanaman, dll, kita juga bisa senam pagi plus belajar ketika ada event pelatihan. Bener-bener seru dan luar biasa. Makin sukses dan semangat buat BSF.
review_translated_text: More exciting than Sunmor or CFD events anywhere. Because at BSF apart from being able to shop for food, drinks, plants, etc., we can also do morning exercise plus study when there are training events. Really exciting and extraordinary. More success and enthusiasm for BSF.

review_text: Event mingguan yg ok punya.. Dekat dengan rumah.. Penjualnya langsung pelaku UMKM warga Banguntapan, jd harganya rerata dibawah pasar.. Bisa jd reseller juga krn harga produsen.. Event yg diadakan juga keren2, ada senam, bincang bisnis, sharing2 berbagai ilmu. Pokoknya kereenn bgt.. Maju terus BSF..
review_translated_text: Its a good weekly event... Close to home.. The sellers are directly MSMEs who are residents of Banguntapan, so the prices are on average below market... Can also be a reseller because of the manufacturers price.. The events held were also cool, there were gymnastics, business talks, sharing of various knowledge. Anyway, its really cool... Keep going BSF...

review_text: Semoga BSF bisa tumbuh dan dapat meningkatkan kesejahteraan bagi pelaku UMKM Banguntapan
review_translated_text: Hopefully BSF can grow and improve the welfare of Banguntapan MSME players

review_text: Masha Allah Finally there are activities on the weekend, no need to go far Yesterday we went there...the menu was excellent Bangtapan UmKM products... are indeed TOP

review_translated_text: A fun way to spend a Sunday morning. You can find food from the old school to the present day. The exercise is also fun, all ages can participate. review_text: Rasa bakso dan mie ayam cukup enak. Harga makanan dan minuman cukup mudah dengan porsi yang pas. Tiap hari jumat ada diskon untuk mie ayam (hanya mie ayam tanpa topping). Parkir mobil cukup. Cenderung ramai saat makan siang. Makanan mulai 10ribu dan minuman 3ribu.
review_translated_text: The taste of meatballs and chicken noodles is quite delicious. Food and drink prices are quite easy with the right portions. Every Friday there is a discount on chicken noodles (only chicken noodles without toppings). Sufficient car parking. Tends to be busy at lunch. Food starts from 10 thousand and drinks from 3 thousand.

place_name: Mie Ayam dan Bakso Idolaku Pak Tikno
review_text: Tempat makan mie ayam solo yang endulita!!!!! Sepertinya tempat makan ini adalah tempat makan yg legend di jogja. Selain menu mie ayam, ada bakso juga. Saya pesan mie ayam ori, menunya cukup gede buat saya dan rasanya enakkk, ga terlalu manis banget jadi rasa asinnya masih mendominasi. Buat yang gabisa makan kalo gaada nasi, tenang aja disini ada tambahan menu nasi!! Jadi aman banget buat porsi   pelayanannya juga sangat cepat satset pol, tempatnya bersih, nyaman, dan sangat proper. Pembayarannya sepertinya hanya bisa cash, untuk parkiran juga cukup luas. Next time bakalan kesini lagi, pertahankan!!
review_translated_text: A great place to eat solo chicken noodles!!!!! It seems like this place to eat is a legendary place to eat in Jogja. Apart from the chicken noodle menu, there are meatballs too. I ordered original chicken noodles, the menu was big enough for me and the taste was delicious, not too sweet so the salty taste still dominated. For those who cant eat without rice, dont worry, there is an additional rice menu here!! So its really safe for portions   the service is also very fast, satset pol, the place is clean, comfortable and very proper. Payment seems to only be cash, the parking lot is also quite large. Next time I will come here again, keep it up!!

review_text: Kesini waktu lebaran kemarin bareng saudara luar kota karena pada penasaran,tempat duduk full di dalem. tinggal diluar panas huhuhu. Menang spot view tugu sih ini. Harga ya bisa di bilang merogoh kocek lebih ya Btw slice cheese cake Oreo patut di coba sih enak harga nya standar juga. Incip nasi goreng pesanan saudara ya lumayan. Yamie nya lumayan. Parking: Lokasi parkir terbatas, susah banget KLO pas rame.
review_translated_text: Came here during Eid yesterday with relatives from out of town because I was curious, the seats were full inside. living outside is hot huhuhu. Winning spot view of this monument. The price can be said to cost more money BTW the Oreo slice cheese cake is worth trying, its delicious and the price is standard too. Taste the fried rice you ordered, its not bad. The Yamie is not bad. Parking: Parking is limited, its really difficult when its crowded.

review_text: Free Palestine. The location is strategic, the food and drinks are all delicious.

review_translated_text: Suitable for hanging out, the coffee is delicious, the service is great, the fried bananas are the best, dont ask about the price, but its worth it

review_text: Pulang dari perjalanan gunung Kidul ke arah Yogya. Berniat mau ngopi dan makan sedikit sebelum pulang ke Semarang, dan melihat tempat ini serasa mengasyikan berada di depan Tugu Yogya. Namun tidak mengasyikan. Yang saya dan teman2 dapatkan kekecewaan pada pelayanannya 1. Pertama tiba disambut hangat dan ramah oleh kepala restonya. Dan dia menginformasikan bahwa akan tutup jam 00.00 malam. Dan saya datang jam 10.35. Saya tanya masih bisa pesan? Dan masih bisa pesan makan?  Jawab dari Orang yang menyambut : baik, bisa apa saja. Lalu saya meng iyakan. Masuk dan pesan. Karena sudah dibilang sebelumnya last order. Dan bisa pesan. Maka kami pesan. Begitu duduk di lantai 2. Saya pesan Es Kopi ( aeropress) pakai ES pisah.  Namun pegawainya bilang tidak bisa. Yang lain saja. Dia menyarankan menu lain yang tidak saya pesan. Ini membuat kecewa. Trus pesan makan nasi, mie pangsit, dan lain2 mereka jawab tidak tersedia. Trus saya tanya  balik yang ada apa? Dia bilang cuma nasi goreng dan bakmi. Telus pegawainya ga niat daftarin menunya. Pegawainya ada sekitar 3 di atas. Dan sepi. Yang ada prang di balkon. Bukannya tadi di bawah bisa pesan apa aja?? Trus saya kecewa dan meninggalkan tempat tersebut. Padahal sayang tempat bagus, pusat kota, pemandangan Tugu Yogya, cozy. Namun pelayanan buruk. Trus pergi ngopi dan makan di tempat lain. Parking: Nice
review_translated_text: Returning from a trip from Gunung Kidul to Yogya. Intended to have coffee and eat a little before returning to Semarang, and seeing this place felt exciting being in front of the Yogya Monument. But its not fun. What my friends and I were disappointed with was the service 1. When you first arrived, you were greeted warmly and friendly by the head of the restaurant. And he informed that it would close at 00.00 at night. And I came at 10.35. I asked if I could still order? And can you still order food? Answer from the person who greeted: OK, it could be anything. Then I said yes. Log in and order. Because it was said before last order. And you can order. So we ordered. As soon as I sat on the 2nd floor, I ordered Iced Coffee (aeropress) using separate ice. But the employee said he couldnt. Just another one. He suggested another menu that I didnt order. This is disappointing. Then ordering rice, wonton noodles, etc. they said they werent available. Then I asked again what was going on? He said only fried rice and noodles. Telus employees dont intend to list the menu. There are around 3 employees above. And quiet. Theres a man on the balcony. Wasnt it possible to order anything below? Then I was disappointed and left the place. Even though its a shame, the place is nice, city center, view of Tugu Yogya, cozy. But bad service. Then go get coffee and eat somewhere else.

review_text: Sebelumnya pernah makan yang di jalan godean itu gak enak banget makanya ragu tapi ternyata setelah dicobain enak banget yang disini. Kebetulan juga gak terlalu rame jadi cepet pelayanannya.

place_name: Special Bakmi & Nasi Goreng Pak Pele
review_text: Rasa masakannya tetap enak, saat kuliah di Jogja dulu sering jajan disini, sekarang aku kesini dengan anakku yang sudah kuliah..  . Pelayanannya tidak nunggu terlalu lama, meski ramai pengunjung, suasana nya suka, ada yg lesehan ataupun pakai meja kursi.. Ada pengamen profesional yang membawakan lagu2 enak didengar dikuping sambil menikmati makanan yang disajikan.. Kalian yang piknik ke Jogja.. harus merasakan suasana disini..  Harganya masih sangat terjangkau.. Jangan kuatir.. Apalagi bagi kantong orang Jakarta..
review_translated_text: The taste of the food is still delicious, when I was studying in Jogja I often had snacks here, now I come here with my son who is already at college..  . The service doesnt take too long, even though there are a lot of visitors, the atmosphere is pleasant, some are sitting on the floor or using tables and chairs... There are professional buskers who sing songs that are pleasant to the ear while enjoying the food served... Those of you who are on a picnic in Jogja... must feel the atmosphere here .. The price is still very affordable.. Dont worry.. Especially for Jakartans pockets..

place_name: Special Bakmi & Nasi Goreng Pak Pele
review_text: Berada di pusat kota kala malam menjelang ditambah perut bak genderang bertalu dan rasa pinisirin melangkahlaah kaki ke ujung alun-alun utara Jogjakarta demi mencicip mie jawa Pak Pele yang lagi nge hits. Berada dalam antrian panjang hingga sekitar sejam baru bisa terpuaskan menikmati seporsi mie jawa di sini. Padahal juru masak nya sudah 3 orang dengan skill mumpuni mampu memasak dengan cepat tapi karena pengunjung yang datang rata-rata berombongan jadi memang harus sabar menanti giliran. Aneka mie dan nasgor jawa bisa dipilih dari deretan menu yang tersedia dan bayarnya cashless tinggal scan QR Code.
review_translated_text: Being in the city center at nightfall, with a stomach like a beating drum and a feeling of pinisirin, I stepped to the end of the north square of Jogjakarta to taste the popular Pak Pele Javanese noodles. Waiting in a long queue for around an hour before you can be satisfied enjoying a portion of Javanese noodles here. Even though there are 3 chefs with excellent skills who can cook quickly, the visitors who come are usually in groups so you have to be patient and wait your turn. A variety of Javanese noodles and nasgor can be chosen from the menu available and you can pay cashless by simply scanning the QR Code.

place_name: Special Bakmi & Nasi Goreng Pak Pele
review_text: Finally mampir juga ke sini. Setelah 4x ke Yogyakarta. Biasanya kalo mau ke sini weekend full banget. Akhirnya pas weekday bisa cepat dapat tempat duduk. Pelayanannya ala rumah makan legendaris lainnya. Rasanya juga khas dengan telur bebek dan ayam kampungnya. Rekomendasi tuk bawa keluarga ke sini. Seuneeeengnya pooollll pasti.
review_translated_text: Finally stopped by here. After going to Yogyakarta 4 times. Usually if you want to come here on weekends its really full. Finally, on a weekday, you can quickly get a seat. The service is like other legendary restaurants. The taste is also unique with duck eggs and free-range chicken. Recommended to bring the family here. Seuneeeengnya pooollll for sure.

review_text: tempatnya simple kecil, meja makan terbatas, kalo gamau join table ya harus sabar nunggu dapet tempat. kalo waktu masaknya cepet kok. sedikit review rasa makanannya ya.. oiya aku makannya ga nambah condiment apa2 uda enak menurutku. - hongkong style : pedes-gurih - singaporean : pedes-manis-gurih (aku gasuka makanan manis, jadi kurang suka) - fried wonton : enak, renyah, panas, isian ayamnya berasa bgt, juicy, gurih - wonton chili oil : enak juga, isiannya sama kek yg digoreng, chili oilnya ga begitu pedes. - oiya topping chicken charsiew enak juga loh, tapi dikit banget dikasihnya wkwk

review_text: Permisi, Saya ingin menyampaikan sedikit saran terkait kebijakan harga tambahan ketika menggunakan cup. Minggu lalu saya mengunjungi Bento Kopi cabang Sorowajan Saya memesan 1 buah Ice Coffe Milk, yang di daftar harga tertulis 10k Tapi ketika membayar, kasir mengatakan bahwa harga yg perlu dibayarkan adalah 11k Saya sama sekali tidak keberatan untuk nambah 1k, namun yang saya permasalahkan adalah akadnya Di menu tertulis 10k, namun di kasir menagih 11k, tanpa menjelaskan bahwa ada tanbahan 1k untuk cup plastik. Di menu pun tidak ada keterangan mengenai tambahan tersebut. Saran saya, hendaknya ditulis keterangan yg jelas di menu terkait kebijakan tersebut, atau mewajibkan kasir untuk menginformasikan adanya tambahan 1k untuk cup plastik Atau misal harganya dinaikkan sekalian pun tidak masalah Pada intinya, saya sarankan manajemen meninjau hal ini. Dengan adanya akad yg jelas, ini bisa menghindari ketidaknyamanan konsumen terkait harga Terimakasih
review_translated_text: Excuse me, I would like to convey a few suggestions regarding additional pricing policies when using cups. Last week I visited Bento Kopi Sorowajan branch I ordered 1 piece of Ice Coffee Milk, which on the price list said 10k But when paying, the cashier said that the price that needed to be paid was 11k I dont mind adding 1k at all, but what I have a problem with is the contract On the menu it says 10k, but the cashier charges 11k, without explaining that there is an additional 1k for the plastic cup. There is no information on the menu regarding these additions. My suggestion is that clear information should be written on the menu regarding this policy, or require the cashier to inform you of the additional 1k for plastic cups. Or, for example, if the price is increased, thats fine In essence, I suggest management review this. By having a clear contract, this can avoid consumer discomfort regarding price Thank You

review_text: Letak strategis, harga makanan dan minuman standar, pelayanan ramah, parkir luas, minuman enak

review_text: Sebenarnya tempat lumayan nyaman dan luas, parkiran pun sangat luas baik motor maupun mobil. Hanya saja di bagian outdoor terasa sangat gerah. Tersedia banyak fan, namun tidak ada satupun yang dinyalakan dan staff pun tidak ada inisiatif menyalakan fan di cuaca siang hari yang terik. Makanan dan minuman cukup murah di rentang harga 13-20 ribuan, namun rasanya jauh di bawah ekspektasi saya. Maksudnya, mentang-mentang murah kemudian kualitas benar-benar seadanya. Saya pesan kopi susu ternyata yang disajikan kopi encer dengan susu kental manis    begitu juga dengan kapucinonya, sangat encer nyaris hambar. Snack pun demikian, order singkong goreng dan tahu walik semua tersaji dalam keadaan dingin sehingga tekstur cenderung keras. Semoga ini bisa menjadi koreksi dan kritik yang memberikan perbaikan ke depannya, khususnya tentang kualitas makanan dan minuman. Murah boleh, tapi jangan segitunya murahan kualitasnya.
review_translated_text: Actually the place is quite comfortable and spacious, the parking lot is very spacious for both motorbikes and cars. Its just that the outdoor part feels very hot. There are lots of fans, but none of them are turned on and the staff doesnt take the initiative to turn on the fans in the hot daytime weather. Food and drinks are quite cheap in the price range of 13-20 thousand, but the taste is far below my expectations. That is, just because its cheap then the quality is really mediocre. I ordered coffee with milk but it turned out to be served with watered down coffee with sweetened condensed milk    as well as the cappuccino, it was very watery, almost tasteless. Snacks are the same, orders of fried cassava and tofu are all served cold so the texture tends to be hard. Hopefully this can be a correction and criticism that will provide improvements in the future, especially regarding the quality of food and drinks. Cheap is fine, but dont make the quality so cheap.

review_text: Udah lama kenal tempat ini, berawal dari temen juga Makanan Insya Allah budget sesuai mahasiswa untuk harga, tempat juga luas, ruangan terpisah antara ac dan non ac, ga di tempat ac pun enak karena kena angin sepoi dan tersedia colokan kalau mepet mepet tembok Ada tempat solat yang gak kecil kecil amat (waktu kesini mukena lagi di laundry semua jadi harus bawa sendiri jaga jaga), juga nyediain sendal buat customer yang pake sepatu, biar leluasa wudu nya Kecepatan internet stabil, waktu itu aku agak lama juga Buat makanan aku pesen kentang goreng sama mie, minumnya lychee tea Kentangnya agak dingin bagian tengah, tapi beberapa doang, mie nya pedes (gaada konfirmasi mau pedes apa nggak alhamdulillah suka pedes) lychee tea yang dikasih sebuah lychee nya juga Tempat parkir luas ga sempit sempit amat Oiya, masnya yang jaga kasir sama bikin minum orangnya sama, gaterlalu banyak kayanya karyawannya, so please wait patiently
review_translated_text: Ive known this place for a long time, starting from friends too God willing, the budget is suitable for students for the price, the place is also spacious, the rooms are separated between AC and non AC, not being in AC is also nice because it gets the breeze and there are plugs available if you are tight against the wall There is a prayer room which is not too small (when I came here, all my mukena was being laundromated so you had to bring your own just to be safe), and also provides sandals for customers who wear shoes, so they can perform their ablution freely. The internet speed is stable, at that time it took me a bit too For food, I ordered french fries and noodles, drank lychee tea The potatoes were a bit cold in the middle, but only a few, the noodles were spicy (no confirmation whether it was spicy or not, thank God I like spicy) the lychee tea was also given a lychee The parking area is spacious, not too narrow Oh yes, the person who is manning the cashier and making drinks is the same person, there arent too many rich employees, so please wait patiently

Duh udah sering banget kesini, baru kali ini kejadian. Perkara sepele sebenernya, tapi gk bisa di sepelein juga Tadi sore aku kesini dan aku gk sengaja numpahin minumanku sendiri yang otomatis ada air minum yang tumpah ke lantai (posisi aku lesehan) ya walaupun airnya cuma tumpah dikit. Aku minta lap ke masnya yang nganter minuman ku, tapi masnya gk respon, ntah gk denger apa gimana, jadi yaudah. Nah disusul temenku baru dateng, otomatis dia pesen dan ada menu yang di anter ke tempat ku dan temenku berada, kebetulan yang nganter masnya beda sama yang nganter minuman punyaku tadi. Aku coba bilang ke masnya buat minta kain lap Mas, boleh minta lap? (Sambil nunjuk air yang ada di lantai lesehan) Alhamdulillah masnya ada respon Oh iya sebentar ya Kak Aku nunggu, mayan lama, dan tiba tiba masnya berdua (yang nganterin pesenan punyaku sama punya temenku) dateng ke kita, nganter menu yang lain punya temenku yang lain juga, mungkin mas yang satunya nyari pelanggan lain yang pesenannya di bawa masnya. Aku berharap masnya bawa lap dong hehe, apalagi datengnya berdua masnya (yang dua duanya ku mintain tolong buat bawain lap). Eh malah pada gk bawa lap sama sekali, padahal mereka liat aku loh, kita tatap tatapan seolah aku natap mana mas lap nya? :( tapi masnya kayak gk peka, apa lupa ya? Dulu aku juga pernah minta kain lap ke mas mas yang nganter pesenan ku, habis itu masnya dateng lagi sambil bawa lap. Buat kedepannya semoga bisa lebih memperhatikan dan mendengarkan apa kata customer ya. Terima kasih sudah melayani kami dengan baik
review_translated_text: Wow, Ive been here a lot, this is the first time this has happened. Its a trivial matter, but it cant be taken lightly either This afternoon I came here and I accidentally spilled my own drink which automatically spilled drinking water onto the floor (where I was lying on the floor), even though the water only spilled a little. I asked the boss who was delivering my drink for a nap, but the boss didnt respond, didnt know what to hear, so that was it. Well, followed by my friend who just came, he automatically ordered and a menu was delivered to where my friend and I were, coincidentally the one who brought it was different from the one who delivered my drink earlier. I tried to tell the boss to ask for a rag Sir, can I have a rag? (While pointing at the water on the floor of the floor) Thank God, bro, there was a response, Oh yes, just a moment, Sis. I waited, it took a long time, and suddenly the two of them (the one who delivered my order and the one my friend had) came to us, delivering another menu from another friend of mine too, maybe the other guy was looking for another customer whose order he brought. I hope the bro brings a rag, hehe, especially since the two of them came (I asked both of them to help bring a rag). Hey, in fact, they didnt bring a rag at all, even though they looked at me, we looked at them as if I were looking, Wheres the rag, sir? :( But the darling doesnt seem to notice, did you forget? In the past, I also asked the boss who delivered my order for a rag, and then he came again with a rag. In the future, hopefully we can pay more attention and listen to what customers say. Thank you for serving us well

review_text: Raos Djogja tampak seperti sebuah rumah makan yang cukup besar dan megah. Beberapa bus dapat terparkir di belakang bangunan. Tempat ini cukup populer dan ramai dikunjungi. Bangunan rumah makan ini memiliki dua lantai, dengan lantai pertama sebagai area makan dan parkir, serta lantai kedua sebagai area makan dan pertemuan. Terdapat panggung kecil. Area parkir Raos Djogja cukup luas dan dapat menampung banyak kendaraan. Hal ini tentunya sangat memudahkan para pengunjung yang membawa kendaraan pribadi. Area parkir ini juga dilengkapi dengan mushola dan toilet berbayar. Area makan ini dilengkapi dengan kipas angin dan angin mbrobos.
review_translated_text: Raos Djogja looks like a fairly large and magnificent restaurant. Some buses can be parked behind the building. This place is quite popular and crowded with visitors. This restaurant building has two floors, with the first floor as a dining and parking area, and the second floor as a dining and meeting area. There is a small stage. The Raos Djogja parking area is quite large and can accommodate many vehicles. This of course makes it very easy for visitors who bring private vehicles. This parking area is also equipped with a prayer room and paid toilets. This dining area is equipped with a fan and blower.

review_text: Raos Djogja Restaurant di Yogyakarta menawarkan pengalaman kuliner yang unik dengan berbagai pilihan masakan yang menggugah selera. Berikut adalah ulasan tentang restoran tersebut: Lokasi dan Jam Operasional : -  Alamat : Jl. Parangtritis KM 3,5 No.99, Brontokusuman, Mergangsan, Yogyakarta, 55153. -  Jam Buka: Setiap hari dari pukul 10:00 - 21:00. Ulasan Pelanggan : - Raos Djogja mendapatkan penilaian **4 dari 5** di Tripadvisor, yang menunjukkan kepuasan pelanggan yang tinggi. - Seorang pengunjung menyebutkan bahwa restoran ini adalah tempat yang luar biasa dengan konsep prasmanan yang ideal untuk makan siang. - Makanan yang disajikan di sini mendapat pujian karena rasanya yang lezat dan porsi yang mengenyangkan. Fasilitas dan Layanan : -  Masakan : Menyajikan berbagai jenis masakan seperti Cina, Asia, Fusion, Makanan Sehat, dan Indonesia. -  Makanan : Tersedia untuk makan siang dan makan malam. - Pelayanan : Dikenal dengan pelayanan yang ramah dan cepat. Suasana : - Restoran ini memiliki suasana yang nyaman dan cocok untuk keluarga, pasangan, maupun individu yang ingin menikmati makanan berkualitas. Kebersihan : - Kebersihan restoran terjaga dengan baik, memberikan kenyamanan lebih bagi pengunjung. Raos Djogja Restaurant menjadi pilihan yang tepat bagi Anda yang mencari tempat makan dengan beragam pilihan masakan dan suasana yang menyenangkan di Yogyakarta.
review_translated_text: Raos Djogja Restaurant in Yogyakarta offers a unique culinary experience with a wide selection of mouth-watering dishes. Here is a review of the restaurant: Location and Operational Hours: - Address: Jl. Parangtritis KM 3.5 No. 99, Brontokusuman, Mergangsan, Yogyakarta, 55153. - Opening Hours: Daily from 10:00 - 21:00. Customer Reviews : - Raos Djogja received a rating of **4 out of 5** on Tripadvisor, which indicates high customer satisfaction. - A visitor mentioned that this restaurant is a great place with a buffet concept that is ideal for lunch. - The food served here is praised for its delicious taste and filling portions. Facilities and Services: - Cuisine: Serves various types of cuisine such as Chinese, Asian, Fusion, Healthy Food, and Indonesian. - Food: Available for lunch and dinner. - Service: Known for friendly and fast service. Atmosphere : - This restaurant has a comfortable atmosphere and is suitable for families, couples and individuals who want to enjoy quality food. Cleanliness : - Restaurant cleanliness is well maintained, providing more comfort for visitors. Raos Djogja Restaurant is the right choice for those of you who are looking for a place to eat with a variety of cuisine choices and a pleasant atmosphere in Yogyakarta.

review_translated_text: If there were 7 stars, I would give this 7 stars. Not because of the 7 headache medicines around, but its really comfortable here. Good food, okay drinks, great service. Im really happy with this fast service Make espresso manually using roxpresso but the taste is really great, fell in love with rum milk coffee. The atmosphere is comfortable, this is suitable for those looking for a place to do assignments or for co-working, which is also good. Plugs are also provided, the music isnt too loud so chatting is still good. The bathroom is also clean, I dont really feel like going back from here. Yesterday I was looking for a place to wait after several unpleasant incidents, coming in here really changed my mood. So come back with a light heart, dont be too disappointed when you find this cafe. Oh yes, this cafe is in Alun2 Kidul, just walk from Alun2. The cafe is full of culinary delights, but the food here is also delicious. The price is affordable, around 20 thousand standard. This is really a hidden gem, if you go to Jogja you have to stop by here. Love it, basically

review_text: Pertama kali ke Sellie Coffee berasa mampir ke rumah teman sendiri. Suasana menyambut setiap tamu yang datang langsung terasa bgitu memasuki ruang kedainya. Lokasi yang sangat strategis dan mudah dijangkau di tengah kota Jogja . Di kawasan penggal  wisata Prawirotaman Jogja membuat semakin menyatu dengan berbagai tempat kuliner, penhinapan dan tempat hangout yang berada dalam satu kawasan.
review_translated_text: The first time I went to Sellie Coffee, it felt like I was at a friends house. The atmosphere of welcoming every guest who comes is felt as soon as you enter the shop. A very strategic location and easy to reach in the middle of Jogja city. In the Prawirotaman tourist area, Jogja makes it more integrated with various culinary places, accommodation and hangout places in one area.

review_text: Sellie Coffee is a small coffee shop thats definitely worth a visit. If youre looking for a cozy and intimate atmosphere with cheap, quality coffee, this place is perfect. The shop has a distinctly artsy vibe thats both modern and unique. Youll find a lot of interesting art pieces and decor that make the space feel very inviting. One of the highlights of Sellie Coffee is their tubruk, a traditional Indonesian coffee brewing method that results in a strong and flavorful cup of coffee. This particular coffee shop has truly mastered the art of tubruk. Their tubruk is great and definitely worth a try if youre looking for something different.
