review_text: Bagus banget dan cozy, kalau ga hujan asik banget. Anak kecilnya dikasih cookies gratis dan mainan, jadi betah banget.
review_translated_text: Very nice and cozy, if it doesnt rain its really cool. The little ones were given free cookies and toys, so they really felt at home.

review_text: Tempatnya tidak teralu luas, tapi cukup menarik untuk ngobrol disini, karena memang tidak terlalu ramai juga
review_translated_text: The place is not too big, but its quite interesting to chat here, because its not too busy either

review_text: Salah satu cafe favorite di jogja yang adem dan nyaman. Staffnya friendly semua dan minumannya enak enak
review_translated_text: One of the favorite cafes in Jogja which is cool and comfortable. The staff are all friendly and the drinks are delicious

review_text: Melipir ke sini krn karena dekat dari alun2, bisa jalan kaki. Tempatnya adem di tengah panasnya Jogja. Di sini yang enak suasananya, tenang, adem, aesthetic. Untuk minuman saya rasa standar cafe/coffee shop. Krn saya suka kopi, menurut saya enak kopinya. Mas baristanya ramah.
review_translated_text: Came here because its close to the main square, you can walk. The place is cool in the heat of Jogja. The atmosphere here is nice, calm, cool, aesthetic. For drinks, I think its standard cafe/coffee shop. Because I like coffee, I think the coffee is delicious. The barista is friendly.

review_text: baristanya sudah menghafal ketika 2x kunjungan jadi tidak perlu sebutkan mau pesan apa sudah di offering duluan. Kopi Susu Regal ya mas? gitu katanya. Tempatnya kecil tapi nyaman untuk ngobrol.
review_translated_text: The barista has already memorized it during two visits so theres no need to mention what you want to order or what has been offered first. Regal Milk Coffee, bro? thats what he said. The place is small but comfortable for chatting.

review_text: Sipp
Tempat ngopi udah buka dari pagi
review_translated_text: The coffee place has been open since morning

review_text: Cafe sekaligus tempat penginapan, pelayanan ramah, f&bnya worth it.
review_translated_text: Cafe and accommodation, friendly service, the F&B is worth it.

review_text: Ngga sengaja lewat dan ternyata vibes coffe shopnya oke bgt.. rasa kopinya juga mantep..
review_translated_text: I accidentally passed by and it turns out the vibes of the coffee shop are really good... the taste of the coffee is also great...

review_text: Kesini random, dan first time. Ga nyangka ada coffee shop yang vibesnya relaxing+private gini. Kursinya gak banyak, nyaman buat ngobrol sama temen2, apalagi posisinya gak di jalan rame. Pesen salted caramel biscoff, mesen ini karna rekomendasi baristany. Buat yg suka manis2, bisa ini. Pesen juga shaken espresso. Light + fresh. Kesini pas siang2, ga kerasa sumuk karna sekeliling banyak pohon+tanaman. Kayaknya lebih asik kalo kesini malem.
review_translated_text: Came here randomly, and first time. I didnt expect there to be a coffee shop with a relaxing + private vibe like this. There arent many seats, its comfortable for chatting with friends, especially since its not on a busy street. Ordered salted caramel biscoff, ordered this because of the baristans recommendation. For those who like sweets, you can do this. Also order an espresso shaken. Light + fresh. Come here in the afternoon, it doesnt feel like its too crowded because there are lots of trees and plants around. It seems like its more fun to come here at night.

review_text: Very pleasant !
review_translated_text: Tres agreable !

review_text: Iiii ini hidden gem yang aku temuin secara ga sengaja. Kayaknya di dalemnya ada guest housenya juga ya. Pelayanannya ramah dan cepet, menu-menunya juga enak. Harga standard sih. Suasananya enak, bukan tipikal yg spacious cafe gitu ya, tapi nyaman. Wangi juga gitu loh pas masuk cafenya, kayak wangi bunga sedap malam. Lokasinya juga ada di tengah kota.
review_translated_text: Iiii this is a hidden gem that I found by accident. It seems like theres a guest house inside too. The service is friendly and fast, the menu is also delicious. The price is standard. The atmosphere is nice, not the typical spacious cafe, but comfortable. It also smells like that when you enter the cafe, like the scent of tuberose flowers. The location is also in the city center.

review_text: Tempat adem semilir & aesthetic, staff ramah, makanan enak, harga masuk akal. Selalu rame.
review_translated_text: Cool, breezy & aesthetic place, friendly staff, delicious food, reasonable prices. Always busy.

review_text: Excellent friendly spot to spend sometime with a coffee drink on a hot day.
Simple, cozy, and nice place

Suddenly visit sih ini. Meeting yang kepagian. Akhirnya ke Sapulu! Ternyata disini sudah buka dari jam 7 pagi. Menunya lebih ke western. Tapi semuanya enak! Menurut aku, tempat ini kurang oke kalau untuk nongkrong lama. Karena tempatnya relatif kecil dan kebanyakan orang yang kesini ya untuk kerja sepertinya (karena membawa laptop). Tapi seru sih. Definisi menikmati Jogja, kerja dari cafe, sambil slow living Notes: - Bisa payment dengan QRIS - Tidak ada retribusi parkir - Ada Resort di bagian belakang cafe ini Enjoy! Semoga terbantu!
review_translated_text: Suddenly visit here. Early meeting. Finally to Sapulu! It turns out its been open here since 7 am. The menu is more western. But everything is delicious! In my opinion, this place is not good for hanging out for a long time. Because the place is relatively small and most people come here for work, apparently (because they bring laptops). But its fun. The definition of enjoying Jogja, working from a cafe, while slow living Notes: - Can pay with QRIS - There are no parking fees - There is a Resort at the back of this cafe Enjoy! Hope this helps!

review_text: Random ke sini sama anak dan suami, ternyata tempatnya lucu, pengunjungnya kebanyakan bule. Di sini juga ada airbnbnya. Staffnya sangat ramah, hospitalitynya juara, mungkin karena standarnya tinggi ya, beda dengan kafe2 lain yg kebanyakan dikunjungi warga lokal. Staff sangat atentif terhadap kebutuhan kami, apalagi kami membawa anak balita. Mulai dari ditawarkan meja yg lebih luas, diambilkan peralatan makan karena lihat kami sharing makanan. Porsi makanannya cukup banyak, jd anak saya tidak bisa menghabiskan makanan sendirian. Ownernya juga sangat humble dan ramah menyapa kami. Anak saya diberi mainan. Selain itu, saya juga melihat ownernya memberikan minuman hangat secara cuma2 untuk lansia yg berjualan kayu.
review_translated_text: Randomly came here with my children and husband, it turns out the place is cute, the visitors are mostly foreigners. There is also an Airbnb here. The staff are very friendly, the hospitality is top notch, maybe because the standards are high, different from other cafes which are mostly visited by local residents. The staff was very attentive to our needs, especially when we brought a toddler. Starting from being offered a wider table, eating utensils being taken because they saw us sharing food. The food portions are quite large, so my child cant finish the food alone. The owner is also very humble and friendly in greeting us. My child was given a toy. Apart from that, I also saw the owner giving free hot drinks to elderly people who sell wood.

review_text: Even though the place is not very large, it is quite comfortable The food and drink are delicious

We came across this coffee place by coincidence and really liked it. The staff were really friendly and tried very hard to explain in English when we had questions. The atmosphere was very nice with the sound of running water and all the plants. Perfect place to hide from the heat and take a break. I tried their Kopi Susu Regal and really enjoyed it. It s basically coffee with milk and crumpled Regal biscuits on top. I might try to make it at home.

Tempat keren, parkirnya cukup luas, di sebrangnya kedai, utk makanan oke, ada prosotan anak, sm atv dgn mini circuit ala2.. Msh dlm pembangunan lg kyknya. Harga makanan std cafe lah yaa Parking: Lokasi di depan kedai,   5rb Kid-friendliness: Anak2 suka main perosotan sm atv (20rb)
review_translated_text: Cool place, the parking is quite large, opposite the shop, for food its okay, theres a childrens slide, an ATV with a mini-circuit ala2... It looks like its still under construction. Std cafe food prices are ok Parking: Location in front of the shop,   5 thousand Kid-friendliness: Kids like to play on ATV slides (20 thousand)

review_text: Tempat nyaman
review_translated_text: Comfortable place

review_text: Beberapa kali makan disini..versi lunch maupun dinner. Pilihan makanan dan minuman sangat beragam, jadi bisa makan sesuai selera masing-masing dan rasanya enak. Pernah acara bareng teman sekitar 60 orang untuk lunch dari jam buka resto, dapat fasilitas ruangan indoor ber-AC, makan prasmanan dan sekalian pesan snack jajanan pasar di tampah. Pesan churros juga dan laris manis. Anak-anak tertarik main ATV jika kesini. Pelayanan bagus dan ramah..fasilitas resto lengkap, ada musholla, toilet, taman, playground dan ruang laktasi juga. Mom n kids friendly banget.
review_translated_text: Have eaten here several times...lunch and dinner. The choice of food and drinks is very diverse, so you can eat according to your own taste and it tastes delicious. Once I had an event with around 60 friends for lunch from the restaurants opening hours, got indoor air-conditioned facilities, ate at the buffet and also ordered market snacks in Tampah. Order churros too and they sell well. Children are interested in playing ATVs when they come here. Good and friendly service...restaurant facilities are complete, there is a prayer room, toilets, garden, playground and lactation room too. Very mom n kids friendly.

review_text: Tempat nya bagus
review_translated_text: Nice place

review_text: Tempatnya nyaman banget, luas, parkirannya juga luas. Kids friendly juga, ada ruangan AC juga disini. Rekomend!
review_translated_text: The place is very comfortable, spacious, the parking area is also spacious. Kids friendly too, there are AC rooms here too. Recommend!

review_text: Lumayan enak akan tetapi mohon maaf layanan agak kurang ramah
review_translated_text: Pretty tasty but sorry the service is a bit less friendly

review_text: Saking banyaknya menu, ngga ada yg rasanya  outstanding . Tapi, bisa dinikmati cuma ngga wah gitu. Yang paling ngena ya menu steambotnya yg tomyum. Tapi menu minumnya okelah. Seger
review_translated_text: There are so many menus, nothing tastes outstanding. But, its just not that great to enjoy. The most popular thing is the Steambot menu which is Tomyum. But the drinking menu is okay. Fresh

review_text: I think the taste of the food need an improvement. Need separate wodho area for men and women. Need a flies catcher or trap, because it is disgusting if my food is infested with flies. Having spacious parking lot and play area for kids are a plus point. But overall is good for family restaurant, keep it up.

Tempatnya ramah anak. Ada play ground, kolam ikan dan kandang kura2. Untuk rasa makaknanya standar...pas kesini pesen nasgor seafood, capcay dan crofle saus strobery. Proses pemesanan dr mulai pesanan masuk sampai ke meja makan lumayan lama. Saran aja untuk tiap meja makan dikasih semacam alat untuk panggil waiters jd ketika pesanan kosong ga perlu bolak balik ke meja pesan. Overall oke lah... Parking: Tempat parkirnya luas untuk mobil dan motor. Parkir motor ada atapnya jd kalo sewaktu2 hujan aman.
response_from_owner_text: terimakasih atas reviewnya kak dengan senang hati kami akan memperbaiki service utk lebih baik kedepannya
review_translated_text: The place is child friendly. There is a play ground, fish pond and turtle cage. As for the taste, the food is standard... here you can order seafood nasgor, capcay and crofle with strawberry sauce. The ordering process from the time the order comes in to the dining table takes quite a long time. Just a suggestion for each dining table to be given some kind of tool to call the waiters so that when an order is empty you dont have to go back and forth to the ordering table. Overall okay... Parking: The parking area is spacious for cars and motorbikes. The motorbike parking has a roof so its safe if it rains.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for the review sis We will be happy to improve our service to be better in the future

review_text: not sure to recomend this food: so far so good, rasanya standar sesuai dengan harganya. porsinya banyak. makanan datang lama, tapi pas sampai tidak dalam kondisi panas/hangat alias dingin alias ngapain aja di dapur? drink: so far so good, rasanya balance, tidak ada yang aneh. services: really bad. pelayan tidak menguasai menu/makanan/minuman. serve hidangan lama dan tidak informatif dalam memberitahu hidangan yang tidak available. hidangan sudah dipesan tapi tidak kunjung datang sampai customer pulang! really bad for the name of restaurant. ambience: standar but more crowded of sounds
review_translated_text: not sure to recommend this food: so far so good, the taste is standard according to the price. the portions are large. The food took a long time to arrive, but when it arrived it wasnt hot/warm or cold, aka what were you doing in the kitchen? drink: so far so good, the taste is balanced, nothing strange. services: really bad. the waiter does not master the menu/food/drinks. serving dishes takes a long time and is not informative in telling which dishes are not available. The dish was ordered but it didnt arrive until the customer went home! really bad for the name of restaurant. ambience: standard but more crowded of sounds

review_text: tempatnya enak buat kumpul bareng teman-teman maupun keluarga, menunya enak enak dan aman dikantong
review_translated_text: nice place to gather with friends and family, the menu is delicious and safe for your pocket

review_text: Pas Ramadan bisa pesan di awal via WA, jadi makanan sudah tersaji saat kami datang. Sayangnya, pesan bakmie dari jam 4 sore, kami udh datang dari stgh 6 tapi bakmie-nya baru datang jam 7. Untungnya ada playground kecil, jadi anak bisa main dulu sambil nunggu makanannya datang. Rasa makanan biasa aja sih.
review_translated_text: During Ramadan, you can order in advance via WA, so the food is served when we arrive. Unfortunately, we ordered bakmie from 4pm, we arrived at 6pm but the bakmie only arrived at 7. Luckily there was a small playground, so the children could play first while waiting for their food to arrive. The food tastes just ordinary.

review_text: harga terjangkau, parkir sangat luas cocok utk acara acara kantor
review_translated_text: Affordable prices, very spacious parking, suitable for office events

review_text: waktu itu cuma pesen kopi caramel, lumayan sih, sayangnya jam 10sudah tutup, jadi jam setengah 10 sudah mulai di usir wkwk
review_translated_text: At that time, I only ordered caramel coffee, which was not bad, unfortunately it was closing at 10, so at half past 10 they were starting to get kicked out hahaha

review_text: pelayanan lama, makan nasi goreng seafood cuma di kasih 1 udang,
review_translated_text: long service, eating seafood fried rice only given 1 shrimp,

review_text: Rekomended untuk buber keluarga, temen, rombongan. Makanannya enak2 dan variasi, pelayanannya bagus. Kalau mau buber lebih baik reservasi dulu dan sekalian pesen makan. Makanannya dateng cepet, padahal tempat full reservasi. Tapi managemen mereka bagus. Jadi bagi yang sudah reservasi dan pesen makan duluan saat reservasi, datangnya makanan cepet. Pelayanannya cekatan, mereka menanyakan ke setiap meja ada yang kurang tidak dari pesanan. Dapet free takjil. Musholla cukup luas, jadi bisa menampung banyak orang, gak penuh karena nunggu antrian. Ada indoor ac, indoor meeting room, gubuk, outdoor taman. Parking: Parkir di sebrang jalan dari kedai. Luas, dan mudah untuk parkir. Bisa mobil banyak. Sepeda motor beratap, jadi tidak perlu khawatir kehujanan motornya. Kid-friendliness: Ada tempat bermain anak, ada kura2nya, ada tamannya atau open space hijau untuk anak yang sedang aktif2nya. Ada tempat atv nya, tapi sepertinya sedang proses perbaikan.
review_translated_text: Recommended for family members, friends, groups. The food is delicious and varied, the service is good. If you want to break up, its better to make a reservation first and order food at the same time. The food came quickly, even though the place was full of reservations. But their management is good. So for those who have made reservations and ordered food first during the reservation, the food arrived quickly. The service was fast, they asked each table if there was anything missing from the order. Get free takjil. The prayer room is quite spacious, so it can accommodate many people, its not full because of waiting in line. There is indoor air conditioning, indoor meeting room, hut, outdoor garden. Parking: Park across the street from the shop. Spacious, and easy to park. Can do lots of cars. The motorbike has a roof, so you dont need to worry about the motorbike getting rained on. Kid-friendliness: There is a childrens play area, there are turtles, there is a park or green open space for children who are active. There is an ATV place, but it looks like it is in the process of being repaired.

review_text: Rekomendasi tempat makan, warmindo hitz
review_translated_text: Recommended place to eat, warmindo hitz

review_text: You have to be patient, the waiting time for food is long. 1 star for speed bumps in front of the location. If its one its still okay.. Its three and its big. The local residents are sure to grumble when they pass in front of this restaurant... I would add a star if it was replaced with a speed trap that is reasonable and not too high.
First and impressive experience, the menu is delicious and the children like it, Alhamdulillah Kid-friendliness: The menu is delicious and kids will definitely like it, the menu is up to date
Recommended
Joss place..

Tempatnya mudah ditemui di maps, parkirannya luas. Pelayanannya ramah, karyawannya cukup banyak, tempatnya lumayan sepi waktu itu, nyaman, tempatnya memanjaaang jadi bisa duduk paling belakaang, ada mushola juga, ada tempat bermain anak seperti ayunan, perosotan, ada hewan kura2 sama kelinci juga Makanannya enak buat sop iganya, yang lainnya biasa, ada bakmi godog atau goreng juga, cukup pricey untuk harganya.
review_translated_text: The place is easy to find on maps, the parking is spacious. The service is friendly, there are quite a lot of employees, the place is quite quiet at that time, comfortable, the place is wide so you can sit at the back, there is a prayer room too, there is a place for children to play like swings, slides, there are turtles and rabbits too The food is delicious for rib soup, everything else is normal, there are godog or fried noodles too, quite pricey for the price.

review_text: tempatnya luas.. parkir sisi timur kedai... tempatnya nyaman menu nya lengkap... ada arena maen khusus anak...
review_translated_text: the place is spacious... parking is on the east side of the shop... the place is comfortable, the menu is complete... there is a special childrens play area...

review_text: Good

masakan nya enak...tempat nyaman...parkir luas...ada ruang ber-AC sehingga nyaman buat keluarga. ada playground nya juga. Bakmi goreng jawa bumbunya kurang mantep...coba di perbaiki lagi...padahal nasi goreng magelangan nya pas bumbunya.
review_translated_text: the food is delicious...the place is comfortable...ample parking...there is an air-conditioned room so it is comfortable for families. there is a playground too. The seasoning for the Javanese fried noodles is not good...try to improve it again...even though the seasoning for the Magelangan fried rice is just right.

review_text: Enak.. Murah.. Bersih pelayanan cepat ramah
review_translated_text: Delicious.. Cheap.. Clean, fast, friendly service

review_text: Tempat makan konsep kafe, menunya banyak banget. Dari mie Jawa, pempek, steambot, ramen, dimsum, rice bowl, lasagna, churos, dll. Wedhang , jus, milkshake, dan kopi ada. Desert juga beragam. Kalau dilihat dr depan kecil tetapi memanjang ke belakang. Ada lesehan, kursi, taman di belakang. Ada playground, dulu Ada keluncinya tapi terakhir kesini kelincinya pada mati. Sedih nya anakku (salah satu daya tarik bagi anak2 kalau ada playground dan kelinci). Kamar mandi bersih, ada nursery room (berasa di mal ya). Udah sering kesini, sampai gak bisa dihitung heheh.. Karena makanannya dan minumannya murah dan enak. Pelayanan wis wus cepet meskipun antri. Tempat luas, parkir di seberang (space motor dan mobil mencukupi).
review_translated_text: Cafe concept dining place, the menu is very large. From Javanese noodles, pempek, steambot, ramen, dimsum, rice bowls, lasagna, churos, etc. Wedhang, juice, milkshakes and coffee are available. Deserts are also diverse. If you look at it from the front, it is small but extends towards the back. There are loungers, chairs, a garden at the back. There is a playground, there used to be a rabbit but the last time I came here the rabbit died. My child is sad (one of the attractions for children is that there is a playground and rabbits). The bathroom is clean, there is a nursery room (it feels like youre in a mall). Ive been here so many times I cant count heheh... Because the food and drinks are cheap and delicious. Wis wus service is fast even though there is a queue. Spacious place, parking opposite (sufficient space for motorbikes and cars).

review_text: Suasana oke, sangat family friendly, ada wahana mainan untuk anak. Tempatnya memanjang kedalam, jadi aman untuk anak kecil bermain, tidak dekat jalan. Makanannya jg lumayan oke, ricebowl porsinya banyak. Penampakan makanan sesuai di buku menu.  Ada banyak variasi makanan Parking: Lokasi parkir di seberang kedai. Tempatnya luas untuk mobil dan motor. Parkiran motor ada atapnya jadi tidak kehujanan.
review_translated_text: The atmosphere is okay, very family friendly, there are toy rides for children. The place extends inside, so its safe for small children to play, not near the road. The food is also pretty good, the rice bowl portions are large. The appearance of the food is according to the menu book. There are many variations of food Parking: Parking location opposite the shop. The place is spacious for cars and motorbikes. The motorbike parking lot has a roof so it doesnt get rained on.

review_text: Minggu, 28 Agustus 2022. Menunya ok, citarasa maknyusss -> Sudah 4x kesini, terakhir Minggu, 03 Maret 2024
review_translated_text: Sunday, August 28 2022. The menu is ok, the taste is delicious -> Been here 4 times, last Sunday, March 3 2024

review_text: Pesanan yang nyusul tidak diproses, dan pesan wafel sampe kelewat belum dibikin. Service nya tidak memuaskan.
review_translated_text: Subsequent orders were not processed, and the waffle order arrived too late and had not been made. The service is not satisfactory.

review_text: Ice milk hazelnut rasanya aneh :)
review_translated_text: Hazelnut ice milk tastes strange :)

Pelayanannya cekatan, booking h-1jam diluar expect bakal lancar acaranya    thankss pokoknya Makanan, minum, snack semua enak.. murah lagiii, porsi jg banyak Ada playground outdoor, tempat main atv jd bawa bocil tetap Parkirnya luasssss bgttt. Next pengen kesini lagi
review_translated_text: Highly recommended... The service is fast, booking 1 hour beyond expectations the event will run smoothly    thanks anyway Food, drinks, snacks are all delicious... cheap and large portions There is an outdoor playground, a place to play ATVs so bring a small child The parking is really spacious. Next I want to come here again

review_text: Heritage.. wonderful restaurant.. Recommended.... Food
Atmosphere and interior are amazing. The food was average. We were only customers at 6 pm on Friday. Too early? Maybe
Tempat ini restoran sekaligus museum, yang sering dimakan pangeran makanan yang ada di menu
review_translated_text: This place is a restaurant and museum, where the prince often eats the food on the menu

review_text: Pengalaman yang luar biasa sekali bisa berkunjung ke gadri resto, tempat dan makanan yg worth it untuk di nikmati. Di layani sama mba dari aceh yg sangat ramah + di kasih option buat tempat yg bisa di kunjungi di jogja karna kebetulan baru hari pertama disana hehe. Sukses selalu untuk gadri resto
review_translated_text: It was an extraordinary experience to be able to visit Gadri Restaurant, a place and food that is worth enjoying. Served by a lady from Aceh who was very friendly + given options for places to visit in Jogja because it happened to be only her first day there hehe. Always success for Gadri Resto

review_text: Makan dengan table manner
review_translated_text: Eat with table manners

review_text: Resto menu tradisional Jawa dengan table manner
review_translated_text: Traditional Javanese restaurant menu with table manners

review_text: The food is delicious, nasi blawong, tamarind ribs are a must try The drink is recommended Javanese beer
suasana keratonnya dapet, makanannya enak,
review_translated_text: the palace atmosphere is good, the food is delicious,

review_text: Went to had lunch hoping their meals will be as great as the Bale Raos just to see its not (sorry to say). But again, it was a good experience for me.

German tourists (couple): Delicious food, a bit too spicy for my palate. Vegetarian alternatives upon request. Long wait for the food (40 minutes). Great ambience and mini tour of the Sultans brothers premises. Vegetarian options: Simply state that you want vegetarian food, then swap the meat side dish for tofu or other soy dishes.
review_translated_text: Deutsche Touristen (Ehepaar): Leckeres Essen, fur meinen Gaumen etwas zu scharf. Auf Wunsch vegetarische Alternativen. Lange Wartezeit auf das Essen (40 Min.). Tolles Ambiente und Mini-Fuhrung durch die Raumlichkeiten des Bruders des Sultans. Vegetarian options: einfach angeben, dass vegetarisch gewunscht ist, dann tauschen sie die Fleischbeilage in Tofu oder andere Sojagerichte.

review_text: Menikmati makanan dengan suasana keraton, berasa jadi sultan semalem. Hahahaa
review_translated_text: Enjoying food in a palace atmosphere, feels like a sultan for the night. Hahaha

review_text: Terrific food, terrific service, great environment. Having tried the restaurant linked to the palace, I thought this was tastier, with better ventilation and  no flies! Gentle gamelan music in the air, birdsong from burung kuku and other songbirds and the gentle December breeze made it really pleasant. I enjoyed my orange juice, with fresh lime accents! It was so good I had to go for seconds and then the nasi kuning was super tasty with impeccably made side dishes. Each one bursting with flavor and a good complement for the meal. Loved it! We also got their version of coconut rice, and a super yummy braised beef short rib with fried rice! Not to mention to super fresh and tasty tahu telur. Mmm

review_text: Resto ini sepertinya usaha keluarga. Tempatnya pun merupakan rumah keluarga Gusti Joyokusumo (adik kandung Sri Sultan HB X). Berkunjung ke sini saat malam hari, dan bertepatan menghadiri HUT salah satu OKP di Jogja. Makanan yang disajikan enak. Pelayanan ramah. Suasana di sini sangat kental dengan kebudayaan Jawa baik itu bangunan, kuliner, cerita, benda peninggalan, hingga terdengar alunan gamelan khas Jogja. Terdapat banyak foto di dinding yang berisi foto keluarga Gusti Joyo, HB X, dan bahkan keluarga keraton lainnya. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.
review_translated_text: This restaurant seems to be a family business. The place is also the family home of Gusti Joyokusumo (the younger brother of Sri Sultan HB Visited here at night, and coincided with attending the anniversary of one of the OKPs in Jogja. The food served is delicious. Friendly service. The atmosphere here is very thick with Javanese culture, including buildings, culinary delights, stories, heritage objects, and even the sounds of typical Jogja gamelan. There are many photos on the walls containing photos of the Gusti Joyo family, HB X, and even other palace families. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.

review_text: Quick Info: Free Wifi: with a minimum purchase of 30,000 Rupiahs. QRIS payment: Available with a minimum purchase of 20,000 Rupiahs. Working Space: Costs 50,000 Rupiahs per person. Detailed Review: It was my first time visiting a mini market fused with a cafe concept, and I found it intriguing. The ambiance is quite cozy, with the added bonus of WiFi and a designated working space available. However, its worth noting that access to the working space requires renting through the cashier. Aside from selling snacks, beverages, and miscellaneous items typical of a minimarket, they also offer a variety of heavy and light meals, coffee, and tea which can be ordered through the cashier. Orders are usually called out for collection. The establishment spans two floors, with the outdoor area on the second floor providing a view of Taman Siswa street. Its suitable for smokers as its not indoors. I enjoyed my experience here. However, there are a few suggestions Id like to offer. Firstly, the method of calling out orders could be improved as sometimes its hard to hear from the second floor. Perhaps using a speaker system for announcements would ensure everyone can hear clearly. Enhancing the communication system for order calls could significantly improve the overall customer experience. Implementing a digital display or smartphone app for order notifications could be a modern and efficient solution. This would not only ensure that customers on both floors are promptly alerted when their orders are ready but also add a tech-savvy touch to the cafes atmosphere Additionally, I found the availability of electricity outlets somewhat limited. Addressing the issue of limited electricity outlets is essential for catering to the needs of modern-day patrons who often rely on electronic devices for work or leisure activities. Installing additional outlets strategically throughout the cafe, especially in the working space area, would encourage customers to linger longer, potentially leading to increased sales and customer satisfaction. Overall, while Alfa X Taman Siswa offers a unique and enjoyable experience, addressing these minor shortcomings would elevate its appeal and make it a go-to destination for both locals and visitors alike. Parking: It cost me 2.000 rupiahs for parking

review_text: Awalnya nyari-nyari coworking space daerah selatan, dan muncullah AlfaX ini. Ternyata di dalemnya ada coworking space gitu yang disewain per hari/minggu/bulan. Tempatnya nyaman, makanannya jg cukup enak, payment bisa cash atau cashless, staffnya ramah-ramah dan accommodating buanget (shout out to mas-mas yg baru semir rambut sama mas-mas yg tinggi), wifi lumayan kenceng (buat nugas & kerja biasa okelah), colokan di dalem juga banyak. Trus soal AC, AC di dalem workspacenya dingin. Kedinginan! Haha. Buat yg suka dingin pasti ga masalah. Tp krn aku rakjel, wajib bgt bawa jaket (+sarung tangan kalo perlu). Downsidenya paling bagian toilet. Toiletnya sering bau dan licin lantainya    plus gaada tissue. Udah pernah minta tissue toilet tp belum direfil juga setelah 3 minggu wkwkwkw jadi selalu bawa tissue sendiri dr rumah. Moga bisa diperbaiki Overall, it was a great 3-week experience.
review_translated_text: Initially I was looking for coworking spaces in the south, and this AlfaX appeared. It turns out that inside there is a coworking space that is rented per day/week/month. The place is comfortable, the food is quite delicious, payment can be cash or cashless, the staff is friendly and accommodating, really (shout out to the guys who have just had their hair dyed and the tall guys), the wifi is pretty fast (for assignments & normal work, its okay ), there are also lots of plugs inside. Then about the AC, the AC in the workspace is cold. Freezing! Ha ha. For those who like it cold, its definitely not a problem. But because Im a rakjel, its mandatory to bring a jacket (+ gloves if necessary). The downside is the toilet part. The toilet often smells and the floor is slippery    plus there is no tissue. Ive asked for toilet tissue but it hasnt been refilled after 3 weeks hahaha so always bring your own tissue from home. Hopefully it can be repaired Overall, it was a great 3-week experience.

Utk co working space harus bayar sewa ruang 50k/12 jam/ orang. Benefit nya dapet makan berat/ minum senilai 15-20k + Snack/minuman kemasan senilai 5-10k. Selain itu dapet akses wifi utk 2 gadget. Buat yg bener2 butuh ruang privat cocok bgt asli. Karna ruang lebih ekslusif, ga semua org bisa masuk karna ada kunci akses khusus. Ruangan juga nyaman, AC dingin, sayangnya bagian lesehan lantai nya bolong. TAPIII buat yg gak bener2 butuh ruang privat kurang recommended! Karna apa? Dg bayar 50k cuma dapet benefit makan+minum senilai 25-30k dan hanya ada akses wifi buat 2 gadget. Mungkin kalau di kafe lain bisa wifian sepuasnya dg cukup bnyk gadget. Oiyaa, nasi Dori sambal matah nya mantapp, sayangnya wadahnya terlalu kecil, nyendoknya susah
review_translated_text: Alfamart next level. Here the focus is on the cafe & co working space concept rather than the minimarket. There are several choices of space, indoor cafe, outdoor, co working space, and meeting room. For co-working space you have to pay 50k/12 hours/person to rent the space. The benefit is getting a heavy meal/drink worth 15-20k + snacks/packaged drinks worth 5-10k. Apart from that, you get WiFi access for 2 gadgets. For those who really need a private space, its really suitable. Because the space is more exclusive, not everyone can enter because there is a special access key. The room was also comfortable, the AC was cold, unfortunately the floor had a hole in the floor. BUT for those who dont really need a private room, its not recommended! Because of what? By paying 50k you only get the benefit of eating + drinking worth 25-30k and there is only wifi access for 2 gadgets. Maybe in other cafes you can have unlimited WiFi with lots of gadgets. Oh yes, the Dori sambal matah rice is great, unfortunately the container is too small, its difficult to scoop

review_text: Co Working Space which is really worth it, 50k a day + 2 food items. Wifi is actually relatively good, not very fast, but the place is super comfortable for working, doing assignments, writing a thesis or just hanging out. You will be given an access key if you want to rent the working space. The facilities are complete and very comfortable
Pilihan makanannya lumayan variatif dengan harga yang terjangkau. Tersedia fasilitas indoor dan outdoor. Untuk yang mau kerja bareng bisa juga di area lantai 2 atau co-working space lantai 1.
review_translated_text: The food choices are quite varied with affordable prices. Indoor and outdoor facilities are available. For those who want to work together, you can also work in the 2nd floor area or the 1st floor co-working space.

review_text: Tempat makannya di lantai atas ada rooftopnya juga jadi bisa lihat pemandangan kota sambil makan cuman kalau siang puanaass, kalau malam atau sore mendingan, ya cuma yang dilihat pemandangan kota saja. Kalau makanan rasanya standar sih makanan yang khas foodcourt gitu laah, kopi juga standar saja. Parkirnya enak cukup luas juga di basement. Sayangnya kurang petunjuk kalau ada foodcourt dilantai atas jadi buat orang yang belum pernah nggak akan tau. Apalagi petunjuk cara menuju keatas juga tidak ada, saya waktu pertama nyasar dan kebetulan ada satpam jadi di kasih tau, coba kalau nggak ada satpam? Oya kalau siang panas banget sih mungkin harus ada kipas ya yang ada embun uapnya jadi adem.
review_translated_text: The place to eat on the top floor has a rooftop, so you can see the city view while eating, but if its midday, its better if its at night or in the afternoon, so you can only see the city view. If the food tastes standard, its typical food court food, the coffee is also just standard. The parking is nice and quite spacious too in the basement. Unfortunately there is no indication that there is a food court on the top floor so people who have never been before wont know. Moreover, there were no instructions on how to get up, I got lost the first time and happened to have a security guard so I was told, what if there wasnt a security guard? Oh yes, if its a really hot day, maybe there should be a fan with steam to make it cool.

review_text: Tempat asik buat nyore bersama keluarga.. Relatif bersih meski pas saya kesana lantainya agak becek karena hujan   Tersedia anjungan utk menikmati skyline kota Jogja.. Untuk makanan yg tersedia enak2 dan harganya terjangkau, ora nuthuk.. service juga bagus      Berasa nggak sedang di pasar..   moga makin banyak pasar di Jogja yg dibikin kayak gini..
review_translated_text: A cool place to spend time with the family.. Relatively clean even though when I went there the floor was a bit muddy because of the rain   There is a platform to enjoy the Jogja city skyline.. The food available is delicious and the price is affordable, dont worry.. the service is also good      Taste not at the market..   I hope more markets in Jogja are made like this..

review_text: Lebih di banyakin stand nya, buka lebih pagi biar yg mau sarapan setelah belanja bisa langsung menikmati sarapan di rooftop
review_translated_text: There are more stands, they open early so that those who want to have breakfast after shopping can immediately enjoy breakfast on the rooftop

review_text: Kesini udh sore, naik ke atas lewat lift. Pemandangan sore menjelang maghrib lumayan asik sih... makanan disini jg enak-enak
review_translated_text: Came here in the afternoon, went upstairs via the elevator. The view in the afternoon before sunset is quite cool... the food here is also delicious

review_text: Kalau sore menjelang malam cocok untuk nongkrong, suasana syahdu. Tenant makanan ada banyakkk dan enak-enakk.
review_translated_text: In the late afternoon, its suitable for hanging out, the atmosphere is serene. There are lots of food tenants and its delicious.

review_text: Lumayan asik buat ngadem, pasar rasa mall. Bersih waktu ke sana ngk bauk sampah. Rawonnya unik 7/10 ngk ada telur asinnya. Sambelnya jg manis saos bukan pedes cabe. Cenderung di rasa manis bukan gurih asin. Sering makan rawon asli buatan saudara yg orang Jatim ngk begini. Penasaran sama Moerni, besok kapan kalau ada waktu dolan ke sini lagi. Parking: Parkir di basement
review_translated_text: Pretty cool for chilling out, the market feels like a mall. It was clean when I went there, it didnt smell like rubbish. The rawon is unique 7/10 Theres no salted egg. The sauce is also sweet, not spicy chili sauce. It tends to taste sweet, not savory and salty. I often eat real rawon made by relatives from East Java who dont like this. Im curious about Moerni, tomorrow, if I have time, Ill come here again. Parking: Parking in the basement

review_text: Suasana Jogja,dari ketinggian pasar Kid-friendliness: Pokoke Mak nyuss Food : 5/5 |
review_translated_text: The atmosphere of Jogja, from the height of the market Food

review_text: Sebetulnya tempatnya bagus, sejuk kena angin sepoi sepoi, cuma sayangnya naik kesana pas pasar udh tutup jadi full pakai tangga sampai lantai 4. Makanannya lumayan ya. Cocok utk nongkrong. Harga makanan juga wajar. Ada beberapa pilihan makanan.
review_translated_text: Actually the place is nice, cool with a gentle breeze, but unfortunately I went up there when the market was closed so it was full of stairs up to the 4th floor. The food was pretty good. Suitable for hanging out. Food prices are also reasonable. There are several food choices.

review_text: The wind on the roof top is cool, the view is good, the food is delicious, the prices are reasonable Ample parking downstairs, good toilets, market smell that makes you nauseous but its clean

Makanan dan minumannya enak-enak sih, banyak tenantnya. Harganya terjangkau. Dapet view rooftop. Tapiii, ini tempatnya tuh di rooftop pasar gitu kan, di pasarnya juga jualan sayur daging ikan dll. Ternyata lalatnya nyampe ke tempat makan rooftop dong (kebayang gak?) Lalat gede-gede gitu. Bukan salah tenant makanannya sih, apalagi tempat makannya outdoor gitu kan, lalatnya mau gak mau ya nyampe atas gitu krn lantai bawah pasar bahan seger huhuhu. Sedih
review_translated_text: The food and drinks are delicious, there are lots of tenants. The price is affordable. Get a rooftop view. But, this place is on the rooftop of the market, right? The market also sells vegetables, fish, etc. It turns out the flies arrived at the rooftop dining area (can you imagine that?) The flies were so big. Its not the food tenants fault, especially since the place to eat is outdoor, right? The flies inevitably get to the top because the ground floor is at the fresh ingredients market huhuhu. Sad

review_text: The meal was delicious and it was nice to have a cool night. The goulash and dim sum were delicious.

Makan siang cari steak dll..ternyata banyak yang buka siang diatas jam 12, sebenarnya menu dan foodcourt cukup banyak pilihan, dan rasa cukup enak serta harga tidak mahal, suasana nyaman dan bersih..lift sangat membantu untuk lansia..
review_translated_text: Lunch looking for steak etc..it turns out there are many that open at noon after 12, actually the menu and food court have quite a lot of choices, and the taste is quite good and the prices are not expensive, the atmosphere is comfortable and clean..the lift is very helpful for the elderly..

review_text: Jam makan full banget.. 2x kesana cancel, soalnya lg kelaparan bgt ! Males antri trs cr makan tempat lain. Sore jm plg kantor jg ruame.. Baiknya punya plan A, B & C utk pilihan makan disekitar Jl. Parangtritis.
review_translated_text: Meal time was really full... I canceled it twice because I was so hungry! Im too lazy to queue so I can eat somewhere else. In the afternoon when Im home from the office its also busy... Its good to have plan A, B & C for eating options around Jl. Parangtritis.

review_text: Ada di Pasar Prawirotaman bagian paling atas (rooftop). Kalo bawa kendaraan bisa langsung parkir di basement, trus langsung naik ke rooftop pakai lift dr basement. Tempatnya cukup luas, hanya saja ketersediaan tempat duduk mungkin bisa ditambah lagi.
review_translated_text: Its at the top of the Prawirotaman Market (rooftop). If you bring a vehicle, you can park directly in the basement, then go straight up to the rooftop using the lift from the basement. The place is quite spacious, its just that the availability of seating could possibly be increased.

review_text: Darang ke sini sore, toilet dan mushola nya bersih. Minuman es nya enak2. Suasananya syahdu juga.
review_translated_text: Darang came here in the afternoon, the toilet and prayer room were clean. The iced drinks are delicious. The atmosphere is serene too.

review_text: An alternative to hanging out and having snacks in the city of Jogja... appreciation for the management... Need to increase the variety of food to make it more crowded...

Tidak diragukan, datang kesini sore saat cuaca cerah, cocok buat deep talk bareng teman atau pasangan. Buat wisatawan pendatang seperti saya, cukup membingungkan saat mencari lokasi ini. Di google maps titiknya sudah sesuai, hanya untuk menuju ke lokasinya mesti bertanya sana-sini dulu. Dan ternyata tempatnya tepat ada di lantai 4 (kalau tidak salah) Pasar Prawirotaman. Rooftop pasar disulap menjadi tempat nongkrong nyaman dan hangat. Untuk makanannya variatif. Ada banyak tenant yang bisa dipilih sesuai selera. Pembayarannya pun sudah bisa cashless. Jangan khawatir, parkir ada basement pasar. Datang kesini lebih baik di waktu sore menjelang malam. Duduknya di atas tepat menghadap ke jalan Prawirotaman.
review_translated_text: There is no doubt that coming here in the afternoon when the weather is sunny is suitable for deep talks with friends or your partner. For foreign tourists like me, it is quite confusing when looking for this location. On Google Maps the point is correct, just to get to the location you have to ask here and there first. And it turns out the right place is on the 4th floor (if Im not mistaken) of Prawirotaman Market. The market rooftop was transformed into a comfortable and warm place to hang out. The food is varied. There are many tenants to choose from according to your taste. Payment can also be cashless. Dont worry, parking is in the market basement. Its better to come here in the afternoon towards evening. It sits at the top directly facing Prawirotaman Street.

review_text: Not many food options, but the place is clean and new. There is lift and a co-working space too. Not many food options. If you go at sunset time go sit at the outdoor upper level, to the sunset direction. These tables are usually full, so be early like 5 pm. Food

Berekspektasi ada banyak pilihan food court, tapi hanya terdapat 5 atau 6 food court yang tersedia. Rooftop paling atas tidak begitu luas, kira-kira ada 4 8 meja yang menyuguhkan panorama Jalan Prawirotaman dan sekitarnya. Kemarin, saya mencoba jajanan Moerni 78, yakni yammie asin, es teh, dan es campur.
review_translated_text: Expecting there to be many food court options, but there are only 5 or 6 food courts available. The top rooftop is not very wide, there are approximately 4 to 8 tables offering a panoramic view of Jalan Prawirotaman and its surroundings. Yesterday, I tried Moerni 78 snacks, namely salted yammie, iced tea and mixed ice.

review_text: first time visiting Pasar Prawirotaman. I found out about the rooftop from Instagram reels. u need to go down to the basement and take the lift there to the rooftop. went there on Thursday night around 7 pm and almost all of the tenants are getting ready to close. I bought the Mie Jawa and Nasi Goreng Ayam from Soto Bathok & Kopi Santen Kang Wawan (halal certified). also bought some dimsum from the stall next to it. I really recommend the metai shumai! was planning to sit at the top part but too much people smoking so we stayed in the indoor part.

INFO BARU : Manis Dibibir Uda gak buka di rooftop ini guys (Review Baru) Aku kembali lagi. Dan kali ini akhirnya bisa nyobain beberapa : 1. Djajan Moerni 78 -Yamie Manis : tektur mienya enak, rasanya ENAKKK BGT. Dan sepertinya yg pedes boleh deh kapan kucoba wkwk. 8.8/10 2. Kedai Ongfe - Claypot ayam Kungpau : klo mau makan ini, kusaranin jangan dlm kondisi laper bgt. Krn mrk masaknya satu. Jd nunggunya lama bgt. Isinya : nasi, potongan ayam, mete, dan saos yg rasanya manis bgt (bagi aku), gurih, dan pedas dari jahenya. Utk varian ini kurang cocok dilidahku 6.5/10 3. Manis dibibir - Cinnamon Roll : aku pilih yg varian cream cheese. Aku kira Cinnamon rollnya langsung disajikan gitu aja, ternyata....egk donk. Mereka panasin dulu bbrp menit. Jd pas disajikan dlm kondisi hangat. Dan itu lembuttt banget. Cream cheese-nya juga enak. Nagih pokoknya... 8/10 Tempatnya ada di rooftop pasar pawirotaman. Cara masuknya bs lewat parkiran bawah (parkiran tutup jam 21.00). Trs nnt naik lift. Lumayan banyak tempat duduk. Ada yg bisa liat sunset juga. Disana banyak bgt pilihan makanan. Tinggal pilih aja. Kemarin aku beli di TFP. Menu TFP lumayan byk. Tp sayang gak ada gambar menunya.  Nah kmrn kayaknya aku salah pilih (aku yg gak suka telur puyuh, malah dpt 4 butir wkwk). Serius, mending tanya detail menu kalian dulu deh sebelum pesen. Kmrn sempet coba menu temen, yg ada Mac n cheese-nya, itu jauhhh lebih cocok di aku.wkkwwk Jd semua tergantung selera. Soal tempat Uda oke kok. Please jaga kebersihan yaaa gaes, biar tetep nyaman. Krn yg berkunjung bukan cm warga lokal, ada turis juga.
review_translated_text: NEW INFORMATION: Sweet on the Lips Its not open on this rooftop, guys (New Review) Im back again. And this time I can finally try some: 1. Djajan Moerni 78 -Yamie Manis: the texture of the noodles is delicious, the taste is SO DELICIOUS. And it looks like the spicy one is okay sometime Ill try it hahaha. 8.8/10 2. Ongfe Store - Kungpau chicken claypot: if you want to eat this, I suggest you dont be too hungry. Because they cook one. So the wait was really long. It contains: rice, chicken pieces, cashews, and a sauce that tastes really sweet (for me), savory, and spicy from the ginger. This variant doesnt suit my taste 6.5/10 3. Sweet on the lips - Cinnamon Roll: I chose the cream cheese variant. I thought the Cinnamon roll was just served straight away, but apparently... no way. They preheat it for a few minutes. So its perfect to serve warm. And its very soft. The cream cheese is also delicious. Basically... 8/10 The place is on the rooftop of the Pairirotaman market. The way to enter is via the lower parking lot (parking closes at 21.00). Then wait to take the elevator. Quite a lot of seating. There are those who can see the sunset too. There are lots of food choices there. Just choose. Yesterday I bought it at TFP. The TFP menu is quite extensive. But unfortunately there is no picture of the menu. Well now it seems like I made the wrong choice (I dont like quail eggs, but I got 4 of them hahaha). Seriously, its better to ask for details of your menu first before ordering. Yesterday I tried a friends menu, the one with Mac n Cheese, it was much more suitable for me. hahaha So it all depends on taste. As for the place, its okay. Please keep it clean, guys, so you stay comfortable. Because those who visit are not just local residents, there are tourists too.

review_text: Never expected this from a market especially it used to be traditional one. Its accessible, the mobility just great since theres elevator. Been there for recording and what a great of use of space. The spaces are well managed. Food

Lokasinya di pasar Prawirotaman. Disediakan lift untuk naik turun dari basement tempat parkir. Tempatnya nyaman, bersih, dan luas dengan variasi makanan yang banyak. Terdapat cws  yang nyaman untuk nugas. Harga makanannya murah dengan porsi yang sangat mengenyangkan. Dibagian atas vibenya cocok untuk curhat atau merenungi dosa-dosa yang telah diperbuat. Ada toilet dan mushola yang bersih dengan tempat wudhu yang terbuka. Sayangnya jam 9 malam sudah tutup dan satpam mulai menyuruh untuk turun. Parking: Parkirnya di basement untuk motor bayar 2.000 Kid-friendliness: Nyaman untuk anak-anak, tetapi perlu pengawasan takut naik turun tempat yang diatas.
review_translated_text: The location is at Prawirotaman market. An elevator is provided for going up and down from the basement parking area. The place is comfortable, clean and spacious with a large variety of food. There is a comfortable CWS for assignments. The food prices are cheap with very filling portions. At the top, the vibe is suitable for venting or reflecting on the sins you have committed. There are clean toilets and prayer rooms with open ablution areas. Unfortunately at 9 pm it was closing and the security guard started telling you to come down. Parking: Parking in the basement for motorbikes costs 2,000 Kid-friendliness: Comfortable for children, but requires supervision for fear of going up and down the places above.

review_text: Buat nyunset, makan dimsum sambil deeptalk asikk bgt disini. Harganya seperti biasa 12k dapet 4 dimsum, rasanya oke kok lumayan berasa ayamnya. Dari parkiran langsung naik lift aja ke rooftop, kesini aku pas jam 4 masih dapet tempat duduk yang hadap sunsetnya. Setelah itu lumayan rame banyak orang
review_translated_text: To relax, eating dim sum while deep talking is really fun here. The price as usual is 12k for 4 dim sums, the taste is okay, the chicken tastes good. From the parking lot, just take the elevator to the rooftop, I came here at 4 oclock and still got a seat facing the sunset. After that, there were quite a lot of people

review_text: Enak untuk melihat sunset ditengah kota
review_translated_text: Nice to see the sunset in the middle of the city

review_text: Menyenangkan sekali jajan di sini karena ada banyak jenis makanan dan minuman, dari makanan berat sampai makanan ringan tersedia. Makanan khas Jogja, makanan daerah, sampai yang kekinian semua ada. Suasananya cocok untuk makan ramai-ramai bersama teman atau keluarga.
review_translated_text: Its fun to have a snack here because there are many types of food and drinks, from heavy meals to snacks available. Typical Jogja food, regional food, even contemporary food is all there. The atmosphere is suitable for eating together with friends or family.

review_text: The place is okay for hanging out on the rooftop, the chairs are high For food, I ordered mushroom & claypot pasta, it tasted pretty good but its better to just buy plain ice

Tempatnya lumayan, enaknya kalo buat nge date yg diatas. Kalo yg bawah sama keluarga atau temen sabi. Buat makanannya cenderung ke mahal yaa, karena pasti mikirnya kalo ada kata pasar pasti murah, tp ini mahal. Pelayanan nya kurang, karna waktu itu kesana habis hujan, gak ada sama sekali pelayan yg inisiatif buat ngebersihin meja atau kursi yg basah. Untuk viewnya city light. Sangat disarankan kesini kalo sore menjelang malam.
review_translated_text: The place is not bad, its good for going on a date above. If youre downstairs, youre with family or friends. The food tends to be expensive, because I think if the market says it must be cheap, but this is expensive. The service was lacking, because it was raining there at that time, there were no waiters at all who took the initiative to clean the wet tables or chairs. For the city light view. It is highly recommended to come here in the late afternoon.

review_text: Kesini sore menjelang malam suasananya  ramai, food stall nya banyak, saya beli di TFP kopi warung dan Moerni 78, pelayanannya cepat harga worth, Di TFP saya pesan lasagna roll rasanya b aja cendrung over cooked, mozarellanya sampe keras, mashed potato nya enak tapi dingin, saladnya enak, minumannya std karena cuman lychee tea ice, overall masih bisa dimakan. Untuk makanan yg saya beli di Moerni 78 enak semua dan harganya sangat bersahabat. Pas kesini juga ada live musiknya, dan bermacam2 genre musik. Tapi musiknya ngajak tawuran, kenceng bgt jd kurang kl buat ngobrol2 khusus buat makan aja kayanya.
review_translated_text: Came here in the afternoon before evening, the atmosphere was busy, there were lots of food stalls, I bought it at TFP coffee stall and Moerni 78, the service was fast, the price was worth it, At TFP, I ordered a lasagna roll, but it tasted like it tended to be overcooked, the mozzarella was hard, the mashed potato was delicious but cold, the salad was delicious, the drink was standard because it was just lychee tea ice, overall it was still edible. The food I bought at Moerni 78 was all delicious and the prices were very friendly. Right here there is also live music, and various music genres. But the music encourages brawls, its so loud that its not enough to chat, especially if its just eating.

review_text: Tp yg di atas cepet2an
review_translated_text: But the one above is fast

review_text: Jusnya gak ada manis hambar, kataku bukan tahu cabe garam si ini lebih ke tahu oseng rasanya sedikit pahit dari daun bawangnya aja gosong gak fresh
review_translated_text: The juice is not sweet, bland, I said its not tofu, chili salt, this is more like stir-fried tofu, it tastes a little bitter from the spring onions, its just burnt, its not fresh

review_text: Merusak mood bgt, pelayanannya kureng. Nungguin pesanan ampe sejam, pas ditanya gada rasa bersalahnya. Tolong dong, mahasiswa pilih tempat buat ngerjain tugas biar tambah mood. Jgn merusak mood dengan pelayanan cafe yg kek gini.
review_translated_text: Really ruins the mood, the service is poor. Waited for my order for an hour, when I asked, I didnt feel guilty. Please, students choose a place to do assignments to improve their mood. Dont ruin your mood with this kind of cafe service.

review_text: kesini waktu bukber , harga paket ayam 35k dapet ayam kecil.. terus waktu bukber kan bisa ambil es sendiri gitu ya tapi waktu dateng agak telat karna hujan es nya habis.. tp mba nya mau ko buatin esteh 1 hehe walapun es buahnya ga dapet tp kurang worthit untuk harga 35k dpt 1 ayam kecil + nasi + esteh doang.. kalau habis tp ga di refill jangan di masukin ke menu paket ka hehe
review_translated_text: came here during bukber, the chicken package price was 35k and got a small chicken.. And when its bukber, you can get your own ice, but when you arrive its a bit late because the hail has run out... but sis, I want to make 1 esteh hehe, even though I cant get the fruit ice, its not worth it for the price of 35k, just get 1 small chicken + rice + esteh... if you run out but dont refill it, dont add it to the package menu, bro, hehe

review_text: Its nice to hang out here
review_translated_text: wuapik cah penuk nggon e sek meh do nongkrong ning kene wae

review_text: pelayanan bagus, makanan nya enak
review_translated_text: good service, the food is delicious

review_text: Kapok. Sudah reservasi dan DP. Kirim daftar pesanan per orang, masih nunggu 1.5jam ga datang. Giliran ditanya ternyata makanan habis.
review_translated_text: Give up. Already made a reservation and down payment. Send a list of orders per person, still waiting 1.5 hours but it doesnt come. It was his turn to be asked and it turned out the food had run out.

review_text: Kacau balau amburadul pelayanannya
review_translated_text: The service is a mess

review_text: Kacau balau pelayanannya
review_translated_text: The service is a mess

review_text: Pelayanan amburadul
review_translated_text: Awful service

review_text: cafe yang memiliki area lumayan luas, ada indoor dan outdoor. untuk ruangan indoor bisa diperhatikan lagi utk kebersihan dan kerapiannya (sedikit bau tidak sedap). area outdoor lumayan nyaman dengan pemandangan sawah. parkiran luas, menu variatif dengan harga terjangkau. ada live musik
review_translated_text: The cafe has a fairly large area, indoor and outdoor. For indoor rooms, you can pay more attention to cleanliness and tidiness (a little unpleasant smell). The outdoor area is quite comfortable with views of the rice fields. Ample parking, varied menu at affordable prices. there is live music

review_text: Bukber di Nilu kopi menu paket ramadhan enak banget, ayamnya empuk. Suasana vibes ramadhan banget. ngabuburit disini ngga ngebosenin dehh + bisa refil minum sepuasnyaaa recomend bgt dehhhh
review_translated_text: The Bukber at Nilu Kopi, the Ramadhan package menu, is really delicious, the chicken is tender. The atmosphere has really Ramadan vibes. Hanging out here isnt boring + you can drink as much as you like, highly recommended

review_text: Kali ini boleh kecewa ngga sih? Menu berbuka, 35rb per paket, ayam se kecil dan se alot ini .. free esteh, tp pas minta tawar, ternyata kena charge lagi .. jujur bawa keluarga disini, ngga rekomend sama sekali. My parents are really angry because its expensive but not worth it, Im so sorry Its better for those who still want to break their fast here, dont take the breaking fast package, its better to just go ala carte, be sure... in the picture its really big, it turns out that its right in the middle of the zonk, tofu with salt chilli, okay, wingsblackpapper okay, the spaghetti carbonara is no longer as delicious as before, Sorry Service, when I asked the older brother who was delivering the menu, what kind of menu was this, the answer was that he didnt know... maybe it could be coordinated between the person who brought out the food and the person who wanted to deliver it, so if you asked, you wouldnt be confused.

Dan makanan datang tdk langsung sesuai pesanan. Tapi satu per satu. Cukup sekali ini saja kesini. Banyak yg kasih ulasan LAMA dalam penyajian, harusnya ini sebagai masukan management. Ini sudah jam 18.40, menu utama belum datang sama sekali. Sampai minuman sudah habis pun belum datang. Kapok. Baru kali ini saya kasih rating 1.
review_translated_text: I made a reservation, paid in full, arrived at 17.00 to break the fast, until sunset no food/drink had arrived. I asked, he said it had just been prepared, the drinks arrived almost at 18.30. And the food didnt come immediately according to the order. But one by one. Just this once is enough here. Many people give LONG reviews on presentation, this should be management input. Its already 18.40, the main menu hasnt arrived at all. Until the drinks were finished they still hadnt arrived. Kapok. This is the first time I give a rating of 1.

Even though the prices are student prices, the taste of the food suits your taste buds. It could be a recommendation for hanging out, doing homework, relaxing and various other events

review_text: Tumeric Coffee nya enak, dapetin sensasi segar kunyit asam sama kopi dingin, seger, nikmat. The place is nice, far from the noise and you get the feel of Javanese Jogja, especially if when you get there there are people dancing, its a priceless moment. The bathroom is lacking, it is not clean and tidy. If you go to the bathroom while eating, you can reduce your appetite. Please pay attention again, unfortunately the atmosphere and taste are ok.

review_text: Ngopi di Cafe Penari. Itulah judul yg paling pas. Paling enak datang ke sini sore menjelang maghrib, trs nongkrong sampai maleman. Seru. Banyak yg lg latihan nari. Berasa disambut dan disajikan tarian sambutan gitu. Mana yg nari keren2. Untuk menu, so-so lah, nggak ada yg bener2 khas. Enak-enak juga kok, meski pelayananannya agak lama. Saran, mushollanya dibersihin, dikasih pewangi, sama lampunya diterangin yah.
review_translated_text: Drinking coffee at Penari Cafe. Thats the most fitting title. Its best to come here in the afternoon before sunset, then hang out until evening. Exciting. Many people are practicing dancing. It felt like being welcomed and being given a welcoming dance like that. Which one dances cool? As for the menu, its so-so, theres nothing really special. Its delicious too, even though the service is a bit slow. Suggestion, clean the prayer room, add perfume, and illuminate the lamp.

place_name: de Ngokow Coffee Roastery & Tea Club Jogja
review_text: Sejujurnya kesini karena lihat review kok kayaknya menarik dan bagus. Awal dateng memang terasa menarik karena ini bangunannya di ndalem. Pas dateng sore masih rame anak anak nari di pendopo. Tapi suasana jadi beda pas udah masuk magrib. Mau shalat, tempat wudhu ga ada dan akhirnya wudhu di toilet yang agak uji nyali ya bund wkwkwk Musholanya agak mengingatkan saya dgn film film horor. Banyak bocor juga jadi lantainya basah dimana mana. Suasana mencekam dan jadi ga nyaman makin malem. Agak curiga sama review google wkwkwkwk
response_from_owner_text: Hi Kak, terima kasih atas reviewnya. Bangunan kami memang merupakan cagar budaya yang merupakan bangunan asli dari Rumah Sultan Hamengkubuwono 8 dan tidak boleh di renovasi secara keseluruhan untuk mempertahankan keaslian bangunan. Dan alhamdulillah review kami selama ini murni secara organik tanpa terlibat pembelian review atau sejenisnya. Jika anda meragukan review kami yang anda ragukan, silahkan kirimkan bukti jika ada review kami yang palsu atau hasil pembelian review. Mungkin market kami memang bukan anda yang tidak sesuai dengan target market kami atau anda mungkin dari pesaing kami. Dan terima kasih atas ulasan anda yang tidak sesuai dengan konsep gerai dan mohon maaf jika memang ada ketidaknyamanan sebelumnya.
review_translated_text: Honestly, I came here because I saw the reviews and it seemed interesting and good. When you first arrived, it felt interesting because this is the building in Ndalem. When we arrived in the afternoon, there were still lots of children dancing in the pavilion. But the atmosphere became different when it was sunset. I wanted to pray, there wasnt a place for ablution and I ended up doing ablution in the toilet, which was a bit of a test of courage, bro hahaha The prayer room reminds me a bit of a horror film. There were lots of leaks too so the floor was wet everywhere. The atmosphere was tense and became uncomfortable as the night went on. A bit suspicious of Google reviews hahaha
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hi Sis, thank you for the review. Our building is indeed a cultural heritage which is the original building of the Sultan Hamengkubuwono 8 House and cannot be completely renovated to maintain the authenticity of the building. And thank God, our reviews so far have been purely organic without any involvement in purchasing reviews or anything like that. If you have doubts about our review, please send us proof if any of our reviews are fake or the results of purchasing reviews. Maybe our market is not you, it doesnt match our target market or you might be our competitor. And thank you for your review which does not match the concept of the outlet and apologize if there was any inconvenience previously.

Wedang Uwuh, Jeruk Jahe Kencur, Jahe Kencur, Wedang Tape dll. Pokoknya tempatnya cozy banget. Direkomendasikan
review_translated_text: Eating Bakmi Jowo at Bakmi Djowo Pendopo is really different, really. Try Bakmi Godog (boiled), Bakmi Goreng and Capcay, the taste is top class. The place is hidden in an alley on Jl. Panembahan Mangkurat, but inside is spacious enough to hang out with guests, relatives or friends/relatives. The drinks also have a variety of very traditional flavors. Wedang Uwuh, Orange Ginger Kencur, Ginger Kencur, Wedang Tape etc. Anyway, the place is really cozy. Recommended

review_text: TLDR; Good for chat and work, though the AC needs to be fixed since its so hot inside. Review Homwok Coffee Tamansiswa Tempat 4/5 Homwok Coffee Tamansiswa terletak di pinggir jalan Tamansiswa, sehingga mudah untuk dicapai. Tempat parkir tidak terlalu luas, jika ingin menggunakan mobil bisa parkir di bahu jalan samping-sampingnya. Tempat duduk dibagi menjadi dua bagian. Satu indoor ber-AC dan satu lagi semi-indoor non-AC diluar. Tempat duduk didalam tidak terlalu banyak, dan cukup sempit karena banyak kardus-kardus di sisi ruangan. Ruangan indoor enurut saya posisi duduknya kurang enak digunakan untuk bekerja, karena mejanya kurang tinggi, jadi lebih cocok untuk mengobrol. Tapi yang sangat parahnya adalah AC disini hampir/sama sekali tidak berfungsi, rasanya seperti di oven di dalam. Sampai salah satu pegawainya menunggu diluar karena saking panasnya, saya juga harus pindah ke kafe es krim sebelah karena tidak memungkinkan bekerja disitu. Untuk ruangan outdoornya cocok digunakan untuk bekerja, tapi lebih enak saat sore-malam hari setelah matahari tidak menyengat, diluar juga ada resiko kebisingan dari lalu lintas kendaraan, karena sangat dekat dengan jalan raya. Menu 5/5 Harga menu minuman disini berjarak 15-27k dengan rata-rata harga kopi susu di harga 24k, bisa upsize dengan tambahan harga 5k. Ada juga promo Minuman + Snack 25k untuk jam 09-14. Harga yang cukup oke bagi saya untuk kafe dengan standar ini. Saya pesan Homwok Original seharga 17k, dan promo Hazelnut + French Fries Barbeque seharga 25k. Untuk Homwok Original menurut saya enak, dengan harga ini sudah bisa dapat komposisi yang past antara kopi, susu, dan SKM. Sedangkan untuk Hazelnut dan French Fries menurut saya standar, worth it untuk membeli saat promo. Pelayanan 5/5 Barista ramah, dan bisa menjelaskan menu dengan baik. Kamar mandi 5/5 Terang, bersih, dan tidak bau.
review_translated_text: TLDR; Good for chat and work, although the AC needs to be fixed since its so hot inside. Review of Homwok Coffee Tamansiswa Place 4/5 Homwok Coffee Tamansiswa is located on the side of Jalan Tamansiswa, so it is easy to reach. The parking area is not too large, if you want to use a car you can park on the side of the road. The seating is divided into two parts. One indoor with air conditioning and the other semi-indoor non-AC outside. There arent many seats inside, and its quite narrow because there are lots of boxes on the sides of the room. In my opinion, the indoor room has a less comfortable sitting position for working, because the table is not high enough, so it is more suitable for chatting. But whats really bad is that the AC here is almost/not working at all, it feels like its in an oven inside. Until one of the employees waited outside because it was so hot, I also had to move to the ice cream cafe next door because it wasnt possible to work there. The outdoor space is suitable for working, but it is better in the afternoon and evening after the sun is not as hot, outside there is also a risk of noise from vehicle traffic, because it is very close to the main road. Menu 5/5 The price of the drink menu here is between 15-27k with the average price of coffee with milk at 24k, can be upsized for an additional 5k. There is also a 25k Drink + Snack promo for 09-14. Prices are quite okay for me for a cafe of this standard. I ordered Homwok Original for 17k, and the Hazelnut + French Fries Barbeque promo for 25k. In my opinion, Homwok Original is delicious, at this price you can get the exact composition of coffee, milk and SKM. Meanwhile, in my opinion, Hazelnut and French Fries are standard, worth buying during the promo. Service 5/5 The barista is friendly and can explain the menu well. Bathroom 5/5 Bright, clean and odorless.

review_text: Terletak di sebuah sudut yang bersejarah dekat Alun-Alun Selatan dan Pojok Beteng Wetan, tersembunyi permata kecil yang memanjakan penikmat kopi. Tempat ini, meski mungil, menawarkan sebuah oase kecil yang sejuk dan nyaman, cocok untuk melepas penat atau sekadar menikmati hari. Segelas americano dingin yang mereka sajikan bukan sekedar hitam dan pahit, melainkan sebuah simfoni yang membangkitkan semangat dengan setiap tegukan. Menemani percakapan tanpa akhir para kawan kawan lamaku. Tak kalah menggugah selera, pisang goreng yang disajikan lembut di dalam, menciptakan harmoni rasa yang sempurna saat disantap bersama kopi. Meskipun tempat ini menawarkan pengalaman yang istimewa, para pengunjung harus memperhatikan bahwa area parkir cukup terbatas. Sebuah tantangan kecil yang patut dipertimbangkan bagi mereka yang mengendarai kendaraan besar. Namun, bagi pejalan kaki atau pengguna kendaraan kecil, lokasi ini adalah pilihan yang tepat untuk menghabiskan waktu santai di akhir pekan atau setelah hari kerja yang panjang. Singkatnya, jika kita mencari tempat yang menawarkan kedamaian di tengah kota dengan sajian yang memanjakan lidah, tempat ini layak menjadi pilihan.
review_translated_text: Located in a historic corner near Alun-Alun Selatan and Pojok Beteng Wetan, there is a hidden little gem that will delight coffee lovers. This place, although small, offers a cool and comfortable little oasis, perfect for unwinding or just enjoying the day. The glass of cold americano they serve is not just black and bitter, but a symphony that lifts the spirits with every sip. Accompanying the endless conversations of my old friends. No less appetizing, the fried bananas served are soft on the inside, creating a perfect harmony of taste when eaten with coffee. Although this place offers a special experience, visitors should note that the parking area is quite limited. A small challenge worth considering for those driving large vehicles. However, for pedestrians or small vehicle users, this location is the right choice to spend relaxing time on the weekend or after a long work day. In short, if we are looking for a place that offers peace in the middle of the city with dishes that pamper the taste buds, this place is worthy of being the choice.

review_text: Ambiencenya oke yah, cozy juga. Ada indoor dan outdoornya. Yang indoor dia ber-AC. Di sini juga ada WiFi jadi enak kalo misal mau sambil nugas, dan lumayan kenceng. Untuk harga, emang ga yang murah banget tapi juga ga mahal banget, yaa masih standar coffeeshop pada umumnya lah..20k an. Meja juga langsung gercep dibersihkan dengan cairan pembersih begitu pelanggan sudah selesai dan pulang sehingga kebersihan terjaga. Kamar mandinya pun bersih dan estetik, bahkan disediakan buku juga di toilet haha. Wastafel juga bersih banget dan disediakan sabun cuci tangan juga tisu. Tidak ada bayar parkir! Ini ni saya suka hehe. Ohiya tapi untuk parkir mobil memang agak sulit sih.
review_translated_text: The ambience is okay, cozy too. There are indoor and outdoor. The indoor one is air-conditioned. There is also WiFi here, so its good if you want to do work, for example, and its pretty fast. Service is very friendly and enthusiastic. The food and drinks are also delicious, I just tried the iced americano and onion rings. As for the price, its not really cheap but its not really expensive either, its still the standard for coffeeshops in general... 20k or so. Tables are also quickly cleaned with cleaning fluid once the customer has finished and gone home so that cleanliness is maintained. The bathroom is clean and aesthetic, there are even books provided in the toilet haha. The sink is also very clean and hand washing soap and tissues are provided. No pay for parking! I like this hehe. Oh yes, but parking the car is a bit difficult.

Meskipun nggak begitu luas, tapi cocok buat berlama-lama memgerjakan tugas atau sekadar nongkrong bersama bestie. Desain bangunannya unik banget dan adem di mata. Menu makanan dan minumnya juga beragam, dengan harga yang nggak terlalu mahal untuk ukuran kafe.

The building design is very unique and cool to the eye. The food and drink menu is also varied, with prices that are not too expensive for a cafe.

review_text: Such a nice place and a nice owner

The meals are simple and delicious, and the interior decoration is also cute. You can feel the owners personal ingenuity  I got sunburned when I was in Yogyakarta, and it was not easy to find aloe vera in the local store. After asking the owner, he cut several pieces from the garden directly for me. My friends and I    we felt well taken care of, these kind and warm locals are one of the lovely memories in Yogyakarta

Great local breakfast!! The boss was very friendly and efficient and I was able to get everything I was looking for at a more than fair price! You can find both savory and sweet options: pressed fruit juices, spiced teas (local drink in Yogyakarta), excellent +++ fruit-filled pancakes, fruit-yogurt-granola bowls, as well as savory dishes from same kind as those found almost everywhere: nasi goreng, noodles etc. Each item costs around 25,000 rp, so with a hearty breakfast you can easily get by for 100,000 rp As a bonus, the room where we eat is rather pretty: wooded, surrounded by a garden imitating a small jungle and in a small street therefore quite quiet, and filled with paintings that the owner paints himself, which is everything also in the atmosphere of Yogyakarta, the  artist city of Indonesia
review_translated_text: Super petit-dejeuner local !! Le patron etait tres sympa et efficace et jai pu avoir tout ce que je cherchais a un prix plus que correct ! Vous pourrez trouver du sale comme du sucre : des jus de fruits presses, des thes aux epices (boisson locale a Yogyakarta), des crepes fourrees aux fruits excellentes +++, des bowls fruit-yaourt-granola, ainsi que des plats sales du meme genre que ceux quon trouve un peu partout : nasi goreng, nouilles etc. Chaque article coute environ 25000 rp, ce qui fait quavec un copieux petit dejeuner on peut sen sortir facilement pour 100000 rp En prime, la salle ou lon mange est plutot jolie : boisee, entouree dun jardin imitant une petite jungle et dans une petite rue donc assez calme, et remplie de tableaux que le patron peint lui-meme, ce qui est tout a fait dans lambiance de Yogyakarta egalement, la ville dartistes dIndonesie

review_text: Very nice location, fair prices, good service

review_translated_text: The first time I tried hanging out here 1 year ago, the atmosphere was really nice, suitable for working, not noisy, calming (I felt like I wanted to stay 24 hours ), the wifi was fast, the prices were cheap, especially the bathroom smelled good Overall the food is delicious especially the fries!! In the past, I bought a kind of rice bowl matah and someone was not happy with it and then tried to complain on IG, apparently the admin was responsive. The drink is delicious, I always order arenga/hazelnut caramel ! What I can suggest = if every order maybe you can note down the name/give a number, guys sometimes dont like to reconize the ones who bought it, its a shame when youre waiting for an order. Overall good job!

review_text: Tempatnya menarik untuk dikunjungi tapi kendalanya di parkir. Kalau lagi rame, parkir motor aja susah banget. Parkir mobil lebih susah lagi. Pas belokan jadi kadang kelewatan. Tapi ga sulit dicari. Tempatnya agak remang enak buat ngobrol santai. Kemarin ke sana wifi nya kurang stabil, atau titik duduknya ga pas jdi wifinya ga nyampe? Kita duduk persis di depan kasir. Krna malam waktu itu banyak yg ud kosong. Harga terjangkau. Pelayanan kurang oke waktu itu jdi mau tanya banyak menu agak ga nyaman. Pembayaran bisa qris.
review_translated_text: The place is interesting to visit but the problem is parking. If its busy, parking a motorbike is really difficult. Parking the car is even more difficult. When I turn, I sometimes miss it. But its not hard to find. The place is a bit dim, good for chatting casually. Yesterday when I went there, the WiFi wasnt stable, or was the seating position not right so the WiFi didnt reach? We sat right in front of the cashier. Because at night, many of them were empty. Affordable prices. The service was not good at that time so wanting to ask a lot about the menu was a bit uncomfortable. Payment can be made qris.

review_text: Sejauh ini, ini kopi TERENAK di Jogja

review_text: Sebenernya suasananya enak, tapi sekarang sering banget ada pengunjung ramean yang berisik, kedengeran dari belakang sampe depan
