review_text: Tempatnya sangan nyaman untuk bekerja maupun untuk hanya sekedar nongkrong menikmati segelas kopi. Untuk  rame-rame cocok untuk yang suka nongkrong sendirian juga sangat bisa. Disedikan card game juga. Poin plusnya kamar mandi bersih mushola juga cukup nyaman meskipun tempat wudhunya hanya ada satu dan kurang tertutup. Minuman kopinya cukup memuaskan, recomended salted caramel nya, karena manis dan gurihnya pas. Selain itu chamomile teanya juga recomended karena bisa Reffil air hangatnya. Makanan recomendednya ada bubur ketan hitam, yang manisnya gak berlebihan dan santanya kental. Sekarang juga ada eskrim glico wingsnya juga.
review_translated_text: The place is very comfortable for working or just hanging out enjoying a cup of coffee. For groups, its also very suitable for those who like to hang out alone. Card games are also provided. The plus point is that the bathroom is clean, the prayer room is also quite comfortable even though there is only one ablution area and it is not closed enough. The coffee drink is quite satisfying, recommended salted caramel, because its just the right amount of sweet and savory. Apart from that, chamomile tea is also recommended because it can be filled with warm water. The recommended food is black sticky rice porridge, which is not too sweet and the coconut milk is thick. Now there is also Glico Wings ice cream too.

review_text: Third time coming in here, spacious lots of table and power sockets. The coffee is quite nice and affordable the snacks too. They have praying room, which is a plus. The only downside is the parking space for car, to my knowledge there arent any. As for motor cycle and bike, plenty of space.

A hidden gem in this area that Ive been a regular at for two years. One of the best coworking space around, with variety of drinks and foods plus internet speed that has reasonable prices. I really love this place, but just remembered to review now. Theres this one day JAKA pass of 35k of chosen food and beverage, that i usually bought. My personal favorite is rosella lychee tea and omega egg/chicken rice bowl or potato wedges (french fries). For the prices, size and taste, its totally worth it. (update: strawberry milk pudding is also my favorite now) The waitress/barista are friendly and accomodating. When it rains, they took our helmet inside so it wouldnt be wet. There are various table group that you can choose, my personal favorite is the one nearby the window. They also offers some table with work lamps. Theres also a private room that you can use for meetings. Plus note: they have smoking room too. THE TOILET ARE CLEAN AND SMELLS GOOD. Keep it up. I love clean toilet.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih banyak dukungannya selama ini kak Sisilia. Sungguh sangat berarti untuk kami.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you very much for your support all this time Sis Sicily. It really means a lot to us.

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of experiencing this coffee shop. The space itself is impeccably clean, with a spacious and naturally lit environment that inspires productivity. The ambiance is elevated by soothing jazz music, creating a relaxed atmosphere perfect for tackling tasks on your laptop. With decent wifi and comfortable air conditioning, its an ideal spot for remote work. One standout aspect was the accommodating staff who graciously fulfilled my request for an affogato, despite it not being on the menu. While the espresso leaned towards the Americano side, it still delivered a satisfying coffee experience. However, for those with discerning taste buds, I must note that while the environment excels, the coffee and pastry offerings may not match up to the standards set by Opera Pastry Cafe less than one block away. Minister of Coffee seems to be recently opened so maybe they ll need more time to identify customer s preference and perfect their beverages. If youre seeking a serene and productive workspace with decent coffee options and a welcoming atmosphere, this coffee shop certainly delivers. Yet, for those prioritizing top-tier coffee and pastry selections, Opera Pastry might still be the preferred choice.

I havent stayed here but I saw everything clean and well-kept. Nice and modern environment. Staff helpful and very kind. Javanese massages are by appointment (serious!) and very nice! Thanks again! Nearby activities: There are shops, restaurants, warung, bakery, ice cream shop etc all within walking distance Noteworthy details: Massages to consider for those who want to break away for a moment! Everything clean and tidy, relaxing music.

We both ordered the only thing left, shakshouka, and waited nearly an hour for just one to arrive, despite being the only people dining in the restaurant. The staff advised us that the other one was still cooking, which was confusing as we ordered the same dish. The second portion came well after I had already finished the first one, which my boyfriend sat and watched me eat. Worse, when his came, the egg in it was still raw. It took another 15 minutes for them to recook it. The coffee and atmosphere is decent, but we would never come back due to the extremely slow service.

review_text: My credentials as a food critic are simply decades of eating at every level of restaurants in Los Angeles.  Everything from $1 chili dogs to $60 steaks. This is not to compare with them but to give my honest opinion of the offerings at Opera. In the past week we have eaten at Opera three times.  Twice for dinner, once breakfast. Each meal will get a brief critique and rating, 10 being food heaven, 1...forget about it. Big Breakfast Described on the menu served with an omelette.  Instead the eggs, dead center on the plate, came undercooked sunnyside up, soaking the surrounding item with mucus like egg whites.  Later I saw a photo of the meal showing sunnyside eggs, not an omelette.  The accompanying sausage were two small, taste lacking, hot dogs.  The potatoes and salad were good. Score...2 Eggs  Florentine Very nice dish.  The eggs were perfectly boiled, resting on toast with a very good avocado spread, similar to guacamole. Score...8 Meltique Ribeye Teriyaki I have absolutely no idea what the meat is on this dish.  It looked nothing similar to the great photo they have posted.  It seemed to be some form of beef that had been pulverized and reconstructed.  It did not have a steak like texture and looked like reformed Spam.  I ordered it with spaghetti as a choice  was offered, rice being the other option.  It got delivered with rice.  I sent it back for correction.  The spaghetti in a mushroom sauce is unremarkable. Score...1 My wife had the barumundi fish entree twice.  Each time the meal was different. We also ordered the fried mushrooms, both times different in quantity and taste. These inconsistencies can result in the downfall of any business. My friends sandwhich order never got noted.  He had to reorder after everyone else was served. Opera offers a wonderful selection of delicious pastries.  This is their forte.  The cheese cake is excellent, when fresh. Cinnamon rolls delicious, just to note a couple. Update on pastry. It is stored in open air displays.  The heat and humidity will destroy them rapidly. My friends cheese cake was awful. Old, dried out. Ambiance is okay.  All meals were eaten in the front AC room.  We prereserved  a table for five, as they do not have much seating in this area.  Our table was waiting upon arrival with a personalized reserved sign on it.  Nice touch! Service is you all too commonly found Indonesian method.  Take the order, deliver the order.  Only return when hailed.  Otherwise, youre on your own. Recommendations Deliver meals that resemble the photos. Wait staff be attentive. Stop serving that steak I ordered. Serve all meals warm at the same time.  Ours came one about every five to ten minutes. Overall score...7 Out of the five in our group, three enjoyed their entrees.  Two vowed not to return for food but would for pastries/coffee.  All agreed that for the price there are better offerings at other restaurants. As mentioned this is only MY opinion.  No two experience anything alike.  I recommend trying Opera, most likely you will enjoy it. Update!  In response to your response. No one asked how I want the eggs. The Meltique Ribeye looked absolutely nothing like the photo on your site and when I showed it to the waitress asking for that meal was assured I was ordering that meal, not what I got...If that is waygu, I was not at all impressed. My wifes barumundi meal one night was encircled with mixed vegetables, last night it was totally different. These substitutions are a serious problem for a restaurant.  I can guarantee most patrons want what they see, that is why they order specific items.  Perhaps it was a mistake for us to have looked at the photos posted on your website before we came, after all, they were what stimulated us to come. Sorry, but highly doubt after three visits within one week that we will return for a meal.  We will return for pastries and coffee, but will not take the risk of having problems that seem to be ongoing. Thank you for your reply.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Ron, thank you for the constructive criticism. We embrace them with a target for improvement. Let us address one by one. Big breakfast: Our server is supposed to ask how the eggs are to be made. We have choices of sunny side, scrambled and omelette. Same goes with the potatoes. We have choices of hashbrown, wedges or fries. As for the total of 2 sausages instead of four we will look at the cctv to be sure what happened to the two missing sausages. Meltique rib eye: Meltique is another form of Wagyu. The meat is marbled therefore its more packed structurally if compared to US beef. Meltique is less fibrous compared to US beef by texture and tends to be more tender, although good US beef when cooked properly may achieve comparable tenderness. One thing we can assure you is that it wasnt Spam that you ate. Noted about the spaghetti. We are looking into it. Also well noted on the barramundi and crispy mushroom. The latter is weighed equally for every portion we serve. Again, we will look at the cctv to see if theres any inconsistencies during the cooking process. About the staff, they will be properly retrained. We know their weakness is in English language and from there they develop insecurity and lack of self confidence, which sometimes lead to misunderstanding with some customers. Do come by again. We will sort you out with a big breakfast on our account. And if you have the time to chit chat we can share with you our findings about the barramundi and mushroom. Again, our apologies for the unsatisfactory performance. We appreciate your constructive criticisms though as these things will push us forward to be a better cafe. See you soon. Warm regards Opera Pastry Cafe Team

Yang direkomendasikan oleh pramusajinya, Opera pastry, yang merupakan signature tempat ini, dan Cromboloni Double Chocolate, yang katanya sedang  viral,  dua-duanya tidak mengecewakan. Kopinya pun decent; saya pesan Iced Americano. Hanya saja, karena saya datang untuk nugas dan buka laptop, menurut saya tempatnya kurang cocok untuk duduk berlama-lama. Saya duduk di bagian dalam, dan cukup gerah.
response_from_owner_text: Halo Kakak, thank you for coming. Maaf ya memang AC kita lagi process claim garansi . Harusnya dalam waktu yg dekat sudah bisa terima unit baru. Sekali lagi thank you for your support. See you again soon. This time with a cooler aircon

Recommended by the waiter, Opera pastry, which is the places signature, and Cromboloni Double Chocolate, which he said was going viral, both did not disappoint. The coffee is decent too; I ordered an Iced Americano. Its just that, because I came to do an assignment and open my laptop, I dont think the place is suitable for sitting for a long time. I sat inside, and it was quite hot.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Brother, thank you for coming. Sorry, our AC is in the process of claiming a warranty. We should be able to receive new units in the near future. Once again thank you for your support. See you again soon. This time with a cooler aircon

review_text: Awalnya ke sini mau nyobain carrot cake nya, soalnya nemu dari menu di maps ada carrot cake kan, tapi pas ke sini ternyata lagi ga ready. Akhirnya pesen salted caramel cheesecake, berry white chocolate danish dan iced americano. Pertama makan si berry white chocolate danish dan ternyata enak banget! Teksturnya lembut dan ringan di mulut, menurutku pas di makan rasa dari si blueberry nya lebih dominan dan berasa kek ga ada cokelatnya tapi ini beneran enak, ga terlalu manis dan masih ada rasa segar dari si blueberry. Lanjut nyobain salted caramel cheesecake, sebenernya enak salted caramelnya, cuma aku pribadi keknya ga terlalu cocok sama cheesecake nya (menurutku terlalu berat), jadi tadi cuma nyicipin separuh dan ngabisin si salted caramelnya aja, tapi overall enak kok. Minumnya si iced americano enak, lebih enak ga pake gula (bisa req gulanya dipisah) dan cocok sama makanan manis di sini. Oh iya tempat duduknya banyak, ada indoor dan outdoor. Staffnya ramah-ramah. Toiletnya dipisah cowok dan cewek, dan juga bersih.
review_translated_text: Initially I came here to try the carrot cake, because I found on the menu on maps that there was carrot cake, but when I came here it turned out it wasnt ready. Finally ordered salted caramel cheesecake, berry white chocolate danish and iced americano. First, I ate the berry white chocolate danish and it turned out to be really delicious! The texture is soft and light in the mouth, I think when you eat it the taste of the blueberry is more dominant and it tastes like it doesnt have any chocolate but this is really delicious, not too sweet and there is still a fresh taste of the blueberry. Next, try the salted caramel cheesecake, the salted caramel is actually delicious, but personally I dont think the cheesecake is too good for it (I think its too heavy), so I only tried half and finished the salted caramel, but overall it was delicious. Drinking the iced americano is delicious, its better without using sugar (you can order the sugar separately) and it goes well with the sweet food here. Oh yes, there are lots of seats, indoor and outdoor. The staff are friendly. The toilets are separated for men and women, and are also clean.

Makanan sama minumannya ENAK BANGET. Pastrynya flaky dan rasanya mahal. Kopinya enak, creamnya enak. Cuma kecewa berat sama tempatnya. Aku dateng ke sini berharapan bisa jadi tempat nugas seharian. Tapi cafe indoornya panas banget. Sebagai orang yang gerahan aku ga tahan banget sama panasnya, jadi berasa pengen buru-buru keluar. Padahal kalo tempatnya nyaman kan kita bisa beli banyak dan sering-sering ke sini. AC-nya cuma satu dan itu juga gaada hawa dinginnya sama sekali. Padahal Jogja lagi panas-panasnya. TLDR, saya saranin ke sini take away aja, soalnya emang pastrynya seenak itu. Maybe the best I had in Jogja.
review_translated_text: The food and drinks are VERY DELICIOUS. The pastry is flaky and tastes expensive. The coffee is delicious, the cream is delicious. Just really disappointed with the place. I came here hoping it could be a place to work all day. But the indoor cafe is really hot. As a hot person, I really cant stand the heat, so I felt like rushing out. In fact, if the place is comfortable, we can buy a lot and come here often. Theres only one AC and theres no cold air at all. Even though Jogja is really hot. TLDR, I suggest you just come here to take away, because the pastry is really that delicious. Maybe the best I had in Jogja.

The live music need improvement and often late. They also mostly singing a local songs in Bahasa or Javanese so if you didnt try to learn those language or culture, then you might wont enjoy here.

The staff is very good, sat set, friendly and agile, 10 points! Food and drinks are worth the price. The portions are large, delicious too. Tomorrow I want to try another menu...

The only good thing is the mother who sells it, shes very friendly but she calculates the price of the food very quickly, I dont know if shes calculating correctly or not.

Trus ambil menu sendiri dong, kayak prasmanan tp lauk standar masakan jawa (sayur lodeh, oseng2 tempe, sayur bening, sayur jantung pisang, baceman, mie goreng)..lalu bergeser k kasir n pesan minum. Pas tanya totalnya agak kaget, perasaan masing2 cmn ambil satu sayur, lauk, & bbrp sate tusukan habisnya 60rban. Lhaa ini gak kayak angkringan jadinya   . Mmmmm .. pokoknya harga gak Jogja banget. Pelayanan ibunya ramah, baik.
review_translated_text: I really remember before the pandemic, it was so busy here that it was hard to even find a seat, even the ones on the mezzanine were full and the prices were affordable... but that was before... The story goes that I wanted to feel nostalgic after not having eaten here for a long time, when I arrived at the location I was a bit surprised that it wasnt quiet like before, but there were only a few tables in use. Then when you choose the menu, its almost the same as DL, only the typical angkringan menu (cat rice) isnt there. Then take your own menu, like a buffet but with standard Javanese side dishes (lodeh vegetables, stir-fried tempeh, clear vegetables, banana flower vegetables, baceman, fried noodles)..then move to the cashier and order a drink. When I asked for the total, I was a bit surprised, I felt like each person taking one vegetable, side dish, & a few skewers of satay would end up costing 60 thousand. Well, this isnt like an angkringan   . Mmmmm .. basically the prices are not really Jogja. Her mothers service is friendly, good.

Whats worse, the hotel isnt really suitable, its ugly, dirty, not well maintained, the toilet is clogged, the hot water doesnt work, the AC isnt cold, the TV is blurry, the door is broken, there isnt a trash can provided, like a dirty warehouse. Everything is serious. No more ordering from OYO. It sucks. Harmful application. The name of the hotel is the Gading Prawirotaman Yogyakarta hotel.

Really nice coffee shop that offers alot of Indonesian beverages even ones that ate Java-specific options like the luwak coffee. I ordered the iced Wedang Uwuh herbal tea which was spicy and slightly sweet. Kind of like a cinnamon tea. So refreshing from the heat. They were out of luwak coffee beans but hope to try soon. Highly recommend grabbing a drink at this place after your tours. They even have a small shop with shampoo, jewelry, oils, teas, and more.

In terms of staff service, efficient and friendly. You can come and try here, friends. Location in/at Taman Sari parking lot. Happy to find. From Malioboro you can ride a motor rickshaw here. Let me know if you want to go to Taman Sari. If you want to go back, there are motor rickshaws waiting at the exit of Taman Sari or in front of the Mosque

review_text: Super hot day, and decided to have some rest in this cafe after TamanSari Keraton visit. Beautiful aesthetic cafe, we tried their Wedang Uwuh, Matcha Latte AND; Banana Nuggets. The price is cheap, and they have a beautiful landscape outdoor. They also provide Mushola! Sumpah lahhh teringat sampai sekarang yaa kesedapan nugget pisang tuuuuu. Unexpected taste. Serius sedappp! And, because i love the taste of wedang uwuh drink tu, i decided to buy A LOT of it in souvenir shop before flying back to Malaysia

-KITA Coffee Taman Sari- Kedai kopi Kita Taman Sari, tentunya berlokasi di kawasan Taman Sari. Spot nongkrong santai dan nyaman setelah berkeliling kawasan wisata Taman Sari. Lokasi mudah dijangkau, jika kalian ke Taman Sari, Anda akan dengan mudah meihatnya. Tersedia ruangan indoor dan outdoor, outdoor utk smooking area. Bisa bayar dengan cash maupun qris. Untuk pilihan menu banyak sekali, tidak hanya varian kopi, ada coklat dan susu juga. Makanan ringan dan berat juga ada. Kebetulan, karena hanya berniat untuk duduk santai melepas penat sekalian ngadem, saya dan teman hanya memesan kopi. Suasana nyaman, bersih dan luas. Cukup untuk menambung sekitar 50 org. Banyak pernak-pernik untuk oleh-oleh, ada tas, topi, dan juga baju. Ada pula toples-toples yang berisi aneka jajanan di susun di rak dengan rapi. Untuk rasa kopi tidak ada yang istimewa, pas sekali dengan rasa dan harganya kisaran 20rb an. Sempatkan diri anda untuk melipir ke kedai kopi Kita ketika mengunjungi Taman Sari. Selmat berlibur.
review_translated_text: -KITA Coffee Taman Sari- Our coffee shop Taman Sari is of course located in the Taman Sari area. Relaxed and comfortable hangout spot after touring the Taman Sari tourist area. The location is easy to reach, if you go to Taman Sari, you will easily see it. Indoor and outdoor rooms are available, outdoor for smoking area. Can pay by cash or qris. There are lots of menu choices, not only coffee variants, there are chocolate and milk too. Light and heavy meals are also available. Coincidentally, because we only intended to sit back and relax and relax and cool down, my friend and I only ordered coffee. Comfortable atmosphere, clean and spacious. Enough to accommodate around 50 people. Lots of knick-knacks for souvenirs, there are bags, hats and also clothes. There are also jars containing various snacks neatly arranged on the shelves. As for the taste of the coffee, theres nothing special, its just right for the taste and the price is around 20 thousand. Take the time to stop by Kita coffee shop when visiting Taman Sari. Have a good holiday.

review_text: Kopi 26 ribu, ternyata ada tax 10% ditotal jadi 28.600 haha Mostly coffee shop harga 22-25 ribu, saya rasa pajak sudah include.. KITA ni agak laen emang.. Pricey dengan rasa yang biasa aja.. Not recommended!
review_translated_text: Coffee was 26 thousand, apparently there was a 10% tax for a total of 28,600 haha Mostly coffee shop prices are 22-25 thousand, I think tax is included... KITA is a bit lazy indeed... Pricey with just an ordinary taste... Not recommended!

review_text: A nice coffee you have to try, what a surprise when we pay visit to Taman Sari and looking for a drink. Good atmosphere and nice people here.

Great aesthetic and comfortable vibe. The dim sum is actually chicken sumai and the accompanying sweet chili was good. Their ice mango tea was refreshing on a hot day. Kid-friendliness: Has board games, books and a baby chair.

review_text: Setelah lelah panas peluh capek muter-muter di wilayah Taman Sari kita beristirahat di tempat ini tempatnya cocok banget buat duduk lepas lelah cari AC di ruangan yang dingin adem sambil nyobain minuman segar ataupun kopi dingin ini mantap banget deh pokoknya sambil di sini bisa sambil kerja juga kalau buka laptop atau mengisi lagi baterai handphone kita yang udah habis setelah buat foto-foto hampir 1 jam lebih di wilayah Taman Sari dan ini bisa ngecas badan kita juga Karena setelah kepanasan muter-muter di Taman Sari foto-foto kiri kanan dan di sini itu tempat buat yang duduk bersantai kalaupun mau salat mau salatnya itu bersih rapi enak areanya juga luas wi-fi-nya juga ada yang lengkap banget lah di sini untuk harga memang ini mungkin agak sedikit mahal Tapi menurut aku sih ini udah worth it banget harga segini di sini juga ada Gelato yang kalau mau nyobain es krim siang-siang enak banget karena ini masih dalam satu area Taman Sari situ jadi Parkirannya masih gabung di sana Jadi kita bisa titip di parkiran dan kita bisa main di sini nunggu sampai hari udah agak adem baru kita jalan lagi ke tempat pemberhentian ataupun tujuan wisata kita selanjutnya sekaligus juga kita bisa mengatur strategi dan langkah ke mana dulu mana yang enggak macet mana yang lebih dekat mana Yang pengen dituju setelah kita habis jadi jalan-jalan di Taman Sari ini
review_translated_text: After being tired, hot, sweaty, tired of going around in the Taman Sari area, we rested in this place, this place is really suitable for sitting and relaxing, looking for air conditioning in a cool, cool room while trying fresh drinks or cold coffee, this is really great, basically, while youre here you can work too. if we open our laptop or refill our cell phone battery which has run out after taking photos for almost 1 hour in the Taman Sari area and this can charge our bodies too because after being hot walking around in Taman Sari the photos are left and right and here they are a place for those who sit and relax, even if they want to pray, its clean, neat, nice, the area is also spacious, the wi-fi is also very complete here. For the price, it might be a bit expensive, but in my opinion, its really worth it at this price. There is also Gelato here, which if you want to try ice cream in the afternoon is really delicious because it is still in the same Taman Sari area, so the parking lot is still connected there. So we can leave it in the parking lot and we can play here, wait until the day is a bit cool, then we walk back to our next stop or tourist destination. At the same time, we can also arrange strategies and steps to go first, which ones are not jammed, which ones are closer, which ones do we want to go to after we have finished walking around Taman Sari?

review_text: editing my review after a year-ish, went here again with a friend &welcomed with a view of a cat roaming around the kitchen area, i love cats but that s not sanitary. also a cockroach flew to our table then scurry away as fast as it could, another sanitary issue. i won t be surprised if i get stomachache after this. the frontline staff needs improvements too regarding their service to us customers, maybe take a rest at home when not in the mood to show up for work &serve people.

The concept of the cafe is good, but the atmosphere really makes me uncomfortable because there are acoustics that are not pleasant to hear and the sound is too loud, its a shame the cafe is nice but sorry to say the vibes are like at the Pantura warkop because of the sound     food and drinks need to be adjusted improve the taste and serving time

Finally, find a cafe with a good ambiance with nice food, drink and affordable. The desk and chair are comfy to work with. If you like a drink with a bitter taste but superb refreshed you should order royal lemon, not too sweet love it! (-) wifi is not stable sometimes

I came here just before entering Taman Sari since its the nearest cafe. I ordered their americano and iced coffee and both tasted just fine. What stands out about this place is their ambiance since its very cozy (and air-conditioned lol).

This cafe is super close to Tamansari. You can take some rest here after walking around Tamansari. There are indoor and outdoor sitting spots. They have a variety of menus, from snacks to meals. I love their cireng They also provide a prayer room, which makes it very convenient for Muslim visitors to visit here.

Located just in front of Taman Sari. There are many stalls and diners around, but this is the most visible and friendly for foreign tourists, I think. Inside is well cooled by AC, and there are power sockets. Staffs are young and clean. I had a sauteed vegetables with rice. They can remove meat. I liked the spice infused sweet drink called Wedang Uwuh. I could use Wise credit card here and total costed 57200rp.

Tempat yang bagus, dekat tempat wisata Tamansari. Mereka memiliki pemandangan yang cukup indah (Tamansari). Mereka juga memiliki beberapa permainan (kartu, uno, monopoli, dll) dan permainan tradisional seperti dakon. Minuman mereka cukup enak, tapi makanannya tidak enak. Capcaynya enak banget. Mie gorengnya rasanya enak. Makan kesini bersama keluarga... anak anak senang di ajak ke sini.
review_translated_text: Good place, near the Tamansari tourist attraction. They have quite beautiful views (Tamansari). They also have several games (card, uno, monopoly, etc.) and traditional games like dakon. Their drinks are pretty good, but the food isnt great. The capcay is really delicious. The fried noodles taste delicious. Eat here with family... children love being invited here.

review_text: Outletnya kecil ada 4-5 meja di dalam dan 1-2 meja diluar yang bisa lihat pemandangan sawah. Tempatnya agak jauh, apalagi dari rumah saya (tapi paling dekat daripada outlet lainnya). Tapi kalau beli pizza selalu kesini, yang murah meriah enak. Adonan rotinya tebal tapi empuk, setelah beberapa jam dimakan masih empuk (bahkan keesokan harinya juga masih enak). Toppingnya bermacam-macam sampai 10-11 pilihan rasa dan tidak pelit alias tumpah-tumpah. Ada Margerita, Spicy Chicken Mushroom, Pepperoni Mushroom, Bratwurst, Meat Lover, Completo, Tuna Onion, Beef Bolognese, Smoked Beef & Corn, Favourite, Super Combo. Kalau kurang tumpah masih ada juga ekstra keju dan sosisnya, bisa juga buat pinggiran pizzanya. Ukurannya ada small, medium, dan large. Untuk harga sudah naik, maklum ya bahan-bahan juga sekarang naik. Harga mulai dari Rp 29.000. Selain pizza, ada menu lain juga seperti lasagna, pasta, french fries, fish ball dan minumannya ada teh, jeruk, lemon tea dan juga special blend. Yang dipoto saya pesan Meat Lover medium yang isinya sosis, kornet, bratwurst, dan daging cincang, cocok untuk anak atau yang tidak suka pedas. Kalau saya pesan Tuna Onion isinya tuna, onion, dan jagung (baru ingat belum diphoto setelah tinggal 1 slice :) Parking: Parkir mobil yang agak sulit, cuma bisa 1 mobil itupun mepet banget.

review_translated_text: The outlet is small, there are 4-5 tables inside and 1-2 tables outside with views of the rice fields. The place is a bit far, especially from my house (but closer than other outlets). But if you buy pizza, always come here, its cheap and delicious. The bread dough is thick but soft, after a few hours of eating it is still soft (even the next day it is still delicious). The toppings vary, up to 10-11 flavor choices and are not stingy or spilled. There are Margerita, Spicy Chicken Mushroom, Pepperoni Mushroom, Bratwurst, Meat Lover, Completo, Tuna Onion, Beef Bolognese, Smoked Beef & Corn, Favorite, Super Combo. If it doesnt spill enough, theres still extra cheese and sausage, you can also use it as a pizza crust. The sizes are small, medium and large. Prices have gone up, understandably, the ingredients have also gone up now. Prices start from IDR 29,000. Apart from pizza, there are other menus such as lasagna, pasta, French fries, fish balls and the drinks include tea, orange, lemon tea and also special blends. In the photo, I ordered the medium Meat Lover which contains sausage, corned beef, bratwurst and minced meat, suitable for children or those who dont like spicy food. If I order Tuna Onion, it contains tuna, onion and corn (I just remembered I hadnt taken a photo after I had 1 slice left :) Parking: Car parking is a bit difficult, you can only get 1 car and its really tight.

review_text: Maaf tapi tempatnya terlihat kurang bersih & kurang nyaman, seperti tidak terawat. Kebersihan kurang terjaga, ada rombongan semut migrasi di salah satu sudut ruang (seharusnya tidak ada seperti ini untuk kelas kafe). Kaca buram seperti tidak pernah dibersihkan. Untuk minuman harga setara kafe pada umumnya (18rb   +-25rban), sayang ukuran gelasnya kecil (mungkin sekitar 250-300ml) dibawah size cup pada umumnya yg kisaran 350ml+. Pelayanan & tempat masih jauh dibawah kafe dgn harga menu segitu. Secara umum kurang rekomended. Berdasar pengalaman saya yg terjebak.. Buat yang ke sini niatnya beli jatinangor, mending takeaway aja. Kalo dine in ya jadi habis banyak karna harga minum hampir sama dgn harga makan
review_translated_text: Sorry but the place doesnt look clean & comfortable, like its not well maintained. Cleanliness was not maintained, there was a group of migrating ants in one corner of the room (there shouldnt be anything like this for a cafe class). The glass is blurry like it has never been cleaned. For drinks, prices are equivalent to cafes in general (18 thousand - +- 25 thousand), unfortunately the glass size is small (maybe around 250-300 ml) below the cup size in general which is around 350 ml+. The service & place are still far below cafes with menu prices like that. In general, it is not recommended. Based on my experience of being trapped... For those who come here with the intention of buying Jatinangor, its better to just takeaway. If you dine in, youll end up running out a lot because the price of a drink is almost the same as the price of a meal

review_text: Pertama di Jogja! Nge-games kekinian&nguliner istimewa. Tempat wisata kuliner yang instagrammable berkonsep foodcourt dengan berbagai wahana bermain yang ramah anak-anak. Khusus untuk outlet kuliner di tempat ini terdiri atas cafe untuk sekedar ngopi dengan varian komplit menu kopi maupun non-kopi,siomay Kang Herman yang komplit&asli ikan tengiri,outlet aneka seblak,dan warung menu berat seperti ayam geprek sambal ijo,dll. No HTM. Semua wahana games di sini gratis,kecuali wahana mancing boneka. Jenis wahana virtual games yang futuristik dibatasi durasinya sekitar 15 menit untuk membudayakan antri pada anak-anak (cukup sih,meski ntar bisa main lagi kalo nggak ada antrian). Keren sih ini Ortu bisa makan dengan tenang&anak-anak bisa main dengan senang. Tersedia area outdoor&semi indoor. Tempat parkir kendaraan cukup memadai. Akses menuju ke lokasi ini mudah&dpt dijangkau oleh motor maupun mobil. Semilir Food&Games Maesan,Krobokan,Tamanan,Banguntapan,Bantul,Yogyakarta
review_translated_text: First in Jogja! Playing contemporary & special games. This instagrammable culinary tourist spot has a food court concept with various children-friendly playgrounds. Especially for culinary outlets, this place consists of a cafe for just drinking coffee with a complete variety of coffee and non-coffee menus, Kang Herman dumplings which are complete & authentic with mackerel fish, various seblak outlets, and stalls with heavy menus such as fried chicken with green chili sauce, etc. HTM No. All the games here are free, except for the doll fishing rides. This type of futuristic virtual games ride is limited in duration to around 15 minutes to get children used to queuing (thats enough, although they can play again later if theres no queue). This is cool Parents can eat in peace & children can play happily. Outdoor & semi indoor areas available. Vehicle parking is adequate. Access to this location is easy and can be reached by motorbike or car. Breezy Food&Games Maesan, Krobokan, Tamanan, Banguntapan, Bantul, Yogyakarta

Located on the side of the road, so the parking area goes inside, the conditions inside are quite clean, continue to improve the quality of service yaaa

place_name: Angkringan Sari Dele Tape pak mo
review_text: Angkringan legendaris sejak 1962   Sekarang sudah dipegang oleh generasi ketiga. Awalnya dijalankan oleh Pak Mo, lalu Pak Jo, dan sekarang oleh Pak Bagus dan Bu Nining. Menu klasiknya ialah minuman sari dele tape. Cita rasa kriminya bikin terngiang-ngiang   Gorengannya juga enak2. Semua gorengan dan nasi dibuat oleh Bu Nining. Saat ini angkringan buka pk. 19.00 dan tutup sekitar pk. 00.30. Tapi bisa jadi lebih cepat jika pengunjung ramai. Tutup hari selasa ya
review_translated_text: Legendary angkringan since 1962   Now it is owned by the third generation. Initially run by Pak Mo, then Pak Jo, and now by Pak Bagus and Bu Nining. The classic menu is the dele tape cider drink. The creamy taste makes you remember   The fritters are also delicious. All the fried food and rice are made by Mrs. Nining. Currently the angkringan is open at 10 p.m. 19.00 and closes around 10 p.m. 00.30. But it could be faster if there are lots of visitors. Closed on Tuesdays OK

review_text: Overall okesih, dari makanan, pelayanan. Mulai dari indonesian food, western   Sedikit notes kemarin; harusnya waiters konfirmasi lagi ke cust kalo memang mineralnya ga ada. Jadi sempet nunggu lumayan lama dan jadi nanya ke waiters. Untungnya masih ada opsi sparkling. Untuk yang suka jalan jalan di malioboro, buat opsi makan siang oke, tempatnya nyaman, dingin. Next time, kalo liburan bakal mampir lagi
review_translated_text: Overall okay, from food, service. Next time, if Im on holiday, Ill stop by again

review_text: My son and Husband are celiac. This was the first place in Indonesia that had someone who could understand enough English to understand that they could not eat anything with wheat in it.  We have come here twice for meals so far and had good food. Dietary restrictions: Celiac

review_translated_text: Location: Located next to Malioboro Mall Interior: Restaurant decorated with interesting paintings Room: Indoor, Semi Outdoor Facilities: Sufficient parking to accommodate motorbikes and cars in sufficient basement tables, WiFi, toilets, plug sockets, prayer room Atmosphere: Busy from opening to closing hours Menu: Various western and Indonesian food menus Service: Friendly, fast Price: Standard restaurant in general Payment: Cash, Qris Taste: Overall the food and drinks here are worth it and a must try For those who have never been here, it is highly recommended to try this place

review_text: Rasa makanan tidak terlalu istimewa. Tapi minumannya saya suka (kami pesan fruit tea party). Pelayannya ramah. Lokasinya yang membuat kami mencoba makan siang di sini. Di tengah marlioboro yang panas terik dan ramai, tempat makan yang tenang jadi harapan kami. Sepertinya kami tidak memilih tempat yang tepat. Di tengah2 kami makan, tiba2 ada manajer (?) yang berteriak2 memarahi anak buahnya.. keras sekali hanya beberapa meter dari kami duduk. Seketika itu juga kenikmatan makan siang kami menguap..
review_translated_text: The taste of the food is not that special. But I like the drinks (we ordered fruit tea party). The waiter is friendly. The location made us try lunch here. In the middle of the sweltering and busy Marlioboro, a quiet place to eat is our hope. Looks like we didnt choose the right place. In the middle of us eating, suddenly there was a manager (?) who shouted and scolded his subordinates... very loudly just a few meters from where we were sitting. Instantly our enjoyment of lunch evaporated...

review_text: I really enjoyed having breakfast at Adams Coffee. I was able to taste one of the specialties, Indonesian-style pancakes with chocolate and more flaky than a classic pancake. I also took a natural, sugar-free guava juice, we only add dates to make it sweeter. The service was very good, smiling and professional. I rented my scooter here for 80k per day.
review_translated_text: Jai beaucoup aime prendre mon petit dejeuner au Adams Coffee. Jai pu gouter une des specialites les pancakes facon indonesiennes au chocolat et plus feuilletes que pancake classique. Jai egalement pris un jus de goyave naturel et sans sucre, on y ajoute seulement des dates pour quil soit plus doux. Le service etait tres bien, souriante et professionnelle. Jai loue mon scooter ici pour 80k par jour.

review_text: Nice place for breakfast and friendly owner. The toilets are not very clean though. The banana pancake was good, though I did not dream of it like some other reviewers, it was also very fatty. The mix fruits platter sadly came wrapped in plastic, so I don t think it is made fresh.
response_from_owner_text: Hallo! Terimakasih atas kunjungan anda serta ulasan baik serta kritik yang anda tulis untuk kami. izin kan kami membalas review anda. pertama, untuk toilet kami akan mengevaluasinya bersama team kami dan kedepannya agar membuatnya toilet tersebut lebih bersih dan nyaman ketika dipakai oleh konsumen. kedua, terkait banana pancake, beberapa dari tamu kita memang ada yang sangat menyukai bahkan ada yang menjadi tamu reguler setiap pagi memesan pancake setiap harinya. namun ada beberapa yang tidak menyukai pancake kami namun itu tidak masalah karena kembali lagi ke selera masing-masing. tapi kami senang bahwa anda mengatakan itu enak, terimakasih banyak. ketiga berbicara tentang fruit platter yang kami wrap dengan plastic wrap. perlu anda ketahui, pagi hari begitu team kami datang, mereka langsung membuat fruit platter pada pagi hari ketika kami buka, dan perlu anda ketahui fruit platter tidak kami siapkan jauh hari sebelumnya. jadi kami menyiapkannya fresh pada hari itu juga, alasan menggunakan plastic wrap supaya lebih higienis. Terimakasih atas kunjungan nya kami sangat menghargai itu!  semoga hari anda baik dan sampai jumpa dilain waktu ya selamat menikmati waktu anda selama di Jogja :)
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello! Thank you for your visit and the good reviews and criticisms you wrote for us. Please allow us to reply to your review. Firstly, for the toilet we will evaluate it with our team and in the future we will make the toilet cleaner and more comfortable when used by consumers. secondly, regarding banana pancakes, some of our guests really like them and some even become regular guests ordering pancakes every morning every day. However, there are some who dont like our pancakes, but that doesnt matter because it comes down to individual taste. but we are happy that you said it was delicious, thank you very much. The third talks about the fruit platter which we wrapped in plastic wrap. You need to know, in the morning when our team arrived, they immediately made the fruit platter in the morning when we opened, and you need to know that we didnt prepare the fruit platter long in advance. So we prepare it fresh on the same day, the reason is using plastic wrap to make it more hygienic. Thank you for visiting, we really appreciate it!  I hope you have a good day and see you next time, enjoy your time in Jogja :)

review_text: Absolutely loved the banana pancake! They are made with croissant dough which is unusual but very delicious. The watermelon juice and mango juice were also great, the orange juice wasnt the best for us. You can also rent a scooter here with the owner.
response_from_owner_text: hallo! kami membuat pancake dengan adonan yang sama dengan croissant namun dengan bentuk yang berbeda lalu kami tambahkan coklat serta topping buah pisang diatasnya. kami senang bahwa anda menyukai nya. untuk jus orange yang anda sebutkan, itu menjadi pertanyaan untuk kami mengapa bukan yang terbaik untuk anda. tetapi kami akan mengevaluasinya agar lebih baik lagi. terimakasih atas review baiknya, semoga kita bisa berjumpa dilain waktu!
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello! we made pancakes with the same dough as croissants but with a different shape then we added chocolate and banana topping on top. we are happy that you like it. For the orange juice you mentioned, its a question for us why its not the best for you. but we will evaluate it to make it even better. Thank you for the good review, hopefully we can meet again next time!

review_text: Delicious coffee, great food, very friendly with a smile.  The people here love a chat and can recommend places and activities to help you to get the most out of Yogyakarta.  We were in town for a week and discovered Adams Coffee on our first day; we came in every morning after that for a delicious breakfast and to plan the day.  Would recommend to anyone from out of town, and anyone who enjoys their coffee. ** Update in response to review from Rivka Jj from mid-Dec 2023, complaining about dirty coffee. This must have been an unlucky one-off, or more likely you got sick from somewhere else. I remember that the owner Mr Agung was a coffee fanatic, always cleaning his machine, adjusting the mix of beans, tweaking the pressure to get the coffee exactly right, and asking customers for feedback.  No chance he would serve bad coffee.

review_text: Very, very slow. Almost 50 minutes for the main breakfast dishes to be brought. The orange juice had too much water. Also, EXCESSIVELY EXPENSIVE. Rp 165,000 for two dishes, two juices (one bad) and two coffees.
response_from_owner_text: Hallo dear Carlos Menanggapi komentar anda tentang : 1. Lambat. 50 menit menunggu. Menurut CCTV yang kami putar ulang anda memesan pada pukul 08.55.35, pesanan kopi keluar pukul 08.58.02, menyusul mango juice dan es jeruk ( no sugar ), jam 09.30.28 nasi goreng spesial dan bakmi goreng ayam telur sudah tersaji di meja anda. Sebagai catatan anda datang ketika cafe sedang ramai pengunjung. Pesanan anda ada diurutan ke 6 2.  Es jeruk ( tanpa gula karena  anda tdk mau ada bahan tambahan)  yang anda bilang mengandung banyak air,  kami ada jeruk murni yg tanpa ada tambahan es yang tentu  saja harganya akan lebih mahal. 3. Harga 165K adalah sangat mahal. Anda pesan dari  list menu dengan harga yang sudah tertera. Pesanan anda : nasi goreng spesial 35 K bakmi goreng ayam telur 25K double espresso 30K Flat white regular milk 25 K Manggo Juice 25 K Es Jeruk 25 K Total 165 K = kurang lebih 10 Euro Kami sudah membebaskan anda dan teman anda  mengambil air putih tanpa membayar dan tidak dibatasi. Untuk memastikan tanggapan dari kami, nota pesanan dan rekaman cctv  masih kami simpan. Bagaimanapun juga kami berterimakasih dengan kunjungan anda dan senang karena hidangan yang Cafe Shop kami sajikan habis.
review_translated_text: Muy, muy lento. Casi 50 minutos para que trajeran los platos principales del desayuno. El jugo de naranja tenia demasiada agua. Ademas, EXCESIVAMENTE CARO. Rp 165.000 por dos platos, dos jugos (uno malo) y dos cafes.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello dear Carlos Responding to your comments regarding: 1. Slow. 50 minute wait. According to the CCTV that we replayed, you ordered at 08.55.35, the coffee order came out at 08.58.02, followed by mango juice and orange ice (no sugar), at 09.30.28 the special fried rice and chicken egg fried noodles were served at your table. . Please note that you come when the cafe is busy with visitors. Your order is in 6th place 2. Orange ice (without sugar because you dont want any additional ingredients) which you said contains a lot of water, we have pure oranges without added ice which of course will be more expensive. 3. The price of 165K is very expensive. You order from the menu list with the prices listed. Your order: special fried rice 35 K Chicken Egg Fried Noodles 25K double espresso 30K Flat white regular milk 25 K Mango Juice 25 K Orange Ice 25 K Total 165 K = approximately 10 Euros We have made it free for you and your friends to take water without paying and without restrictions. To ensure our response, we still keep order notes and CCTV recordings. However, we thank you for your visit and are happy that the dishes our Cafe Shop serves are finished.

review_text: No Doubt A Jealous Competitor. I read the Dec 20, 2023 ( Rivka JJ ) review of Adams Coffee, JL Prawiroraman 30 Yogyakarta on Google and thought to my self, what a joke!. Adams Coffee shop is constantly filled with customers who are served what is some of the best Java Coffee Indonesia has offer. In fact, I asked  the owner, the coffee is a blend of 70% premium arabica beans, 30% Robusta. The water is fresh, pure,BPA ( that harmful chemical ) free, and is precisely heated by top-of-line brewing equipment to the exact temperature required for the type of coffee drink you have ordered. Whats more, the price is right- considerably cheaper than competitors inferior Coffee. I wonder, could this Google reviewer be an envious competitor who is spamming Adams Coffee? Sound like it... Ive been coming here daily for six months along with my good friends who has been a steady customer for two years. I plan to keep coming. So does my friend.

review_translated_text: For a place with an old school concept, this place is quite comfortable and relaxing. review_text: Malam ini kami kelaparan selewat pk 21.45. Teringatlah kami dengan warung ini. Kami pesan nila goreng dan nasi uduk serta sayur kangkung. Sambalnya sambal tomat mentah, asyik. Pedas sambalnya yang enak membuat nila gorengku tambah mak nyuss! Akhirnyaaa....aku menemukan warung yang jual pecel lele dengan bersih, tempatnya enak, dan higienis, betapa senangnya!! Warung ini buka hingga pk 23.30, dan ini kucatat baik-baik sehingga suatu kali aku kelaparan selewat pk 22.00, masih ada warung ini... Apalagi harganya ekonomis banget. Lelenya sedang-sedang saja, terasa manis dan gurih dagingnya. Ikan tersebut juga digoreng dengan pas, sehingga dagingnya lembut dan tidak kering. Selain lele, ada juga bebek, ayam dan lainnya. Bisa digoreng atau dibakar, semua sama enaknya. Yang unik adalah kita boleh pilih mau sambal apa, dan di menu pilihan kita itu ada seiris tahu dan tempe goreng. Disantap dengan nasi putih dan lalap, yummy.....
review_translated_text: Tonight we were hungry after 21.45. Remember us with this shop. We ordered fried tilapia and uduk rice and kale vegetables. The chili sauce is raw tomato sauce, fun. The delicious spicy chili sauce makes my fried tilapia even more delicious! Finally....I found a stall that sells catfish pecel in a clean, tasty and hygienic place, how happy!! This stall is open until 23.30, and I noted this carefully so that one time I was hungry after 22.00, this stall was still there... Moreover, the price was really economical. The catfish is mediocre, the meat tastes sweet and tasty. The fish is also fried properly, so the meat is soft and not dry. Apart from catfish, there are also ducks, chickens and others. Can be fried or grilled, they are all equally delicious. Whats unique is that we can choose what chili sauce we want, and on the menu of our choice there is a slice of tofu and fried tempeh. Eaten with white rice and salad, yummy.....

review_translated_text: Theres no need to doubt the taste, price and quantity, five stars Just have to fix the queue problem when its busy. Just a suggestion, its better to use the queue number, so that the wait is guaranteed... if you go there when its crowded, go home disappointed. The intention was that before ordering, I wanted to maintain etiquette and let the one who came first be served, instead the one who had just arrived immediately jumped into the queue several times and was immediately served by his mother without being reprimanded. I wanted to complain but everyone didnt line up in an orderly manner, after 3 times being grabbed, my queue lasted for around 20 minutes, finally I was disappointed and went home... For other customers who read this comment, please ANTRIII!!! everyones busy, arent you the only one, dont be tacky, please bring the village customs like that.

review_translated_text: If you are looking for a variety of fruit juices at relatively cheap prices and large portions, this place could be an option. Located on Jalan Tamansiswa, this juice stall is easy to find. There are various kinds of fruit that can be processed into juice, with variations of adding milk or orange. The average price of juice here is IDR 11,000. What may be a concern is the limited parking area, both 2-wheeled and 4-wheeled.

review_text: Mohon maaf, tidak ada niat apapun hanya berbagi pengalaman. Saya seringkali beli jus disini, dan selama ini selalu aman baik2 aja walaupun agak kemanisan. Hari ini saya beli pagi sekitar jam 10, saya beli jus jambu. Tapi, mohon maaf rasanya kok sudah ga segar? Kaya udah agak seger sedikit pahit dan sedikit apa ya ngomongnya menyek gitu. Ga kaya jus2 seger jambu lainnya. Memang saya perhatikan kalau buah jambu itu sudah di jus kentel dan ditaruh di kulkasnya, jadi kalau ada yang mau beli tinggal diambil jus kentel dari kulkas terus ditambahkan air es dan gula. Bisa jadi ini campuran sisa atau mungkin terlalu pagi ngejusnya jadi jaraknya agak lama (tapi ya saya kurang paham juga). Saya kesana berniat untuk memberi tahu supaya takutnya pelanggan lain tidak merasakan yang sama dengan saya. Pas saya kesana, hmm ibunya seperti tidak terima, dikira saya mau menjelekkan nama, langsung jusnya dicicipi dan pelanggan lain disuruh mencicipi, ya kalau sedikit sesendok memang tidak terlalu kerasa, coba lebih banyak pasti kerasa karena ya baru peka rasanya berbeda. Saya sedikit digentak atau nada tinggi  namanya jus jambu memang gini mbak  uang saya dikembalikan. Tapi buktinya mas2 belakang saya ga jadi beli habis disuruh nyicipin. Saya sama sekalia tidak ada niat menjatuhkan. Karena memang saya suka beli jus disini. Tapi mohon maaf kalau kaya gini saya jadi kapok mau kesana. Saya harap semoga bisa dijadikan evaluasi kedepannya. Supaya buah bisa lebih segar dan lebih ramah lagi kepada pelanggan.
review_translated_text: Sorry, I didnt have any intention, just sharing my experience. I often buy juice here, and so far its always been fine, even though its a bit sweet. Today I bought it in the morning around 10 oclock, I bought guava juice. But, Im sorry, how come its not fresh? Its like its a little fresh, a little bitter and a little bit, what can I say? Not like other fresh guava juices. Indeed, I noticed that the guava fruit was already in condensed juice and put in the refrigerator, so if someone wanted to buy it, they just took the condensed juice from the refrigerator and then added ice water and sugar. It could be that this is leftover mixture or maybe I was juicing it too early so it took a while (but yeah, I dont really know either). I went there with the intention of telling you so that other customers might not feel the same as me. When I went there, hmm, the mother didnt seem to accept it, she thought I wanted to discredit her name, she immediately tasted the juice and other customers were told to taste it, yes, if you take a little spoonful, you wont really taste it, try more, youll definitely taste it because then youll be aware that the taste is different. I was a little nagged or in a high tone its called guava juice, thats what it is, sis my money was returned. But the proof is that in the end I didnt buy it after I was told to try it. I have absolutely no intention of dropping it. Because I really like buying juice here. But Im sorry, if its like this, Ill give up on going there. I hope that it can be used as an evaluation in the future. So that the fruit can be fresher and friendlier to customers.

review_text: Jus yang porsinya ga masuk akal tapi rasanya tetep enak?! Belom lama ini coba beli jus di sini setelah liat konten di instagram dan kepo. Karena belom pernah nyobain, aku beli jus mangga dan jus alpukat soalnya belinya berdua. Ga nyangka banget ternyata porsinya emang sebanyak itu. Satu porsi jus di sini bisa buat 2-3 orang kalo diminum, dan mungkin satu liter ada kali klo diukur. Karena minum sendiri, jadi jusnya bisa awet sampai malem. Walaupun porsinya banyak, tapi rasa buahnya tetep kerasa banget. Buat kalian yang ngga terlalu terbiasa sama manis, mungkin bisa request dikurangin gulanya karena emang cukup manis jusnya. Untuk harga jus, ada di sekitar 10k-15k waktu beli (bulan agustus 2023). Untuk minusnya, karena lokasi penjualan diapit sama tempo gelato, jadi gaada tempat buat parkir. Tapi ga terlalu masalah soalnya minuman pasti dibawa pergi. Sama kayanya belum ada di ojol (atau aku ga nemu). Padahal semingguan ini pengen banget karena cuaca baru panas, tapi males buat ke lokasi soalnya ga deket sama rumah. Rekomended
review_translated_text: Juice portions that dont make sense but still taste delicious?! Not long ago I tried buying juice here after seeing the content on Instagram and was curious. Because Ive never tried it, I bought mango juice and avocado juice because I bought both. I really didnt expect the portion to be that big. One serving of juice here can serve 2-3 people if you drink it, and maybe a liter if you measure it. Because you drink it yourself, the juice can last until evening. Even though the portion is large, the fruit taste is still really strong. For those of you who arent used to sweets, maybe you can request less sugar because the juice is quite sweet. For the price of juice, it was around 10k-15k at the time of purchase (August 2023). As for the minus, because the sales location is flanked by a gelato shop, there is no place to park. But its not too much of a problem because the drinks will be taken away. Its just as if its not available on Ojol yet (or I didnt find it). Even though I really wanted to this week because the weather was hot, I was too lazy to go to the location because it wasnt close to home. Recommended

There is WiFi and plugs, so I can work smoothly. The music is nice, not too loud. Many digital workers also share the same appreciation. The baristas are friendly. The rooftop is comfortable, suitable for unwinding after work or hanging out with friends Parking: There is only a parking area for motorbikes, it can accommodate around 10-15 motorbikes. Kid-friendliness: Maybe the children can be comfortable on the rooftop while being supervised by their family Wheelchair accessibility: There are stairs at the entrance, as far as I remember there is no access for wheelchairs. So even if the steps are few, they may still have to be lifted. The inside area is wheelchair accessible, while the rooftop area is not.

review_text: Dalem Space is a cozy and charming place to stay in Yogyakarta. It is located near the Keraton, the palace of the sultan, where you can witness the rich culture and history of Java. The rooms are spacious and comfortable, with air conditioning and Wi-Fi. The staff are friendly and helpful, and they serve delicious breakfast every morning. You can also enjoy the beautiful garden and the relaxing atmosphere of the place. Dalem Space is a perfect choice for travelers who want to experience the authentic Yogyakarta.

review_translated_text: Who likes to drink fresh milk. Please come. Location east of Lempuyangan station. Easy access from all directions Can sit on a chair. Or sit down while watching the trains pass by. Open afternoon until evening. Standard prices are not expensive and not cheap either. The atmosphere is good for chatting because its not too noisy. Traffic is also rarely jammed. Only on weekends when walking, the railway crossing gates are closed. Its also only about 5 minutes. The rest is fine.

review_text: I love the atmosphere and choco mint

Pesen nasi goreng 30rb: dptnya tanpa secuil ayam. Beras yg dipakai yg butir2 kecil patah2.. Tempe Mendoan daun bawannya seuiprittt. Tp penyajian ok. Bakmi, hambar... utk sekelas 30k. Oh iya, saya adalah pelanggan yg minta tissu sejak awal mendoan dtg... tapi pelayannya selalu lupa. Akhirnya sy turun dtg ambil sndri baru mqj diantarkan. Itupun cuma 4 lembar tissue. Pdhl butuh buat lap2 es krim.
review_translated_text: Ordered fried rice for 30 thousand: got it without a piece of chicken. The rice used has broken small grains... Tempe Mendoan has seuiprittt blanched leaves. But the presentation is ok. Noodles, bland... for the 30k class. Oh yes, I was a customer who asked for a tissue from the start and asked to come... but the waiter always forgot. Finally I went down and picked it up and then MQJ was delivered. And thats only 4 sheets of tissue. Even though I need to make ice cream wipes.

review_text: Came here and told the waiter we ll sit upstairs. But they didn t let us know that we must order from downstairs after waiting and finally went downstairs to ask. We orders 3 different snacks and it was all frozen products you can buy in supermarket. You can tell immediately. For the price they put, they could ve just make real food.

Tempat gelato yang juga menjual makanan baik western maupun lokal, di area jalan malioboro. Tempatnya lumayan ,pelayanannya samgat ramah,penyajian agak lama,dan rasa makanan  perlu peningkatan. Pesan nasi goreng nasinya benyek ,dengan harga 30rb hanya disajikan nasi dan krupuk tanpa telur,ayam  ataupun bakso.kurang worth it meski rasa lumayan. Lalapan burung puyuh (55rb) ,lalapan bebek(60rb) gak worth it juga,hanya disajikan nasi dan burung puyuh ataupun bebek,tanpa ada tambahan tahu atau tempe dan juga sambel sangat  sedikit bahkan bebek daging sedikit dan dikasih potongan kepala .es lemon tea(25rb) rasa juga sangat kurang. Rating:7/10
review_translated_text: A gelato place that also sells both western and local food, in the Malioboro street area. The place is not bad, the service is very friendly, the serving takes a bit of time, and the taste of the food needs to be improved. Order fried rice, the rice is soft, at a price of 30 thousand you only serve rice and crackers without eggs, chicken or meatballs. Its not worth it even though the taste is decent. Lalapan quail (55 thousand), lalapan duck (60 thousand) is not worth it either, only served with rice and quail or duck, without any addition of tofu or tempeh and also very little chili sauce, even a little duck meat and given pieces of head. Ice lemon tea( 25 thousand) the taste is also very lacking. Rating:7/10

review_text: Went there to celebrate a birthday. we order nadie goreng pigeon and chicken burger. Food came late and at different times. We didn t get all our food until asked them for it after being waiting for almost 40 min! Portions weren t too big. The burger was very disappointing, 4 wedges, no coleslaw just some lettuce with 4 strings of carrots 4 pieces of onion and a bit of mayo, the bread was very dried and the burger felt more a frozen burger than a proper chicken fillet, the pigeon over cooked so almost impossible to eat. Quite disappointing, we didn t even get napkins! If you look for a place to have a drink and listen to some music maybe it s ok but I won t recommend it for dine in! Sorry!

review_text: They didnt have coke or Fanta. We ordered the food and a beer and I asked if I could buy the coke in the supermarket across the street and they said yes. Of course, for the glass with ice they wanted to charge me 5000 rupees... as if it was my fault that a bar doesnt have drinks! In short, very bad

review_text: Kecewa dg pelayanan yg lama & harga teh tawar 25 rb tp g ada istimewanya.. malah kecewa. Minta teh tawar panas yg datang malah cuma teh hangat yg mendekati dingin. Hadeeeeh.. g recommended.
review_translated_text: Disappointed with the long service & the price of plain tea is 25 thousand but theres nothing special... even disappointed. Asked for hot plain tea which came instead only warm tea which was almost cold. Hadeeeeh.. g recommended.

review_text: Tgl 18 Mei 2023 kami romb 24 org makan di resto itu..dgn harga makanan yg dirasa wajar kami pesan minuman tanpa lihat lagi harga.  Pas bayar kaget luar biasa harga teh tawarnya 25 rb selisih sedikit dgn harga makanan 1 porsi.  Sah2 aja..tp tidak pantas aja. Daaan sekian  pesanan makanan kami yg datang paling awal dikirim telaaaat amp pd kelaparan sementara sebagian lain sudah pd habis.  Smg jd perhatian manajemen. Kalau mau terima pelanggan banyak siapin juga dong sdmnya yg memadai..
review_translated_text: On May 18 2023, 24 of us ate at the restaurant... with food prices that we felt were reasonable, we ordered drinks without looking at the prices. When I paid, I was really surprised that the price of plain tea was 25 thousand, a small difference from the price of 1 portion of food. Its legal... but its not appropriate. So many of our food orders that arrived early were delivered late and we were starving while others had already run out. Its also getting managements attention. If you want to receive lots of customers, prepare adequate human resources.

review_text: We went for gelato and you have to pay before you can taste the ice cream. We were going to have ice cream each anyway, so why charge us first? Not welcoming at all so that s your first impression. Then, When I started trying the flavours weren t great but of course you re pressured to have something now you ve paid! Some of the  sorbet  aren t actually sorbets and yoghurt based so DO taste before you just decide on your flavours! In the end I told the guy what kind of flavours I liked and he recommended the unlabelled ice creams they had which were nice. Overall Did not like the system of paying first before tasting/knowing what you d like , it s very unwelcoming

Makanannya enak, apalagi yang western. No kaleng-kaleng sedapnya. Aku pesan spaghetti carbonara sama chicken cordon bleu, rasanya super enak kayak di resto fine dining. Porsinya juga nggak terlalu banyak jadi beneran kenyang, jadi soal makanan nggak ada yang perlu diragukan. Gelato mereka juga rasanya kuat banget, jadi memang nggak kaleng kaleng. Tapi tempatnya ini nggak nyaman buat duduk agak lama. Meja lipat yang sekaligus kursi itu kayak terlalu kecil, duduk rasanya harus hati-hati kalau nggak mau terjungkal. Kalau mau ajak keluarga yang ada lansia dengan kebutuhan ekstra, mikir mikir lagi deh. Oh ya, bisa merokok juga di semua area, jadi kalau yang nggak suka asap rokok ada risiko terganggu. Mereka juga menyajikan alkohol jadi kalau ini masalah buatmu, baiknya cari tempat lain aja. Overall, makanannya enak banget, gelatonya juga. Tapi tempatnya ini yang rasanya beneran nggak nyaman dan kayak nggak bisa imbangi makanannya yang udah terasa super premium. Kalau tempatnya bisa lebih nyaman lagi, aku berani bilang dia sejajar dengan resto fine dining lainnya di Jogja.
response_from_owner_text: Yth Bapak Stefanus Paulus, Terima kasih telah meluangkan waktu memberikan ulasan saat berkunjung ke Malio Terrace. Terima kasih juga atas apresiasi Bapak mengenai makanan yang enak terutama western food dan juga gelato. terima kasih atas masukan Bapak mengenai kenyamanan tempat. sebagai informasi kami juga menyediakan tempat private dining room di lantai 2 dengan kapasitas 4 hingga 12 orang, tersedia juga area di indoor kitchen lantai 1 untuk kapasitas 12 hingga 15 orang menggunakan sofa. Kami nantikan kedatangan Bapak kembali ke Malio Terrace dengan pengalaman yang lebih menyenangkan. Salam hangat, Manajemen
review_translated_text: The food is delicious, especially western. No. The cans are delicious. I ordered spaghetti carbonara and chicken cordon bleu, it tasted super delicious like at a fine dining restaurant. The portions arent too big so youre really full, so theres no need to doubt the food. Their gelato also tastes really strong, so its not canned. But this place is not comfortable for sitting for a long time. The folding table and chairs seemed too small, you had to sit carefully if you didnt want to fall over. If you want to invite a family with elderly people with extra needs, think again. Oh yes, you can also smoke in all areas, so if you dont like cigarette smoke there is a risk of being disturbed. They also serve alcohol so if this is a problem for you, its best to look elsewhere. Overall, the food is really delicious, the gelato too. But this place feels really uncomfortable and doesnt seem to be able to compensate with the food which already tastes super premium. If the place could be more comfortable, I dare say it would be on par with other fine dining restaurants in Jogja.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Dear Mr Stephen Paulus, Thank you for taking the time to provide a review while visiting Malio Terrace. Thank you also for your appreciation regarding delicious food, especially western food and also gelato. Thank you for your input regarding the comfort of the place. For your information, we also provide a private dining room on the 2nd floor with a capacity of 4 to 12 people, there is also an area in the indoor kitchen on the 1st floor for a capacity of 12 to 15 people using a sofa. We look forward to welcoming you back to Malio Terrace with an even more enjoyable experience. Warm regards, Management

review_text: Penyajian lama
review_translated_text: Long presentation

review_text: We went for dinner at Malio Terrace or Massimo Gelato called it whatever you want. Set up is really nice menu is diverse however the service literally did not exist. They dont clean and sanitised tables after customers only pick up the dirty plates and when you ask then fir help they say is a self service. The weird thing is that it is not that they do not have staff, they have plenty however they seem so disengaged and bored that is hard to even get thier attention. Prices I might say is expensive as you can see from the photos of the menu posted by other customers. Food is in the best case average, they have a buffet with local food however if you order noodles you will get dry packed egg noodles which is not even remotely close to  even the simple mie cart on the streets of Yogyakarta. I personally had a burger which came a rare in best case medium rare they never asked my wife that order the burger what temperature I would like to have it. It will not be a problem if the burger was uneatable however I was struggling finding any good flavours while removing the pieces of raw meet between my teeth. My wife asked them to change and they took it away, 3 minutes later I received my burger and for my surprise it was the same burger that I tried to eat earlier they just put it back in the grill burned it and send it back, lets not forget that when the waiter tried to serve my burger the patty fell on his tray and he tried to fix it with his fingers. After realising it was the same burger the send tk me I went I request to be changed however it took me more than 5 minutes until I found someone that can speak English. At the end the burger took more than 30 min to came again on the twentieth minute I just went and ask them to canceled the order by the time we were leaving on of the staff xame running after us with the take away. I do not understand how one of the biggest hotels in Yogyakarta can tolerate such a service!!!

Gelato shop located at (or right next to) the Grand Inna Malioboro hotel. The price is cheap and it is easy to find as it is at the beginning of Malioboro Street. There is a gelato shop across the street, but I dont know how it tastes.

The ice cream is delicious and the price is also quite cheap for around the Malioboro area. The menu seems quite complete. Just because I bought it during the day, the ice melted quickly. The place is spacious, there is outdoor, indoor, and the second floor has a balcony. If youre going to Malioboro, you can try going here, its not far from the Malioboro entrance from YK station.

Berada satu area dengan Hotel Ina Garuda. Menikmati suasana Malioboro ditemani gelato dengan beragam varian rasa yang bisa dipilih sesuai selera. Paling cocok datang saat sore menjelang malam dan pilih area outdoor yang diterangi lampu-lampu membuat suasana terasa hangat dan romantis atau bisa juga pilih duduk di lantai 2 dengan view jalanan Malioboro sambil mengabadikan beberapa moment :) Selain gelato, Malio Terrace juga menyediakan menu makanan berat seperti bakmi jawa, juga camilan, serta beragam minuman.
review_translated_text: Located in the same area as the Ina Garuda Hotel. Enjoy the atmosphere of Malioboro accompanied by gelato with various flavors that you can choose according to your taste. Its best to come in the late afternoon and choose the outdoor area which is lit up with lights making the atmosphere feel warm and romantic or you can also choose to sit on the 2nd floor with a view of Malioboro street while capturing some moments :) Apart from gelato, Malio Terrace also provides a heavy food menu such as Javanese noodles, as well as snacks and various drinks.

review_text: MALIO TERRACE adalah kedai yang menyajikan gelato, pizza, snack dan aneka minuman di pinggiran Jalan Malioboro. Meja kursinya cukup banyak tersusun di halaman yang lumayan luas. Cocok untuk bersantai sambil menikmati sajian aneka menu dari Malio Terrace. Tempatnya bagus, bersih, pelayanannya baik dan bisa lebih santai duduk2 di sini. Harga setiap item menu sudah sesuai dengan kualitas dan sajiannya.
review_translated_text: MALIO TERRACE is a shop that serves gelato, pizza, snacks and various drinks on the edge of Jalan Malioboro. There are quite a lot of tables and chairs arranged in a fairly large yard. Suitable for relaxing while enjoying various menus from Malio Terrace. The place is nice, clean, the service is good and you can sit more relaxed here. The price of each menu item is in accordance with the quality and presentation.

Mas yang jaga juga lucu banget sama pacarnya, pas pacarnya dateng hahaha pasangan imut. Disini juga ada camilannya kok! Jangan takut kelaperan ya :)

Its in the same building as the barbershop, women can also get their hair cut here as long as its a boys hairstyle hahaha. Its cheap and delicious here, but unfortunately the outdoor area is limited so theres no place outside, even though its fun watching people go by at night hehe. Mas, who is on guard, is also really funny with his girlfriend, when his girlfriend comes, hahaha, cute couple. There are snacks here too! Dont be afraid of being hungry, okay? :)

review_text: Namanya Movement coffe, tapi disini tempat Barbershop. Kesini cuma mau potong rambut aja jadi kurang tau kalau nongkrong nyaman atau tidak, untuk menu saya kurang tau juga. Tapi kalau mau potomg di sini harus Booking Order dulu, nggak bisa langsung potong. Saya kemaren dateng Booking Order dulu, setelah itu kalau sudah waktunya nanti di Whatsapp. Booking Order nya bisa langsung ke lokasi atau via Whatsapp. Kalo beli minuman sekalian potong, harga minumannya beda. Saya di kasih tau sama adminnya.
review_translated_text: Its called Movement Coffee, but this is a barbershop. I just came here to get a haircut so I dont know if hanging out is comfortable or not, I dont know about the menu either. But if you want to cut here you have to book an order first, you cant cut straight away. Yesterday I came to Book Order first, after that, when its time, Ill go to Whatsapp. Booking orders can be done directly at the location or via Whatsapp. If you buy a drink and cut it, the price of the drink is different. I was notified by the admin.

review_text: good place to chill out. fyi the name changed to  movement coffee . was craving for some burger but most stuff on the menu weren t available anymore. i only ordered hot peach lemon tea &original toast, both were okay.

Harganya ramah kantong eey, hampir semua menu gak nyampe 20k kecuali burgernya doang seingetku. Suasananya nyaman juga bisa ngopi outdoor tapi tempatnya agak terbatas. Btw kalo lucky bisa dapet diskonan untuk pembelian tertentu. Karna kemaren pesen mix platter & coffee latte doang langsung dapet voucher diskon kopi 50%, cuma lupa sampe kapan event beginiannya berakhir sama S&K buat dapet voucher-nya. Kalo soal rasa kopi sayangnya bukan ahlinya, yg penting mah ngopi we sambil nongkrong.
review_translated_text: The prices are pocket friendly, almost all of the menu doesnt cost 20k, except for the burgers as far as I remember. The atmosphere is comfortable and you can drink coffee outdoors but the space is a bit limited. BTW, if youre lucky, you can get a discount on certain purchases. Because yesterday I ordered a mix platter & coffee latte and immediately got a 50% coffee discount voucher, I just forgot how long an event like this ends with the T&C for getting the voucher. When it comes to the taste of coffee, unfortunately Im not an expert, the important thing is drinking coffee while hanging out.

review_text: Keramaian yang dipertontonkan setara dengan rasa yang ditawarkan serta nuansa yang disajikan. Spot menarik, karena terletak di gedung tua; terasa seperti di Jogja jaman penjajahan. Unik, terlebih makan di lesehan. Pengunjung cukup memilih sajian yang disuka, bawa ke kasir, lalu bayar. Akan lebih enak kalau dapatkan posisi duduk terlebih dahulu agar nggak kerepotan saat siap menyantap makanan. Vegetarian options: Angkringan provides numerous meals, including the non meat-based ones. This is a neutral zone in which carnivores, herbivores, and omnivores can meet and eat together in harmonious way.
review_translated_text: The excitement on display is commensurate with the flavors offered and the nuances presented. Interesting spot, because it is located in an old building; feels like in Jogja during the colonial era. Unique, especially eating on the lesehan. Visitors simply choose the dish they like, take it to the cashier, then pay. It would be better if you get into a sitting position first so you dont have to worry when you are ready to eat your food. Vegetarian options: Angkringan provides numerous meals, including the non-meat-based ones. review_text: Tempat favorit buat beli ice coffie sepulang kerja. Sering beli yg variant ice coffie nut / mocha meltime. Level manisnya bisa dikurangi sesuai selera. Dan menurutku kopi disini bener2 manjur sih, bikin gak ngantuk. Jadi langganan kalo mau perjalanan jauh atau ngejar deadline  . Oia, beberapa kali coba cookiesnya, paling suka yg ada topping coklat nutella krn gurih manis (cookiesnya warna putih, lupa namanya  ). Brownies melted yg varian nutella enak juga. Bener2 lumer dimulut isiannya. Andaikan ada sedikit sensasi pahit dari coklatnya lebih ok sih (menurutku  ). Pembayaran bs tunai, Qris, atau debit. Overall, ok Must try
review_translated_text: Favorite place to buy iced coffee after work. Often buy the ice coffee nut / mocha melttime variant. The sweetness level can be reduced according to taste. And I think the coffee here is really effective, it makes you not sleepy. So subscribe if you want to go on a long trip or meet a deadline  . Oh yes, I have tried the cookies several times, I really like the ones with chocolate nutella topping because they are deliciously sweet (the cookies are white, I forgot the name  ). The melted brownies with the Nutella variant are delicious too. The filling literally melts in your mouth. If there was a slight bitter sensation from the chocolate, it would be better (in my opinion  ). Payment can be cash, Qris, or debit. Overall, okay Must try

review_text: Hanya sekitar 500 meter dari rumah,lokasinya strategis pas pojok perempatan, mudah pula dijangkau dari jalan raya utama ( Ring road ),sebelum trafficlight belok ke timur di jalan Jupiter sekitar 100 meter saja. Hari ini nyoba promo yang disediakan set Croffle plus 1 minuman yang bisa pilih coklat atau kopi,dan kami mencoba kopi nya,Alhamdulillah cocok dengan selera kami . Tempatnya lumayan bersih,rapi,tapi karena mungkin baru beberapa hari bertempat di Banguntapan ini,nantinya pasti akan makin baik lagi penataannya. Sukses selalu buat Melted Brownies.
review_translated_text: Only about 500 meters from the house, strategic location right at the corner of an intersection, also easy to reach from the main highway (Ring road), before the traffic light turns east on Jalan Jupiter for about 100 meters. Today tried the promo provided by the Croffle set plus 1 drink, you can choose chocolate or coffee, and we tried the coffee, thank God it suited our tastes. The place is quite clean, neat, but because we have only been in Banguntapan for a few days, the arrangement will definitely be better in the future. Always successful for Melted Brownies.

review_translated_text: Sorry, this is the rating for the new menu of melted brownies, namely croffles which are currently popular everywhere. Honestly, there are high expectations for melted brownies, in terms of the melted brownies menu there is no competition... but for the croffle menu you need to pay more attention, it really is layered like a croissant but the texture is dry, crumbly and crunchy, like eating malkist biscuits... tried croffles several times in other cafes, the texture is still good like a croissant that is soft on the inside, textured on the outside and still wet, there are layers too, this is more like a biscuit in texture, the price is indeed affordable because it is priced at only 36 thousand rupiah for 4 pieces... luckily there is a discount so I wasnt too disappointed because it didnt meet my expectations. melted brownie class
