review_text: Disini sedia biji kopi Temanggung robusta dan arabica. Green beans, roasted beans, dan ground coffee/bubuk kopi, dengan tingkat kematangan biasanya medium to fine, namun bisa disesuaikan permintaan pembeli. Kalau mau houseblend juga bisa disiapkan. Untuk menjaga kualitas, kopi yang dijual disortir lagi dengan manual picking. Bapak dan Ibu penjual sangat ramah dan mau menjelaskan dengan detil. Buka 24 jam, pasti dilayani. Bisa bayar tunai dan transfer.
review_translated_text: Here, Temanggung robusta and Arabica coffee beans are available. Green beans, roasted beans, and ground coffee/coffee powder, with maturity levels usually medium to fine, but can be adjusted to the buyers request. If you want, you can also prepare a houseblend. To maintain quality, the coffee sold is sorted again by manual picking. The sellers are very friendly and willing to explain in detail. Open 24 hours, guaranteed service. Can pay cash and transfer.

review_text: The location is on the side of Iowa Road (west of the road), the fence is constantly closed because there are small children. Only coffee from Temanggung is available at cheap prices, subscribe to cafes in Jogja. You can do Qris payment, juoos

Terima Kasih atas ilmunya pak berkah dunia akhirat. Oh ya saya juga beli kopi bubuk disini dan beliau sendiri yg mengolahnya TOP banget servicenya. Workshop kopi yg recommend banget.

Parking is very free. Quality? Very nice! Original Temanggung robusta coffee, selected beans, good roasting, soft, delicious results. Dont ask about the aroma. Freshy! Price? Not found anywhere cheaper than this yet. The price is very affordable with this good quality. RO? Of course! Recommend? Highly.

Gak sengaja mau kesini karena tempat yang mau dituju tutup dan cari-cari di sekitaran prawiratoman. Kalo gak salah tadi gak ada plangnya ya sampai akhirnya kebablasan dan baru tahu setelah baca review ternyata coffeeshop nya ada bersama di hotel, tepatnya di hotel muria. Kalo dr plangnya nampak hotel tua tapi pas masuk ternyata interior nya okay sih. Cukup nyaman. Walaupun memang gak luas ya tempatnya. Karena ingin makan dan ngopi jadi kami pesan menu aman. Americano dan makannya salted egg chicken dan aglio olio. Untuk kopinya standarnya americano, nothing spesial. Kalo untuk makanannya aglio olio nya enak sih aku suka topping pakai tuna gitu ya. Kalo untuk salted egg chicken tadi coba punya temen menurutku ya enak tapi yang gak enak banget karena tipe yang  kering  bukan yang pakai saus salted egg. Untuk lama tunggu cukupan lah gak begitu lama karena pas datang pun baru gak ada customer.
review_translated_text: I didnt want to come here on purpose because the place I wanted to go was closed and I was looking around Prawiratoman. If Im not mistaken, there wasnt a sign until I finally went too far and only found out after reading the review that the coffee shop was in the hotel, precisely at the Muria Hotel. From the sign it looks like an old hotel, but when you enter it turns out the interior is okay. Quite comfortable. Even though its not that big, the place is. Because we wanted to eat and drink coffee, we ordered the safe menu. Americano and eat salted egg chicken and aglio olio. The standard coffee is Americano, nothing special. As for food, the aglio olio is delicious, I like topping it with tuna. If you try salted egg chicken, I think its delicious with a friend, but its not really delicious because its the dry type, not the one that uses salted egg sauce. For a long wait, it wasnt that long because when we arrived there were no customers.

review_text: Small but comfortable, standard food, just B coffee. Good service, standard cafe prices

It makes a good place for work: the cafe/restaurant is spacious, bright, and air conditioned. Sockets are easily available though the wifi connection is not excellent (but still ok). The staff are friendly (including the parking attendant) and the music playlist is great! One note: I dont recommend the kwetiau, I think the noodles were still undercooked and it was too salty by my standard. I havent tried the coffee. As I can see that the review for the coffee is good, I think I should try in the next visit.

Overall Not Bad, but Nothing Special

review_text: Its a simpel coffee shop where you can get coffee based drinks. You can stop by and enjoy coffee here or just take it away. There is no snack offered here. There is no wifi. However, there are 4 tables and a bar with 3 high chairs available here, so you can chill out with your friends here. It opens from 7 AM until 10 PM. There is a toilet here. The parking area is wide enough to contain some motorcycles and 3 cars. Over all, this shop is a great idea.

review_text: Kalau kamu suka suasana sepi di tengah keriuhan pusat kota; cafe ini pilihan terbaik. Kami tidak sengaja menemukannya. Kamu bisa duduk dengan segelas kopi, beberapa halaman buku, atau layar laptop. Bagus juga kalau mau sekadar melamun. Kopi susu karamelnya enak, harga murah. Kedai kopi kecil ini tidak banyak aksesoris; tempelan-tempelan hiasan di setiap ruang. Semuanya sederhana saja. Sebuah bekas rumah tua yang disulap jadi kedai dengan kursi kursi yang pas, meja yang nyaman; semua memanggilmu untuk duduk beberapa waktu disini, dengan segelas kopi dan melihat hidup ya cuma gini gini.
review_translated_text: If you like a quiet atmosphere amidst the hustle and bustle of the city center; This cafe is the best choice. We stumbled upon it by accident. You can sit with a cup of coffee, a few pages of a book, or a laptop screen. Its also good if you want to just daydream. The caramel milk coffee is delicious, the price is cheap. This small coffee shop doesnt have many accessories; decorative hangings in every room. Its all simple. A former old house transformed into a shop with suitable chairs, comfortable tables; everyone is calling you to sit here for a while, with a cup of coffee and see life just like this.

review_text: Sebuah kafe rumahan yang nyaman sekali untuk berlama-lama di dalamnya. Lokasinya hanya sepelemparan batu dari Alun-Alun Selatan. Mungkin karena kafe baru, pelanggannya masih belum terlalu banyak. Pelayanannya luar biasa ramah. Saat datang pada sore hari sekitar jam 16.00, seorang pelayan yang sepertinya juga pemilik kafe menyambut dengan ceria dan bilang bahwa mereka baru saja buka hari Minggu itu karena ada acara keluarga sebelumnya. Waktu bertanya sudah berapa lama kafe ini berdiri, mbak yang melayani menjawab, Baru tiga bulan. Saya memesan choco latte, platter, dan roti bakar choco cheese. Rasa ketiga menu itu enak dan pas. Harganya pun pas di kantong dengan porsi yang lumayan mengenyangkan. Bahkan roti bakarnya tidak habis, padahal enak banget. Saya akan kembali lagi ke sini. Mungkin beberapa kali seminggu. Saya bahkan berkelakar dengan teman saya, Wah bisa nih jadi rumah kedua! Tempat yang cocok sekali untuk bekerja sambil laptopan atau hanya nongkrong/ngobrol bareng teman atau keluarga!
review_translated_text: A homely cafe that is very comfortable to linger in. The location is just a stones throw from South Square. Maybe because the cafe is new, there arent many customers yet. The service is extraordinarily friendly. When we arrived in the afternoon at around 16.00, a waiter who seemed to be the owner of the cafe greeted us cheerfully and said that they had just opened that Sunday because there was a family event beforehand. When asked how long this cafe had been around, the lady serving answered, Only three months. I ordered a choco latte, platter and choco cheese toast. The taste of the three menus was delicious and just right. The price is right on the pocket with portions that are quite filling. Even the toast wasnt finished, even though it was really delicious. I will come back here again. Maybe a few times a week. I even joked with my friend, Wow, this could be a second home! A perfect place to work on your laptop or just hang out/chat with friends or family!

Pesan Takoyaki disini karena ingat Takoyakinya enak. Sayangnya mngkn yg baru mbaknya kurang ngerti Takoyaki (karena dl sama masnya), jadi dikasih sausnya sampai mrebes mili banyak banget kayak kuah seblak. Alhasil Takoyaki jadi lembek banget kayak makan bakso kuah. Alhamdulillah mbaknya mau gorengin lg dua buat pembanding, kecewa tapi gak papa semoga bisa ditingkatkan. Thai Teanya terlalu panas dihangatinnya, jadi rasanya agak sangit.
review_translated_text: Order Takoyaki here because remember the Takoyaki is delicious. Unfortunately, the new lady didnt understand Takoyaki (because she was with her bro), so she gave the sauce until it oozed out a lot, like seblak sauce. As a result, the Takoyaki becomes really soft, like eating meatballs with sauce. Thank God, sis, I want to fry two more for comparison, Im disappointed but its okay, I hope it can be improved. The Thai Tea was too hot to warm, so it tasted a bit bitter.

review_text: Banyak banget varian jenis jajanannya. Jajanan yang dijual di sini ada takoyaki (dengan harga sepuluh ribu per porsinya), terus ada telur gulung (ada pilihan harga lima ribuan atau yang sepuluh ribuan), sosis bakar (harganya sepuluh ribu), ada minuman cokelat (yang original harganya enam ribu, sedangkan yang toping harganya delapan ribu). Selain cokelat, ada minuman berbagai rasa juga, yaitu rasa red velvet, taro, avocado, green tea, sama thai tea. Di sini harganya yang original delapan ribu, sedangkan yang bertoping sepuluh ribu. Oiya hampir lupa, di sini juga jual baby crab dengan harga sepuluh ribu per porsinya. Ada varian rasa original, saos jos, bbq, balado, keju, dan pedas. Overall cukup worth it buat jajan di sinisaos karena bisa beli banyak jenis jajanan cukup di satu tempat aja dan harganya juga standar. Kemarin ke sini beli takoyakinya aja sih. Seporsinya isi enam bulat dengan harga sepuluh ribu rupiah. Takoyakinya agak lembek, tapi mungkin itu karna masih panas dan kena saos. Next, mau nyobain jajanan yang lainnya
review_translated_text: There are so many different types of snacks. The snacks sold here are takoyaki (priced at ten thousand per portion), then there are egg rolls (there is a choice of five thousand or ten thousand), grilled sausages (priced at ten thousand), there are chocolate drinks (original ones cost six thousand, while the topping costs eight thousand). Apart from chocolate, there are drinks with various flavors too, namely red velvet, taro, avocado, green tea and Thai tea. Here the price for the original is eight thousand, while the one with the top is ten thousand. Oh yes, almost forgot, here they also sell baby crab for ten thousand per portion. There are original flavors, jos sauce, bbq, balado, cheese and spicy. Overall, its quite worth it for snacks at Sinisaos because you can buy many types of snacks in just one place and the prices are also standard. Yesterday I came here to buy takoyaki. A portion contains six rounds and costs ten thousand rupiah. The takoyaki was a bit soft, but maybe that was because it was still hot and covered in sauce. Next, I want to try other snacks

review_text: Bosas ecofarm simplicity : kata bosas diambil dari kata bausasran yang dipelesetkan oleh anak muda jaman sekarang menjadi kata bosas, biar keren mungkin. Hal yang paling aku suka dari bosas ecofarm simplicity yaitu sesuai dengan namanya ecofarm yang mencintai alam dan lingkungan yang berbasis pertanian lahan sempit, dengan slogan baru Apa yang aku taman itu yang aku makan apa yang di tanam? Ada kangkung, lombok, tomat, sawi, bayam, telang, jeruk pecel, dll. Dan juga ada berbagai macam hewan disini yang hidup bersama dan dipelihara, semua hidup berdampingan ada iguana, marmut, ikan lele, nila, cupang, tokek, kadal. Menurutku salah satu hutan kota di jogja berada disini, bosas ecofarm simplicity. Di samping hal itu mengenai kata simplicity, kehidupan disini sungguh penuh dengan kesederhanaan, bukan sederhana deng, tapi belajar hidup prihatin. Berkaitan dengan nongkrong nongkrong, bosas ini juga sangat cocok untuk untuk hal itu bisa mengajak pasangan, teman, saudara, sahabat dan kerabat. Perpaduan antara nongkrong dan suasana alam yang bersahabat, yang membuat teman teman betah dan tidak ingin pulang. Ada juga berkaitan dengan tes mental yang cocok untuk bagu orang muda yang mentalnya lemah. Jika ada dari antara reviewer lainnya yang mengatakan bosas ini horror atau angker dirasa tidak tepat, mungkin yang lebih tepat adalah suasana syahdu ala jaman dahulu vintage yang membuat bosas eco farm simplicity menjadi agak remang remang.
review_translated_text: Bosas ecofarm simplicity: the word bosas is taken from the word bausasran which is distorted by todays young people to become the word bosas, to make it as cool as possible. The thing I like most about Bosas Ecofarm Simplicity is that as the name suggests ecofarm which loves nature and the environment based on small land farming, with the new slogan What I garden is what I eat what is planted? There are kale, chili peppers, tomatoes, mustard greens, spinach, telang, orange pecel, etc. And there are also various kinds of animals here that live together and are cared for, all living side by side, there are iguanas, guinea pigs, catfish, tilapia, bettas, geckos, lizards. I think one of the urban forests in Jogja is here, Bosas EcoFarm Simplicity. Apart from that regarding the word simplicity, life here is really full of simplicity, not simple, but learning to live with concern. Regarding hanging out, this bosas is also very suitable for inviting partners, friends, relatives, close friends and relatives. A combination of hanging out and a friendly natural atmosphere, which makes friends feel at home and not want to go home. There are also mental tests that are suitable for young people who are mentally weak. If there are other reviewers who say that this Bosas is horror or haunted which is not appropriate, perhaps what is more appropriate is the serene, vintage style atmosphere which makes Bosas Eco Farm Simplicity a bit dimly lit.

review_text: The coffee shop is not far from the center of Jogja city. You can have manual brew coffee, latte, non coffee, and some snacks. If you feel hungry you can order instant noodle. The prices are affordable. The service is friendly. You can find a toilet and get a free WIFI here. The location of this shop is a bit hidden. You need to go through an alley to get here. You can park your motorcycles in this alley. Cars can be parked at the street before the alley, but mind your own security since there is no guard at the parking area. Over all, it is a recommended coffee shop to calm your mind.

review_text: Warmindo yang buka 24 jam.  Pengunjungnya banyak bahkan hingga tengah malam. Cocok buat nongkrong tengah malam sambil ngopi, ngobrol, atau makan malam. Ada banyak menu makanan dan minuman yang ditawarkan. Nasi Rames, Nasi Campur, Ayam, Ikan, kopi, teh, dan lain-lain. Ada wifi gratis dan banyak varian menu. Tempatnya luas dan nyaman untuk ukuran Warmindo di Jogja. Tersedia banyak meja, kursi, toilet, dan kafe. Meja dan kursi rata-rata di luar ruangan. Di dalam Warmindo juga ada kafe yang menawarkan berbagai varian kopi. Nongkrong di sini juga bisa pesan minuman di Kafe selain di Warmindo. Toiletnya tersedia di bagian dalam Warmindo. Masuknya lewat dapur. Bisa langsung ditanyakan ke penjaga warungnya. Tempat parkir juga luas untuk pengunjung yang membawa mobil atau motor. Parkirinya tepat di depan Warmindo di pinggir jalan. Tempatnya nyaman untuk ngobrol lama dan santai. Yang nyari tempat makan murah 24 jam yang ada wifinya bisa mampir di sini.
review_translated_text: Warmindo which is open 24 hours. There are lots of visitors even until midnight. Suitable for hanging out at midnight while drinking coffee, chatting or having dinner. There are many food and drink menus on offer. Rames Rice, Mixed Rice, Chicken, Fish, coffee, tea, etc. There is free wifi and many menu variants. The place is spacious and comfortable for Warmindo in Jogja. There are lots of tables, chairs, toilets and a cafe. Average outdoor tables and chairs. Inside Warmindo there is also a cafe that offers various coffee variants. Hanging out here you can also order drinks at cafes other than Warmindo. The toilet is available inside Warmindo. Enter through the kitchen. You can directly ask the stall keeper. The parking area is also spacious for visitors who bring cars or motorbikes. Park right in front of Warmindo on the side of the road. The place is comfortable for a long and relaxed chat. Those looking for a cheap 24 hour place to eat that has wifi can stop by here.

review_translated_text: The coffee place is hidden behind a booth on the side of Jl Parangtritis. It is located south of Alfamart. When I went there, I just ordered coffee. But, yes, its fun, having coffee on the edge of Jl Raya Paris, you can count the passing vehicles if you want. Hihihi

Ibar Malioboro adalah sebuah rumah makan berbentuk bar dan lounge, yang berlokasi di lantai 2, Ibis Yogyakarta Malioboro Hotel, Jalan Malioboro No. 52-58, Suryatmajan, Danurejan, Kota Yogyakarta. Terdapat area outdoor. Juga sering menampilkan pertunjukan live music dan DJ performance pada hari-hari tertentu. Juga mempunyai paket-paket tertentu untuk wine dan beverage lainnya. Juga menyediakan pilihan minuman non alkohol seperti Milky Yuzu yang segar, dengan harga Rp 25.000,-. Ibar Malioboro merupakan singkatan dari Ibis Bar and Relationship.
review_translated_text: Ibar Malioboro is a restaurant in the form of a bar and lounge, located on the 2nd floor, Ibis Yogyakarta Malioboro Hotel, Jalan Malioboro No. 52-58, Suryatmajan, Danurejan, Yogyakarta City. There is an outdoor area. Also often featuring live music performances and DJ performances on certain days. Also has certain packages for wine and other beverages. Also provides a choice of non-alcoholic drinks such as fresh Milky Yuzu, priced at IDR 25,000. Ibar Malioboro is an abbreviation of Ibis Bar and Relationship.

review_text: Kesini pas tanggal 30 desember 2018, pas malioboro lagi rame ramenya tapi tempat ini syepii sekali. Pas kesini cuma ada 4 orang di meja lain. Tempatnya sih bagus,  bersih dan pelayanan sangat sangat oke ramah. Pesen apple pie cukup enak. Tapi menurutku menunya kurang variatif, kaya gak ada gitu menu spesialnya apa atau dia spesialis di menu apa. Jadi ada indonesianya ada western tapi gak banyakk.
review_translated_text: Came here on December 30 2018, when Malioboro was busy but this place was very quiet. When I came here there were only 4 people at another table. The place is nice, clean and the service is very, very friendly. The apple pie order was quite delicious. But in my opinion the menu is not very varied, its like theres no such thing as a special menu or what menu he specializes in. So in Indonesia there are westerns but not many.

review_text: Angkringan Pak Siman ini ngga terlalu berbeda jauh dengan angkringan angkringan yang ada disetiap sudut kota Jogja. Menu yang ditawarkan mulai dari nasi kucing teri, nasi sambel, oseng tempe, mendoan, bakwan, sate usus, sate daging, sate telur puyuh, bacem tahu tempe, kacang goreng, kerupuk, tambak, aneka camilan lain. Minumanya ada teh, jeruk, jahe, kopi, dan minuman minumam sachet lainnya. Pelayanan sudah pasti ramah dan memuaskan.
review_translated_text: Pak Simans angkringan is not too different from the angkringan that are found in every corner of the city of Jogja. The menu offered ranges from anchovy cat rice, sambal rice, stir-fried tempe, mendoan, bakwan, intestine satay, meat satay, quail egg satay, tempeh tofu bacem, fried peanuts, crackers, tambak, various other snacks. The drinks include tea, orange, ginger, coffee and other sachet drinks. Service is definitely friendly and satisfying.
